    'Waters of the continental shelf in which local upwelling conditions are generated by features of the sea floor or the circulation of water masses.', '(Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Augier, 1985; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Shallow waters over permanently submerged elevated features of the continental shelf sea-floor, whether shoals, banks or reefs. ', '(Eisma and Fey, 1982: 50-51; Müller, 1998: Annex 5).');
    'Communities of marine animals and algae occupying the sea floor. Included are all communities of animals and algae of the infralittoral, circalittoral and deeper zones, situated below the level of average low spring tides, or of regular emergence through wind or atmospheric pressure variations. Also  included are communities of marine animals and algae occupying the mediolittoral zone, comprised between the low and high tide levels of average spring tides or within the regular range of wind or atmospheric pressure induced sea-level fluctuations, as well as marine assemblies installed in the supralittoral zone, reached only by spray, exceptional waves or exceptional high tides.', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin, 1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Kullenberg, 1983: 328-329; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Britton and Morton, 1989; Munda, 1991; Wallentinus, 1991; Lipkin, 1991; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999a, 1999b; Gunnarsson, 2000; Galan, 2000; Sigurdsson, 2000; Jonsson and Gunnarsson, 2000).');
    'Bathyal, abyssal, hadal and hydro-thermal benthic communities of the continental slope, the abyssal plain and its features. ', '(Pautot, 1983; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990; Francheteau, 1993).');
    'Benthic communities of the continental slope, developed on blue, coral, green or red oceanic muds, and of relatively high diversity.', '(Pautot, 1983; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990).');
    'Benthic communities of abyssal plains and abyssal hills, large relatively level areas of the deep ocean floor, covered by thin layers of biogenic or nonbiogenic oozes.', '(Pautot, 1983; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990).');
    'Benthic communities of the oceanic trenches, deep elongated subduction troughs of the ocean floor.', '(Pautot, 1983; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990).');
    'Benthic communities occupying raised features of the deep sea-floor; they include assemblages colonizing active or nonactive constructive midocean ridges, as well as those developed on asismic ridges, but with the exception of hydrothermal communities.', '(Pautot, 1983: 80-81, 84-85; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990; Munda, 1991).');
    'Highly distinctive benthic communities inhabiting the vicinity of oceanic hydrothermal vents, mostly localized along the central rift of the mid-oceanic ridges and along submerged volcanic chains of lesser ocean basins.', '(Laubier, 1983: 46-47, 121; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990; Rona, 1993; Laubier, 1993; Cann y al., 1994; Riedel, 1999; Maddocks, 2000; Lutz and Kristof, 2000).');
    'Hydrothermal vent communities of the Central Atlantic Ridge, highly distinctive from those of other known ridges, distributed in widely separated areas strewn along the ridge from Iceland (Reykjanes Ridge) to the Azores and the Kane fracture zone.', '(Laubier, 1983: 46-47, 121; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990; Rona, 1993; Laubier, 1993; Cann y al., 1994; Riedel, 1999; Maddocks, 2000; Lutz and Kristof, 2000).');
    'Hydrothermal vent communities of the Indian Ocean Ridge, represented within the Palaearctic region as here defined, in the Red Sea.', '(Laubier, 1983: 46-47, 121; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Clark, 1990; Rona, 1993; Laubier, 1993; Cann y al., 1994; Lutz and Kristof, 2000).');
    'Hydrothermal vent communities of the Marianas-Japan Ridge, represented in the Palaearctic region, as here defined, along the extreme southeastern boundaries.', '(Laubier, 1983: 46-47, 121; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Rona, 1993; Laubier, 1993; Cann y al., 1994).');
    'Hydrothermal vent communities of the Nansen-Gakkel, Knepivich and Mohns ridges, extending in Arctic seas from the Kolbeinsey Ridge, at the northern margin of Iceland to the Laptev Shelf, separated from the Central Atlantic Ridge communities by the Iceland-Greenland and Iceland-Scotland sills.', '(Cann y al., 1994; Rihm and Langseth, 1994).');
    'Highly distinctive benthic communities of large bivalves, sponges and bryozoans, inhabiting the vicinity of oceanic methane-laden seeps, mostly localized in subduction trenches.', '(Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Laubier, 1993; Lutz and Kristof, 2000).');
    'Mostly animal communities colonizing soft sediments such as mud, sand or gravel of the infralittoral and circalittoral zones. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Munda, 1991; Weslawski and Stempniewicz, 1995; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Magri, 1999; Müller, 1998: Annex 5).');
    'Communities of mostly annual algae and invertebrates developing on pebble deposits of the infralittoral and circalittoral zones. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255).');
    'Varied, strongly stratified communities colonizing underwater cliffs, reefs and rocky continental shelf seabeds. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 52-54; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 54; Bournérias y al., 1987: 70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 86-87; Bournérias y al., 1990: 72-75; Bournérias y al., 1991: 64-68; Munda, 1991: 70-78; Bournérias y al., 1992: 65-68; Weslawski and Stempniewicz, 1995; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Draganovic, 1996; Müller, 1998: Annex 5; Schembri, 1999b; Magri, 1999; Jonsson and Gunnarsson, 2000; Gunnarsson, 2000; Sigurdsson, 2000; Galan, 2000; Hauksson, 2000).');
    'Continental shelf colonies of lower plants or animals resulting in concretions and encrustations. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Draganovic, 1996; Müller, 1998: Annex 5; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Communities forming and colonizing corallogenic concretions of calcified red algae in the circalittoral zone of the Mediterranean. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Mediterranean communities associated with mediolittoral pavements of encrusting algae ([Lithospermum tortuosum]).  ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Draganovic, 1996; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Infralittoral ledges built by gastropods or polychaetes. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Communities of Atlantic, Baltic and Mediterranean mussel beds. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin, 1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988: 107-108, 119; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Munda, 1991; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999a, 1999b; Sigurdsson, 2000; Hauksson, 2000).');
    'Communities of bacteria and invertebrates colonizing the vicinity of hot or cold gas seeps of the continental shelf, often forming encrusted tubes or chimneys. ', '(Barnes and Hughes, 1988). ');
    'Infralittoral communities of coral reefs of the Red Sea, the Arabian Sea, the Persian Gulf, the South China Sea and the East China Sea.', '(Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255). ');
    'Infralittoral communities of coral reefs of the Red Sea, the Arabian Sea and the Persian Gulf.', '(Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995). ');
    'Infralittoral communities of coral reefs of the South China Sea and the East China Sea.', '(Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995). ');
    'Communities of marine invertebrates and algae colonizing the bottom and sides of caves (unit 12.7) situated under the sea or the sublittoral part of caves having an entirely, periodically or partly submerged opening.  ', '(Augier, 1982, 1985; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Boury-Esnoult y al., 1993).');
    'Invertebrate and algal communities colonizing soft sediments such as mud, sand or gravel of the intertidal zone.', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Magri, 1999; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Communities of mostly annual algae and invertebrates developing on pebble deposits of the intertidal zone.', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255).');
    'Communities of algae, invertebrates and lichens colonizing the mediolittoral and supralittoral zones of rocky shores and cliffs.', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 44-52; Bournérias y al., 1985: 52-64; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 49-58; Bournérias y al., 1987: 58-70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 75-86; Bournérias y al., 1990: 69-72; Bournérias y al., 1991: 58-64; Bournérias y al., 1992: 57-64; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Draganovic, 1996; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Cliffs and rocks of the lowest part of the mediolittoral zone, occupied by communities transitional to those of the infralittoral zone.', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 44-52; Bournérias y al., 1985: 52-64; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 49-58; Bournérias y al., 1987: 58-70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 75-86; Bournérias y al., 1990: 69-72; Bournérias y al., 1991: 58-64; Munda, 1991; Bournérias y al., 1992: 57-64; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Cliffs and rocks of the lower part of the mediolittoral zone, occupied, in particular, by encrusting algae.', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 44-52; Bournérias y al., 1985: 52-64; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 49-58; Bournérias y al., 1987: 58-70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 75-86; Bournérias y al., 1990: 69-72; Bournérias y al., 1991: 58-64; Munda, 1991; Bournérias y al., 1992: 57-64; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999b; Jonsson and Gunnarsson, 2000; Gunnarsson, 2000; Hauksson, 2000).');
    'Cliffs and rocks of the higher part of the mediolittoral zone, occupied by communities characterized, in particular, by cirriped crustaceans and soft algae. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 44-52; Bournérias y al., 1985: 52-64; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 49-58; Bournérias y al., 1987: 58-70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 75-86; Bournérias y al., 1990: 69-72; Bournérias y al., 1991: 58-64; Munda, 1991; Bournérias y al., 1992: 57-64; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999b; Jonsson and Gunnarsson, 2000; Gunnarsson, 2000; Hauksson, 2000).');
    'Communities of marine animals and lower plants colonizing mediolittoral overhangs and crevices, and the mediolittoral level of sea-caves (unit 12.7).', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 44-52; Bournérias y al., 1985: 52-64; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 49-58; Bournérias y al., 1987: 58-70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 75-86; Bournérias y al., 1990: 69-72; Bournérias y al., 1991: 58-64; Bournérias y al., 1992: 57-64; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255).');
    'Permanent saline pools of the mediolittoral zone, fed by flood tides (tide pools).', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 44-52; Bournérias y al., 1985: 52-64; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 49-58; Bournérias y al., 1987: 58-70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 75-86; Bournérias y al., 1990: 69-72; Bournérias y al., 1991: 58-64; Munda, 1991; Bournérias y al., 1992: 57-64; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255).');
    'Cliffs and rocks of the supralittoral spray zone, mostly occupied by lichens such as [Verrucaria].', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 50; Bournérias y al., 1984: 44-52; Bournérias y al., 1985: 52-64; Bournérias y al., 1985: 58-61; Bournérias y al., 1986: 49-58; Bournérias y al., 1987: 58-70; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Bournérias y al., 1988: 75-86; Bournérias y al., 1990: 69-72; Bournérias y al., 1991: 58-64; Munda, 1991; Bournérias y al., 1992: 57-64; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Pools of the supralittoral spray zone, of variable salinity, fed by rainwater, spray and occasionally waves.', '(Munda, 1991; Stewart and Church, 1992: 25).');
    'Littoral colonies of lower plants or animals resulting in concretions and encrustations. ', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin, 1983; Bournérias y al., 1983: 27; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 183-255; Draganovic, 1996; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Beds of submerged marine vascular vegetation of the oceans, seas and coastal lagoons, except those of brackish seas and lagoons. ', '(Good, 1974: 256; Heywood, 1978; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Duarte, 2001). 
');
    'Eelgrass beds dominated by [Zostera marina], established between the base of the intertidal zone and a depth of about 10 metres in Palaearctic waters of the Atlantic, the North Sea, the Baltic and adjacent seas of the northern basin.', '(Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Heywood, 1978: 276; Tutin, 1980; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984a; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Diaz Gonzales and Fernandez Prieto, 1987: 86; Ellenberg, 1988; Oberdorfer, 1990; Pott, 1992; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.4.1.1; Mossberg y al., 1995: 512; Duarte, 2001).');
    '[Zostera marina]-dominated eelgrass beds of eastern Atlantic, North Sea, Irish Sea, Norway Sea and Baltic coasts of the Eurasian mainland and its continental shelf islands, north to the Faeroe Islands and northwestern Finmark.', '(Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Hanso, 1975: 100; Heywood, 1978: 276; Tutin, 1980; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984a; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Diaz Gonzales and Fernandez Prieto, 1987: 86; Ellenberg, 1988; Oberdorfer, 1990; Pott, 1992; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.4.1.1; Mossberg y al., 1995: 512; Müller, 1998: Annex 5; Duarte, 2001).');
    'Oceanic, inshore and offshore waters and their open-water and bottom communities; marine communities of the littoral zone and of coastal lagoons, bays, inlets, estuaries and tidal rivers; coastal and azonal interior halophyte or gypsophyte communities of saltmarshes, salt steppes, salt scrubs and gypsum scrubs; coastal sand dunes, sand beaches, shingle beaches, sea cliffs, rocky shores, coastal islets, rock stacks, reefs, banks and shoals; characteristically coastal agrosystems incorporating seminatural elements.', NULL);
    'Oceanic and continental shelf waters of the world ocean and its connected seas, their associated open-water and bottom communities, and marine vascular vegetation beds; marine communities of the littoral zone and of coastal lagoons. Included within the Palaearctic realm are the waters of the Northeast Atlantic, of the northern part of the West African Atlantic, south to the latitude of the Cape Verde Islands, of the Arabian Sea and of the eastern and northern Red Sea, of the Mediterranean, of the Baltic Sea, of the Arctic Ocean east of Greenland and west of the Bering Strait, and of the northwest Pacific (Marine Region as used by the IUCN Commission on National Parks and Protected Areas, Kelleher y al., 1995: ii).', '(Molinier and Picard, 1959; Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Augier, 1982, 1985; Sorokin,1983; Hood, 1983; Kullenberg, 1983; Lofgren, 1984; Mitchell, 1987; Harmelin y al., 1987; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Britton and Morton, 1989; Lalli and Parsons, 1995; Schembri, 1999a).');
    'Pelagic biocoenoses of the world ocean, its connected seas and coastal lagoons. They can be characterized by their planktonic communities and by the composition of their nektonic or surface-feeding faunas of cephalopods, fish, sea mammals and seabirds.', '(Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Augier, 1985; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995: 9-179).');
    'Waters beyond the continental shelf. In the Palaearctic region they occupy the greatest part of the Arctic, Atlantic and Pacific oceans, of the Barents Sea,  the Sea of Okhotsk, the Sea of Japan, the Arabian Sea, the Mediterranean Sea, the Ligurian Sea, the Tyrrhenian Sea, the Ionian Sea, as well as the central part of the Aegean Sea, the Red Sea, the Black Sea, the southern Adriatic Sea, the eastern part of the northern North Sea, the southern Bering Sea. They are absent from the Baltic Sea.', '(Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Pautot, 1983: 64-72; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23; Augier, 1985; Melis, 1986: 92-94; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Oceanic waters of tropical and subtropical regions, generally of low productivity and high species diversity. In the Palaearctic, they include oceanic waters of the Atlantic north to about 40øN latitude, of the Mediterreanean, the Black Sea, the Red Sea, the Arabian Sea, the Pacific north to about 32øN latitude.', '(Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Oceanic waters of boreal, subarctic and arctic regions. In the Palaearctic, they include oceanic waters of the Arctic Ocean and its satellite seas, of the  Atlantic south to about 40øN latitude, of the North Sea, the Bering Sea, the Sea of Okhotsk, the Sea of Japan, of the Pacific south to about 32øN latitude. ', '(Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Munda, 1991; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Oceanic areas over which the warmer surface water is displaced, allowing cooler water rich in nutrients to rise to the surface. They are characterized by higher biological productivity and lower diversity.', '(Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Waters of the continental shelf, underwater plateau extending from the coast to a depth of about 100 fathoms, beyond which the continental slope falls steeply toward the ocean bottom. ', '(Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Augier, 1985; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Waters within the strong influence of land masses, both in terms of physical parameters and of fauna, often arbitrarily defined as waters less than 5 km from low water mark, waters between the continent and islands or islets well in sight of shore, and any seas of depth less than 6 metres. They include the inshore waters of the Eurasian and African continents and their nearshore islands, south to Mauritania in the Atlantic, Egypt in the Red Sea, the Arabian peninsula and Iran in the Indian Ocean, China in the Pacific, and of Greenland, Iceland, the Azores, the Madeiran archipelago, the Canaries, the Cape Verde Islands, Soccotra, the Bonin, Volcano and Marcus islands, the Commander Islands.', '(Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Augier, 1985; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Waters of the continental shelf comprised between the limits of inshore waters and the continental slope.', '(Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Augier, 1985; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
    'Continental shelf waters of the high Arctic zone, bordering middle and northern Greenland, Spitzbergen, Franz Josef Land, Novaya Zemlya, Severnaya Zemlya, the New Siberian Islands, Wrangel Island and the nothern Siberian mainland from the north coast of the Yamal peninsula eastwards. 
', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23; Bliss, 1993: 17; Weslawski and Stempniewicz, 1995).');
    'Continental shelf waters of the low Arctic zone.', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984; Bliss, 1993: 17).');
    'Offshore waters of the low Arctic region of the North Atlantic and the Arctic Ocean, off southern Greenland, Iceland, Jan Mayen, Bear Island, northern Scandinavia, northwestern mainland Russia, southern and middle Novaya Zemlya. ', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23; Munda, 1991; Bliss, 1993: 17).');
    'Offshore waters of the Chukchi Sea, the Bering Strait, the Bering Sea, the Commander Islands, Kamchatka, the northern and central Kuriles, the Sea of Okhotsk and the Tatar Straits.', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23).');
    'Continental shelf waters of the boreal (temperate, subarctic) maritime zone of the Atlantic, including the North Sea, the Baltic, the English Channel, the Irish Sea, the Bay of Biscay, bordering the coasts of Scandinavia south of the Arctic Circle, those of the Faeroes, of the British Isles and of their outlying archipelagoes, and those of mainland Europe south to Galicia, and of 
the Pacific, bordering the coasts of the southern Kuriles, Honshu, Hokkaido, Shikoku and continental Korea.', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984).');
    'Offshore waters of the Atlantic temperate region, including the North Sea, the English Channel, the Irish Sea and the Bay of Biscay, bordering the coasts of Scandinavia south of the Arctic Circle, those of the Faeroes, of the British Isles and of their outlying archipelagoes, and those of mainland Europe south to Galicia.  ', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23).');
    'Offshore waters of the Baltic Sea. ', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Kullenberg, 1983: 328-331; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23).');
