    'Offshore waters of the tropical zone of the Atlantic, bordering the Cape Verde Islands and the southern coast of Mauritania.', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23).');
    'Offshore waters of the tropical Indian Ocean and its connected seas, comprising, in the Palaearctic region as here defined, those of the northern Red Sea, of the continental shelf of Asia in the Red Sea, the Gulf of Aden,  the Arabian Sea, the Gulf of Oman, the Persian Gulf, and of the African continental shelf around Socotra.', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23).');
    'Offshore waters of the Asian continental shelf in the northern South China Sea.', '(Nelson, 1980: 25-28; Lofgren, 1984: 22-23).');
    'Waters situated over the continental slope, the steep descent from the continental shelf to the ocean bottom, an area where upwellings, water mixing or shearing and other anomalies often develop. ', '(Nicholson, 1977; Nelson, 1980; Lofgren, 1984; Augier, 1985; Fiala-Médione y al., 1987; Wood, 1988; Barnes and Hughes, 1988; Lalli and Parsons, 1995).');
