    'Salt meadows of the shores of the Atlantic and Pacific oceans and connected seas, including the Baltic, the North Sea and the English Channel, within the nemoral and boreal zones. [Aster tripolium] can be present or abundant in most western subdivisions.  ', '(Rebassoo, 1975; Beeftink, 1965, 1977; Géhu y al., 1975; Géhu and Delzenne, 1975; Duvigneaud, 1975; Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Chapman, 1977a: 5, 11-12; Parent and Burny, 1981; Dijkema y al., 1984; Drachenfels y al., 1984; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984a; Géhu, 1984a, 1986; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Noirfalise, 1986; Peinado Lorca and Rivas-Martinez, 1987; Ellenberg, 1988; Oberdorfer, 1990; Korotkov y al., 1991; Pott, 1992; Påhlsson, 1994; Müller, 1998: Annex 5).');
