    'Salt meadows of inland salt basins of the nemoral zones of western Europe and eastern Asia. Continental saltmarshes of interior middle Europe are remarkable, extremely threatened communities occurring in a few isolated stations of Saxony and Lower Saxony, Schleswig-Holstein, Thuringe, Hesse, Lorraine, Auvergne, the Midlands and southeastern Poland (lower Nida valley). They comprise this unit and continental glasswort swards (unit 15.112). ', '(Duvigneaud, 1967; Lee, 1977; Drachenfels y al., 1984; Doody y al., 1984: 121; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984a; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Dejou, 1985; Peinado Lorca and Rivas-Martinez, 1987; Trzcinska-Tacik, 1988; Ellenberg, 1988; Oberdorfer, 1990; Pott, 1992).');
