    'Formations of often large, silver-glaucous shrubs of [Limoniastrum monopetalum] with showy pink flowers in late spring, of drier parts of Mediterranean and Iberian saltmarshes, distributed locally in North Africa, the Iberian peninsula, the southern Italian peninsula, western Sicily, Lampedusa, Sardinia and Crete.', '(Rivas-Martinez y al., 1980: 50-51, 59-60; Pignatti, 1982: III 318; Asensi Marfil and Diez Garretas, 1987: 226; Conti y al., 1992: 295; Julve, 1993: 45).');
    'Low shrubby expanses of woody glassworts, seablites, sea purslanes or [Zygophyllum], characteristic of temporarily inundated saltmarshes of Canary Island coasts.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Hohenester and Welss, 1993: 14; Santos Guerra, 1993: 52).');
    'Formations of [Arthrocnemum perenne] occupying the lowest level of the saltmarshes of the coasts of Fuerteventura, Lanzarote and Isla de Lobos.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987: 523; Santos Guerra, 1993: 52).');
    'Formations of the Canario-Saharan halophyte [Zygophyllum fontanesii], associated with [Arthrocnemum glaucum], of the higher level of the saltmarshes of the eastern islands and, very locally, of Alegranza and La Graciosa.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987: 523-524; Santos Guerra, 1993: 52).');
    'Formations of [Salsola longifolia], often dense and sometimes up to 2 metres high, of Canary Island coastal marshes, barranco openings and lagoons.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987: 525).');
    'Scrubby formations of saltmarshes of the temperate coasts of the western Pacific and its connected seas.', NULL);
    'Halophile shrub formations of dry ground in low-precipitation areas of the mediterranean zone, in particular, the Iberian peninsula and Sicily, and of the Macaronesian Islands. Xerohalophile scrubs of the steppe zones are listed under unit 15.A, of the desert and semidesert regions under 7. ', '(Braun-Blanquet and Bolos, 1957; Delvosalle and Duvigneaud, 1962; Freitag, 1971; Bolos, 1973; Polunin and Smythies, 1973; Rivas-Martinez, 1977b; Bellot Rodriquez, 1979; Brullo y al., 1980; Peinado-Lorca y al., 1984: 178; Peinado and Martinez-Parras, 1984; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984; Peinado Lorca and Rivas-Martinez, 1987; Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Serrada y al., 1988; Hohenester and Welss, 1993).');
    'Shrubby formations of [Zygophyllum fontanesii], [Chenoleoides tomentosa], sea-heath, saltworts and seablites of the vicinity of the coasts of the Canary Islands.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Serrada y al., 1988; Hohenester and Welss, 1993; Santos Guerra, 1993: 56-57).');
    'Formations of [Chenoleoides tomentosa], [Suaeda vermiculata], [Frankenia laevis], [Zygophyllum fontanesii], [Polycarpaea nivea], [Atriplex halimus], [Atriplex glauca] and [Limonium spp.] forming a halophile belt in the littoral zone of the larger Canary Islands and, with somewhat modified composition, of the islets.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Serrada y al., 1988; Hohenester and Welss, 1993: 14).');
    'Formations of [Zygophyllum fontanesii] of sandy stone fields and black sands of the coastal zone of the Canary Islands.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Serrada y al., 1988; Hohenester and Welss, 1993: 14).');
    'Formations of [Salsola oppositifolia] ([Salsola longifolia]) of dry coastal areas of the Canary Islands.  ', '(Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Serrada y al., 1988; Hohenester and Welss, 1993: 64).');
    'Shrubby formations of [Suaeda vera] of the Selvagens, with [Limonium papillatum] var. [callibotryum].', '(Santos Guerra, 1993: 56-57). ');
    'Nitrophilous scrubby formations typically of dry soils and arid climates, often greyish-white and semidesert-like, sometimes including taller, denser brushes. They are most frequent in the eastern Iberian peninsula, where characteristic shrubs include [Peganum harmala], [Artemisia herba-alba], [Lycium intricatum], [Capparis ovata] and the Chenopodiaceae [Salsola vermiculata], [Salsola genistoides], [Salsola verticillata], [Suaeda pruinosa], [Atriplex halimus], [Atriplex glauca], [Camphorosma monspeliaca], [Anabasis articulata] and [Haloxylon articulatum]. ', '(Braun-Blanquet and Bolos, 1957; Delvosalle and Duvigneaud, 1962; Freitag, 1971; Bolos, 1973; Polunin and Smythies, 1973; Rivas-Martinez, 1977b; Bellot Rodriquez, 1979; Brullo y al., 1980; Peinado-Lorca y al., 1984: 178; Peinado and Martinez-Parras, 1984; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984; Peinado Lorca and Rivas-Martinez, 1987).');
    'Interior, extensive and varied, halonitrophilous scrubs of the Ebro basin, comprising both dry ground sisallares proper, as well as various more hygrophile communities of edges of salt lagoons. ', '(Braun-Blanquet and Bolos, 1957; Delvosalle and Duvigneaud, 1962; Bolos, 1973; Polunin and Smythies, 1973; Rivas-Martinez, 1977b; Bellot Rodriquez, 1979; Peinado and Martinez-Parras, 1984; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984; Peinado Lorca and Rivas-Martinez, 1987).');
    'Salt-meadow communities of the Pannonic basin, developed around depressions, usually in conjunction with meadows of unit 15.A1241, but on somewhat lower, damper ground, with  [Carex distans], [Taraxacum bessarabicum], [Juncus gerardi], [Agrostis stolonifera], [Lotus glaber], [Plantago maritima].', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Serbanescu, 1965; Vicherek, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1986; Moravec y al., 1983; Moravec, 1986; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Communities of the Pannonic basin forming a transition between salt-meadows, humid meadows and flood swards, developed on mostly small surfaces and strongly nitrified grounds, dominated by creeping herbs, in particular [Potentilla anserina], [Trifolium fragiferum], [Ranunculus repens], carpet-forming grasses such as [Agrostis stolonifera], tussock-forming sedges, in particular, [Carex secalina], [Carex hordeistichos], rushes, notably [Juncus articulatus] and [Juncus gerardi].', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Serbanescu, 1965; Vicherek, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1986; Moravec y al., 1983; Moravec, 1986; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Salt-meadow communities of the western Pannonic plain, dominated by [Eleocharis quinqueflora], with [Agrostis stolonifera], [Carex distans], [Blysmus compressus].', '(Mucina, 1993d).
');
    'Salt-meadow communities of low-lying, mostly long-inundated, areas of the Alf¿ld of Hungary and southern Slovakia, with strongly alkaline soil, dominated by [Carex divisa], accompanied by [Triglochin palustris], [Triglochin maritima], [Orchis coriophora], [Orchis palustris] and, on the highest surfaces, [Ophrys sphegodes].  ', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Serbanescu, 1965; Vicherek, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1986; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Short-grass salt-meadow communities installed on high chloride soils that remain damp to very damp year-round, surrounding endoreic depressions of the Transylvanian basin of eastern Pannonia, composed of central Asian species such as [Peucedanum latifolium], together with [Aster tripolium] ssp. [pannonicus], [Triglochin maritima], [Plantago cornuti], [Agrostis stolonifera].', '(Todor, 1947; Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Short-grass saline meadows of the Transylvanian basin, dominated by [Triglochin palustris] and [Aster tripolium] ssp. [pannonicus], with [Spergularia marina], [Cyperus pannonicus] ([Acorellus pannonicus]), [Crypsis aculeata], [Trifolium fragiferum], [Taraxacum bessarabicum], [Puccinellia distans], [Suaeda maritima].', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda and Popescu, 1991).');
    'Short-grass salt-meadow communities of the Transylvanian basin, rich in hygro-mesophile meadow species, and with [Plantago cornuti], [Scorzonera parviflora], [Trifolium fragiferum], [Aster tripolium] ssp. [pannonicus], [Triglochin maritima], [Juncus gerardi].', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda and Popescu, 1990a).');
    'Rill communities, mostly characteristic of the eastern part of the Pannonic basin, developed on lime-poor sandy or clayey solonetz soils.', '(Topa, 1939; Soo, 1957a, 1980; Serbanescu, 1965; Holub y al., 1967; Vicherek, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1982, 1986; Szujko-Lacza y al., 1982; Komaromy, 1982; Moravec y al., 1983; Moravec, 1986; Elias y al., 1991; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Communities of moist rills, mostly characteristic of the eastern Pannonic salt steppes, with a 50% to 80% cover, dominated by the small tussocks of [Puccinellia distans] ssp. [limosa] with [Mentha pulegium], [Aster tripolium] ssp. [pannonicus], [Atriplex littoralis], [Atriplex tatarica], [Kochia prostrata], [Puccinellia distans] ssp. [distans], [Chenopodium botryodes].  ', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1982, 1986; Szujko-Lacza y al., 1982; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Communities of dry rills, sparse and species-poor, mostly characteristic of the eastern Pannonic salt steppes, though extending west to the Neusiedlersee (Lake Ferto), dominated by [Camphorosma annua], with [Chamomilla recutita], [Matricaria perforata], and, on more silty soils [Spergularia rubra], [Spergularia marina], [Spergularia media].', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1982, 1986; Szujko-Lacza y al., 1982; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Rare formations of dry rills of the eastern Pannonic salt steppes, characteristic of extreme dry conditions, with [Bassia sedoides]. ', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1982, 1986; Szujko-Lacza y al., 1982; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Communities of moist rills, wet until the beginning of summer, mostly characteristic of the eastern Pannonic salt steppes, with [Pholiurus pannonicus], [Plantago tenuiflora], [Myosurus minimus] and the blue alga [Nostoc commune]. They reach their western limit at the Neusidlersee (Lake Ferto) where they are extremely rare and endangered. ', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1982, 1986; Szujko-Lacza y al., 1982; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Halonitrophile, zooanthropogenous formations of the Pannonic salt steppes dominated by [Hordeum hystrix] ([Hordeum geniculatum]) and [Puccinellia distans] ssp. [limosa] with [Agrostis stolonifera], [Elymus repens], [Lotus tenuis] ([Lotus glaber]), [Artemisia santonicum] ssp. [santonicum], [Scorzonera cana].', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1981, 1982, 1986; Szujko-Lacza y al., 1982; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Poolside and rill communities, mostly characteristic of the western part of the Pannonic basin, developed on lime-rich sandy or clayey solonchak soils.', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Vicherek, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1986; Mucina, 1993d).');
    'Rill formations of the Alf¿ld and of the Danube-Tisza interfluve, with large tussocks of [Puccinellia distans] ssp. [limosa] surrounding bare low-lying surfaces.  Characteristic species include [Lepidium cartilagineum] ssp. [crassifolium], [Tetragonolobus maritimus], [Plantago maritima], [Aster tripolium] ssp. [pannonicus] and the extinct [Puccinellia pannonica].', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1986; Mucina, 1993d).
');
    'Endemic community of the Seewinkel, in the eastern Neusiedlersee (Lake Ferto) basin, developed along the shores of salt pools on solonchaks that remain wet until the beginning of summer, with [Puccinellia festuciformis] ssp. [intermedia] ([Puccinellia peisonis]), [Aster tripolium] ssp. [pannonicus], [Cerastium diffusum] ssp. [subtetrandrum], [Plantago maritima].', '(Mucina, 1993d).
');
    'Sparse communities of hollows of the western Pannonic salt steppes, in particular of the Neusiedlersee (Lake Ferto) basin, of eastern Transdanubia and of the Danube-Tisza interfluve, developed on higher, drier ground than those of units 15.A141 and 15.A142.', '(Soo, 1957a, 1980; Szujko-Lacza, 1986; Mucina, 1993d).
');
    'Endemic community of the Seewinkel, in the eastern Neusiedlersee basin, developed along the shores of salt ponds, where it occupies higher ground or more landward locations of the solonchak belt than the [Puccinellia] swards of unit 15.A142, and is submitted to more extreme conditions of high saltiness and summer soda efflorescences resulting from a briefer annual period of soaking and less frequent inundations. [Lepidium cartilagineum] ssp. [crassifolium] dominates alone or in association with [Puccinellia festuciformis] ssp. [intermedia] ([Puccinellia peisonis]).', '(Mucina, 1993d).
');
    'Interior halophile communities of the southwestern Balkan peninsula, isolated southwestern outlyers of the Ponto-Pannonic formations, developed in the low rainfall areas of the Vardar-upper Morava trough and and of associated or neighbouring small intermontane basins, in particular, within the Pelagonian and Moeso-Macedonian mountains.', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 184, 271-272).');
    'Salt-meadow communities of medium tall often tussock-forming grasses of the intermontane basins of the southwestern Balkan peninsula, recorded, in particular, from the northern Vardar and Strumica basins in the F.Y.R. of Macedonia and from Albania.', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 184, 273; Hoda y al., 1998: 10).');
    'Rill communities of interior salt-steppe and saltmarsh complexes of intermontane basins of the southwestern Balkan peninsula, in particular, of the Vardar trough of the F.Y.R. of Macedonia, with [Camphorosma annua], [Puccinellia festuciformis] ssp. [convoluta], [Pholiurus pannonicus], [Plantago tenuifolia].', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 271-272).');
    '[Camphorosma monspeliaca]-dominated formations of saline flats of intermontane basins of the southwestern Balkan peninsula, recorded, in particular, from the  Vardar trough in the F.Y.R. of Macedonia.', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 271-272).');
    'Salt steppes of the central F.Y.R. of Macedonia developed in the Vardar trough between Titov Veles, Stip and Negotino.', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 272).');
    'Salt steppes and saltmarshes of the western and northern Black Sea and Sea of Azov plain, of the basins of the lower Danube, the Prut, the Dniester, the Dnieper, the Don, and of the southern Russian hills, north of the Caspian depression and west of the Volga-Kama trough, associated with the steppes of unit 34.92. Coastal saltmarshes of the Black Sea and Azov Sea.', '(Walter, 1974; Chapman, 1977a; Tolmachev, 1980: 36-37; Sanda y al., 1980; Walter and Breckle, 1986: 183, 232; Korotkov y al., 1991).');
