', '(Serbanescu, 1965; Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Communities of the western Pontic region forming a transition between salt-meadows, humid meadows and flood swards, developed on mostly small surfaces and strongly nitrified ground, dominated by creeping herbs, in particular [Potentilla anserina], [Trifolium fragiferum], [Ranunculus repens], carpet-forming grasses such as [Agrostis stolonifera], tussock-forming sedges, in particular [Carex secalina], [Carex hordeistichos], rushes, notably [Juncus articulatus] and [Juncus gerardi].', '(Sanda y al., 1980; Chifu y al., 1991).');
