    'Communities occupying small, permanently humid, weakly saline depressions of the Sarmatic salt-steppes and saltmarshes.', '(Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Meso-hygrophile hay meadows of Moldavia, developed on weakly saline soils, with [Leuzea salina], [Peucedanum latifolium], [Iris halophila], [Aster sedifolius], [Scorzonera austriaca] var. [aucronata], [Lotus tenuis], [Taraxacum bessarabicum], [Juncus gerardi], [Aster tripolium] ssp. [pannonicus], [Plantago schwarzenbergiana], [Limonium gmelinii].', '(Topa, 1939; Ravarut, 1958; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda and Popescu, 1990a).');
    'Sarmatic saline meadows formed on alluvial sandy, weakly saline soils, with a high diversity of halophile species, with [Iris halophila], [Camphorosma annua], [Juncus gerardi], [Puccinellia distans], [Atriplex littoralis].

 ', '(Ravarut y al., 1968; Serbanescu I., 1965; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda and Popescu, 1990a).');
    'Communities of [Juncus gerardi] with [Aster tripolium], [Puccinellia limosa], [Spergularia media], [Lotus tenuis], [Trifolium fragiferum], [Centaurium pulchellum].
', '(Ravarut y al., 1963).');
    'Sarmatic formations dominated by [Carex distans], of soils with low humidity and very low salinity.', '(Mititelu, 1971).');
    'Communities dominated by grasses, chenopods or sea-lavenders, formed on solonetz or solonchak-solonetz soils in the rills of salt steppes of the Sarmatic region.', '(Korotkov y al., 1991: 68-69, 70).');
    'Grassy formations of Sarmatic solonetz and solonchak-solonetz soils constituted by [Puccinellia distans] ([Puccinellia limosa]) or [Puccinellia festuciformis] ssp. [convoluta], accompanied by [Plantago maritima], [Spergularia media], [Aster tripolium], [Juncus gerardi], [Scorzonera austriaca] and [Camphorosma annua].
', '(Ravarut y al., 1956; Walter, 1974: 194; Korotkov y al., 1991: 70).');
    'Communities of solonetz or solonchak-solonetz soils of river terraces of the Sarmatic region dominated by [Camphorosma annua], often accompanied by [Puccinellia distans] or [Puccinellia festuciformis].', '(Walter, 1974: 194; Korotkov y al., 1991: 70).');
    'Communities of solonetz or solonchak-solonetz soils of the Sarmatic region dominated by [Carex distans], with [Aster tripolium], [Juncus compressus], [Taraxacum bessarabicum] and [Agrostis stolonifera] ([Agrostis stolonizans]).', '(Walter, 1974: 194). ');
    'Communities dominated by perennial grasses and herbs or by steppe and semidesert zone annuals, developed on solonchak soils of the Sarmatic region.', '(Korotkov y al., 1991: 52, 67-68, 72, 157-159).');
    'Solonchak swards, of Ponto-Pannonic affinities, of northern Moldavia, massively dominated by [Lepidium cartilagineum] ssp. [crassifolium], with [Puccinellia distans] ssp. [limosa] ([Puccinellia limosa]), [Camphorosma annua], [Agropyron elongatum], [Plantago maritima], [Spergularia media], [Dianthus guttatus].', '(Serbanescu, 1965; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda and Popescu, 1990a; Mucina, 1993d).');
