    'Halonitrophilous communities of Black Sea sand beaches dominated by [Lactuca tatarica], with [Glaucium leiocarpum], [Glaucium flavum], [Apera spica-venti] ssp. [maritima], [Salsola soda], [Euphorbia peplis].', '(Morariu, 1957; Dihoru and Negrean, 1976; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda and Popescu, 1990b; Lovric, 1993c: 484; Meshinev and Apostolova, 1994).');
    'Halonitrophilous communities of Black Sea sand beaches dominated by [Argusia sibirica] ([Tournefortia sibirica]), with [Cakile maritima], [Salsola soda], [Elymus sabulosus], [Eryngium maritimum], [Gypsophila perfoliata], [Aeluropus littoralis], [Puccinellia distans] ssp. [limosa], [Plantago maritima], [Cynodon dactylon]. ', '(Morariu, 1957; Dihoru and Negrean, 1976; Popescu and Sanda, 1976; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda and Popescu, 1990b; Hanganu y al., 1994).');
    'Halonitrophilous communities of Black Sea sand beaches dominated by [Petasites spurius] with [Argusia sibirica], [Bromus squarrosus], [Corispermum nitidum], [Lactuca serriola], [Trifolium fragiferum], [Salsola kali] ssp. [tragus], [Eryngium maritimum].', '(Morariu, 1957; Dihoru and Negrean, 1976; Sanda y al., 1980; Hanganu y al., 1994).');
    'Annual communities of driftlines of the temperate and subtropical western Pacific and its connected seas, including those of southern Amurland, Japan, Korea and China.', '(Kolbek y al., 1989; Miyawaki and Suzuki, 1993: 167-168).');
    'Perennial halonitrophilous communities of sand, gravelly sand and gravel cordons of upper beaches of the arctic and boreal sea coasts of Eurasia formed by [Leymus arenarius] ([Elymus arenarius]), [Ammophila arenaria], [Honkenya peploides], [Elymus farctus], [Elymus repens], [Mertensia maritima], accompanied by [Atriplex spp.] ([Atriplex prostrata], [Atriplex longipes] ssp. [praecox], [Atriplex glabriuscula]), [Polygonum aviculare], [Cakile maritima], [Cakile arctica], [Petasites spurius], [Potentilla anserina]. Representatives of these communities occur very locally within the nemoral zone.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Géhu, 1984a, 1985; Oberdorfer, 1990: 27; Pott, 1992: 206, 207; Bliss, 1993: 18; van der Maarel, 1993c; Påhlsson, 1994; Géhu, 1996: 36).');
