    '[Leymus arenarius]-dominated perennial halonitrophilous communities of southern and central Baltic upper beaches, often with [Petasites spurius].', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 4.1.2.9 [p.], 4.1.1.6 [p.]; Géhu, 1985: 30, 35, region 2d, 39, 50; Oberdorfer, 1990: 27; Påhlsson, 1994: units 4.1.3.1 [p.], 4.2.1.5 [p.]; Müller, 1998: Annex 5).');
    'Perennial halonitrophilous communities of the upper beaches of the Gulf of Bothnia dominated by [Leymus arenarius] and [Festuca rubra] ssp. [arenaria].', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 4.1.2.9a [p.], 4.1.1.6 [p.]; Géhu, 1985: 30, 35, region 2b, 39, 50; Påhlsson, 1994: units 4.1.3.1 [p.], 4.2.1.5 [p.]).');
    'Perennial halonitrophilous communities of upper beaches of Iceland dominated by [Leymus arenarius] or [Mertensia maritima].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b; Hadac, 1970; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Géhu, 1985; van der Maarel, 1993c; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    '[Leymus arenarius]-dominated perennial halonitrophilous communities of upper beaches of Iceland, with irradiations in the Faeroe Islands. Accompanying plants include [Honkenya peploides], [Potentilla anserina], [Cakile arctica], [Silene uniflora].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 86; Hadac, 1970: 138-139; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 4.1.2.9a [p.], 4.1.1.6 [p.]; Géhu, 1985: 30, 35, region 2a [p.], 39, 49; van der Maarel, 1993c: 490; Påhlsson, 1994: units 4.1.3.1a, 4.2.1.5 [p.], 4.2.1.6 [p.]; Fridriksson, 2000).');
