    'Upper shore communities of arctic shores dominated by [Mertensia maritima], often in almost pure stands. On the arctic coasts of Scandinavia, they form a belt between annual driftline communities and the [Festuca]-[Leymus] formations of unit 16.1351; in Greenland they are of local occurrence, particularly on the southwestern coast, with isolated occurrences in Thule and in the Ammassalik area of the east coast.', '(Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.2.8; Bliss, 1993: 18, 20; Géhu, 1985: 49; van der Maarel, 1993c: 489; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.2.8; Gensbol, 1996: 88, 408).');
