    'Oak woods of the geographically isolated Pannonic basin wooded steppe zone, separated from the main Ukraino-Russian belt by the Carpathian arc. ', '(Wendelberger, 1954; Zolyomi, 1957; Horvat y al., 1974; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 211-212; Chytry, 1997; Chytry, 1998).');
    'Oak woods on black or brown soils over loess substrates of the Pannonic basin and its hills, dominated by [Quercus cerris], [Quercus pubescens], [Quercus robur] or [Quercus petraea]; the upper part of the well-stratified shrub layer is composed mainly of [Acer tataricum] and [Acer campestre], the herb layer of [Festuca rupicola], [Brachypodium pinnatum], [Brachypodium sylvaticum], [Melica altissima], [Nepeta pannonica], [Phlomis tuberosa], [Pulmonaria mollissima], [Doronicum hungaricum], [Polygonatum odoratum], [Buglossoides purpurocaerulea] ([Lithospermum purpurocaeruleum]). Formerly extending in the entire Pannonic basin, from Hungary and southern Slovakia to the Srijem area of northeastern Croatia and northwestern Serbia and the Deliblat region of northeastern Serbia, these forests have been reduced to a few dozen remnant stands.', '(Zolyomi, 1957; Horvat y al., 1974: 284-288; Soo, 1980: 537; Fekete, 1992; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 211-212; Chytry, 1997: 229-230; Chytry, 1998: 169-172, unit 31).');
    'Rare oak woods of the Danube basin lowlands developed in the transition zone between inundation areas and loess plateaux, on soils with a higher water table in spring. [Acer tataricum], growing with great vitality, reaches the second tree layer. Characteristic understorey species are [Carex michelii], [Pulmonaria mollissima], [Doronicum hungaricum] accompanying [Alopecurus pratensis], [Melica altissima], [Festuca rupicola], [Brachypodium sylvaticum], [Geranium robertianum], [Polygonatum latifolium], [Corydalis bulbosa] ([Corydalis cava]), [Ranunculus ficaria], [Viscaria vulgaris]; tall herbs ([Peucedanum officinale], [Galatella punctata]) and other species ([Artemisia pontica], [Limonium gmelinii i.a.])  penetrate the wood from the bordering grasslands on alkaline soil.  Only a few stands of this community remain, in Hungary and Transsylvania. ', '(Zolyomi and Tallos, 1967; Tallos and Toth, 1968; Soo, 1980; Fekete, 1992). ');
    'Oak woods of sandy substrates of the Pannonic plain. ', '(Horvat y al., 1974; Chytry, 1997; Chytry, 1998).');
    'Low, open woods of [Quercus robur] on lowland sands with a very low water table, sometimes accompanied by [Acer campestre] and [Pyrus pyraster]. The shrub layer is most commonly of [Acer campestre], [Sambucus nigra], [Ligustrum vulgare] and [Prunus spinosa] and is accompanied by a grassy, xylophilous herb layer including [Brachypodium pinnatum], [Poa angustifolia], [Trifolium alpestre], [Dictamnus albus], [Peucedanum oreoselinum], [Veronica spuria] ssp. [foliosa], [Pulmonaria mollissima]. These woods, restricted to Hungary, have been greatly reduced. ', '(Soo, 1934, 1980; Hargitai, 1940; Horvat y al., 1974; Fekete y al., 1992).');
    'Well developed oak woods on lowland sands with a higher spring water table, of Hungary and northwestern Romania. [Quercus robur] is sometimes accompanied by [Quercus cerris], [Fraxinus angustifolia] ssp. [pannonica], [Populus alba], [Populus tremula] and has a rich shrub layer including [Cornus sanguinea], [Ligustrum vulgare], [Corylus avellana], [Euonymus europaeus]. The understorey comprises flood plain elements ([Agropyron caninum], [Rubus tomentosus]); mesophilous species ([Stachys sylvatica], [Salvia glutinosa], [Circaea lutetiana]) and xerophilous elements [Buglossoides purpurocaerulea] ([Lithospermum purpurocaeruleum]), [Asparagus officinalis], [Vicia pisiformis], [Geranium sanguineum]. The floristic richness of these woods is jeopardized by a lowering water table.', '(Soo, 1934, 1980; Hargitai, 1940; Zsolt, 1943; Horvat y al., 1974; Fekete y al., 1992.)');
    '[Quercus pubescens] woods of dry sands of Deliblat, with [Tilia tomentosa], [Prunus mahaleb], [Fraxinus ornus], [Acer campestre], [Ligustrum vulgare], [Crataegus monogyna], [Thalictrum minus]. ', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 291).');
    'Tall, open woods of [Quercus robur] developed on siliceous sands of southern Moravia deposited over calcareous clays and with base-rich ground water, with a sparse shrub layer and species-rich field layer that includes thermophilous oak forest and forest-edge species, species of intermittently wet soils, species of mesophile grasslands and acidophilous species of mesic or xeric habitats, among them [Geranium sanguineum], [Iris variegata], [Trifolium alpestre], [Vincetoxicum hirundinaria], [Molinia caerulea], [Potentilla alba], [Ajuge reptans].', '(Chytry, 1997: 230-231; Chytry, 1998: 173-175, unit 32). ');
    'Communities of solonchak depressions of the Sarmatic region, with a strongly fluctuating water regime that may include acute periods of drought, dominated by [Beckmannia eruciformis], [Agrostis stolonifera] ([Agrostis stolonizans]), [Puccinellia distans], [Juncus compressus], characteristic, in particular, of the middle Don region.', '(Walter, 1974: 194; Korotkov y al., 1991: 157-159).');
