    'Salt steppes and saltmarshes of Transbaikalia, Outer Mongolia, Inner Mongolia, the Songnen Plain of Northeast China, the western Loess Plateau of North China, of the Tien Shan, from the rim of the Naryn and Isyk-K¿l basins eastwards, of the Sayan and Tannu mountains, associated with the steppes of unit 34.94. Saltmarshes of the inland waterbodies of the Gobi, Takla Makan, Tarim, Lop-nor, Bei-shan, Ala-shan, Ordos, Tsaidam and Pamyro-Tibetan Central Asiatic deserts and semideserts.', '(Walter, 1974; Chapman, 1977a; Walter and Breckle, 1986: 184, 232; Mei''e y al., 1985: 152-153).');
    'Salt steppes and saltmarshes of steppic areas of the Anatolian Plateau, of Transcaucasia, of the eastern cis-Caucasian hills of Daghestan and the Terek basin, of the Iranian Plateau, the Kopet Dagh, the Pamir-Alai, the extreme western Tien-Shan, around the rim of the Ferghana basin and along the spur of the Karatau, and of northern Mesopotamia, associated with the steppes of unit 34.95. Saltmarshes of the cold desert or subdesert areas of the Iranian Plateau.', '(Zohary, 1963, 1973; Walter, 1979; Walter and Breckle, 1991c).');
    'Salt steppes and saltmarshes of the western Anatolian Plateau, mostly characteristic of Lycaonia, particularly around Tuz Golu and in the region of Nigde. They are rich in endemic as well as Asiatic species. ', '(Davis, 1967; Zohary, 1973: 469-470; Noirfalise, 1987: unit Y6). ');
    'Almost monospecific formations of [Halocnemum strobilaceum] forming the inner belt of vegetation around western Anatolian salt lakes.', '(Davis, 1967; Zohary, 1973: 469-470). ');
    'Formations of [Artemisia fragrans], [Aeluropus lagopoides], [Camphorosma monspeliaca], [Limonium iconium], [Salsola inermis], [Salsola anatolica], [Salsola kali] forming the outermost belt of vegetation of western Anatolian halophile complexes, in contact with nonhalophile [Artemisia] steppes. ', '(Davis, 1967; Zohary, 1973: 469-470). ');
    'Communities of rosette-forming sea-lavenders, prostrate perennial [Frankenia], annual [Petrosimonia] and related genera occupying clearings of Anatolian grassy or shrubby salt steppes, in particular on hypersaline soils with extreme regimes of inundation and dessication.', '(Davis, 1967; Zohary, 1973: 469-470). ');
    'Communities of [Frankenia hirsuta], [Limonium iconium], [Limonium gmelinii], [Camphorosma monspeliaca] forming on gently sloping rises in the vicinity of Anatolian salt lakes. ', '(Davis, 1967; Zohary, 1973: 469-470). ');
    'Formations of [Petrosimonia nigdeensis], [Petrosimonia brachiata], [Halanthium kulpianum] ([Petrosimonia birandii]) occupying muddy sand soils in the vicinity of Anatolian salt lakes.', '(Davis, 1967; Zohary, 1973: 469-470). ');
    'Communities [Puccinellia distans] [s.l.], [Limonium gmelinii], [Limonium globuliferum] of western Anatolian halophile complexes, forming on sandy clay soils with brief periods of inundation.', '(Davis, 1967; Zohary, 1973: 469-470). ');
    'Saltmarsh meadows of water-logged depressions, puddles and small waterbodies of Anatolia, with [Juncus maritimus] dominant, [Limonium globuliferum], [Aeluropus lagopoides], [Puccinellia distans], [Halimione portulacoides], [Lepidium cartilagineum].', '(Zohary, 1973: 469-470).');
    'Salt steppes and saltmarshes of Transcaucasia, the eastern cis-Caucasian hills of Daghestan and the Terek basin, eastern Anatolia and northwestern Iran, including the communities of the edges of Lake Van and Lake Urmia.', '(Zohary, 1963; Zohary, 1973: 469-470; Walter, 1974: 397-398; Botch and Masing, 1983; Noirfalise, 1987; Walter and Breckle, 1991c: 108-119). ');
    'Salt steppes and saltmarshes of steppic areas of the Central and Eastern Iranian Plateau in Iran and Afghanistan, of the Kopet Dagh, the Pamir-Alai and the extreme western Tien-Shan, around the rim of the Ferghana basin and along the spur of the Karatau, associated with the steppes of unit 34.953. Communities of saltmarshes and temporary waterbodies of the cold desert or subdesert areas of Iran and Afghanistan, in particular the Dasht-i-Kewir and Dasht-i-Lut.', '(Zohary, 1963, 1973; Walter, 1979; Walter and Breckle, 1991c).');
    'Salt steppes and saltmarshes of the Mesopotamian steppic region bordering the Near Eastern Saharo-Sindian deserts, extending north to southeastern Turkey and Khuzestan in western Iran. Among characteristic species are [Suaeda palaestina], [Seidlitzia rosmarinus], [Alhagi maurorum], [Bassia eriophora], [Suaeda fruticosa], [Atriplex leucoclada], [Atriplex halimus], [Suaeda aegyptiaca], [Juncus maritimus] var. [arabicus].', '(Zohary, 1963, 1973: 227, 461-467; Noirfalise, 1987). ');
    'Salt steppes and interior saltmarshes of the steppic regions of the North African transition zone between the Mediterranean region and the Sahara ("Mauritanian Steppe").', '(Le Houérou, 1969: 237-238, 299-303; Zohary, 1973; Chapman, 1977a: 3; White, 1983: region XVIII; Géhu y al., 1993).');
    'Salt meadows, salt steppe meadows, swamp meadows, alases and salt marshes of the middle Lena basin of eastern Siberia, formed in regions of extreme continentality near the southern edge of the permafrost and the northern limit of the taiga belt, associated with the steppes of unit 34.96.', '(Walter, 1974: 89-90; Mirkin y al., 1985: 369-379; Walter and Breckle, 1986: 396-401; Korotkov y al., 1991: 55, 80-84, 97, 131, 138-139).');
    'Coastal saltmarshes of the Arctic zone, along the coasts of Greenland, the Norwegian Sea, Greenland Sea, Barents Sea, Kara Sea, Laptev Sea, East Siberian Sea, Chukchi Sea and Glacial Ocean coasts of northern Iceland, Jan Mayen, Spitsbergen, Bear Island, Finnmark in northern Norway, Franz Josef Land, northern continental Russia, Kolguyev Island, Novaya Zemlya, continental Siberia and the Siberian archipelagoes.', '(Chapman, 1977a; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984: 34-35; Dijkema, 1984a: 69-70; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Hadac, 1989; Bliss, 1993: 18-20; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Species-poor communities of the lower shores of arctic Eurasia and Greenland, submitted to winter sea ice.', '(Chapman, 1977a; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984: 34-37; Dijkema, 1984a: 69-70; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Hadac, 1989: 134, 135-138; Bliss, 1993: 18-20; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Open, sparse communities of the lower, intertidal, sector of saltmarshes of arctic coasts of Eurasia, from northern Troms and Finnmark eastwards, of the archipelagoes of the Eurasian polar basin, including Spitzbergen, Nova Zemlya,  and the New Siberian archipelago, of Jan Mayen and of Greenland, dominated by [Puccinellia phryganodes] [s.l.]', '(Walter, 1974: 26-27; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.3.4a; Dijkema, 1984a: 69; Hadac, 1989: 134, 136; Bliss, 1993: 18-20; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.3.5a).');
    'Lower shore salt meadow communities of northwestern Greenland, northeastern Greenland, Iceland, Spitzbergen, arctic Norway, the Kola peninsula, Yakutia, developed on clay substrates, dominated by [Carex subspathacea], often accompanied by [Puccinellia maritima] and [Puccinellia phryganodes]. In Iceland, [Puccinellia phryganodes] is absent and [Puccinellia capillaris] may codominate with [Carex subspathacea].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 88; Dijkema, 1984a: 69; Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.3.4; Hadac, 1989: 134, 136-137; Bliss, 1993: 18-19; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.3.5).');
    'Salt meadows of the lower and middle shores of the coasts of arctic Eurasia, in particular, of western Iceland, western Finnmark, the Kola peninsula and Yakutia, dominated by [Puccinellia maritima].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 88; Dijkema, 1984a: 69, 70; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.3.1; Bliss, 1993: 19; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.3.1 [p.]).');
    'Salt meadow communities of the lower and middle shores of arctic coasts, in particular of northeastern Greenland, Spitzbergen, Nova Zemlya, Yakutia, dominated by [Carex ursina].', '(Walter, 1974: 26; Dijkema, 1984a: 69, 70; Hadac, 1989: 134, 135-138; Bliss, 1993: 19).');
    'Coastal saltmarshes of the upper shores of arctic Eurasia and Greenland submitted to winter sea ice.', '(Chapman, 1977a; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984: 34-37; Dijkema, 1984a: 69-70; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Bliss, 1993: 18-20; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Upper shore salt meadow communities of arctic coasts of northern Norway, the Kola peninsula, Iceland and Greenland, extending locally along boreal-Atlantic coasts in Iceland and northwestern Norway, as well as in the Gulf of Bothnia, dominated by [Carex glareosa] and [Festuca rubra], often with [Gentianella detonsa], [Potentilla egedii], [Stellaria humifusa], [Carex subspathacea] and with abundant [Drepanocladus uncinatus] in the ground layer.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 89; Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984: 34, 37; Dijkema, 1984a: 69; Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.2.4; Bliss, 1993: 18-19; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.2.1c).');
    'Middle and upper shore communities of Iceland dominated by [Kobresia myosuroides], with [Rhacomitrium lanuginosum] often very prominent, occupying relatively dry, high, stony areas of coastal banks.', '(Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.2.1b; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.2.1b).');
    'Usually open saltmarsh communities of upper shores of arctic Eurasia dominated by [Puccinellia capillaris] ([Puccinellia distans] ssp. [borealis]) with [Festuca rubra] and [Cochlearia officinalis], characteristic, in particular, of exposed wet shingle beaches with little fine material in northern Norway and northern Iceland.', '(Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.2.7 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.2.7 [p.]).');
    'Saltmarsh communities of upper shores of arctic Eurasia, in particular, of northern Norway and northern Iceland, constituting a fescue-dominated facies of unit 15.B23.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 89; Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.2.7 [p.]; Bliss, 1993: 19; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.2.7 [p.]).');
    'Communities of arctic coasts dominated by [Dupontia fisheri], [Dupontia pelligera] or [Dupontia psilosantha], characteristic, in particular, of brackish upper shores of Greenland, Spitzbergen, the New Siberian archipelago, Yakutia. ', '(Walter, 1974: 27; Dijkema, 1984a: 70; Hadac, 1989: 138-139; Bliss, 1993: 19).');
    'Salt meadow communities of brackish upper shores of Finnmark dominated by [Carex rariflora], often with [Carex salina], [Calamagrostis stricta].', '(Dijkema, 1984a: 70; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.2.6 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.2.6 [p.]).');
    'Saltmarsh communities of northern Norway, northern Russia and northern Iceland dominated by [Carex mackenziei] with [Agrostis stolonifera], accompanied by [Drepanocladus aduncus], [Drepanocladus uncinatus], characteristic of brackish basins of the upper shore.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 89; Chater, 1980: 302; Dijkema, 1984a: 70; Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.4.4 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.4.1a [p.]).');
    'Low swards of middle and upper shores of northern Iceland, northern Norway and the Kola peninsula dominated by [Carex salina], developed, in relatively exposed situations, on substrates of coarse material.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 88; Chater, 1980: 320; Dijkema, 1984a: 70; Nordiska Ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.3.4b; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.2.2.4b; Mossberg y al., 1995: 639).');
    'Communities of the arctic coasts of Eurasia developed in brackish water on sulphurous gleys, in particular, [Hippuris tetraphylla] beds of brackish shores of Finnmark and northern Iceland.', '(Géhu and Rivas-Martinez, 1984: 37; Mossberg y al., 1995: 309).');
    'Frutescent and herbaceous halophilous communities of inland saltmarshes and temporary waterbodies of the Saharo-Sindian zone, and of coastal saltmarshes and lagoon fringes of the desert coasts of the African Atlantic, of the extreme southeastern Mediterranean, of the Red Sea, of the Arabian Sea and of the Persian Gulf.', '(Adam, 1968a: 50; Zohary, 1973; Knapp, 1973; Chapman, 1977a; Zahran, 1977; Chapman, 1977b; White, 1983: 222-223; Zahran and Willis, 1992).');
    'Frutescent and herbaceous halophilous communities of coastal saltmarshes, lagoon fringes and inundatable depressions of the Sinai coasts of the extreme southeastern Mediterranean and of the adjacent northern Sinai plain.', '(Zohary, 1973: 460).');
    'Frutescent halophilous communities of coastal saltmarshes, lagoon fringes and inundatable depressions of the northern Sinai dominated by [Halocnemum strobilaceum], usually occupying the wettest ground.', '(Zohary, 1973: 386, 460).');
    'Frutescent halophilous communities of coastal saltmarshes, lagoon fringes and inundatable depressions of the northern Sinai dominated by [Arthrocnemum glaucum], usually forming a girdle on the drier side of [Halocnemum] formations.', '(Zohary, 1973: 460).');
    'Frutescent halophilous communities of coastal saltmarshes, lagoon fringes and inundatable depressions of the northern Sinai dominated by [Nitraria retusa], associated with [Suaeda vermiculata], [Suaeda vera], [Limoniastrum monopetalum], [Frankenia hirsuta], [Halogeton alopecuroides], [Limonium pruinosum], usually forming on higher ground adjacent to [Halocnemum] and [Arthrocnemum] communities.', '(Zohary, 1973: 460).');
    'Frutescent halophilous communities of coastal saltmarshes, lagoon fringes and inundatable depressions of the northern Sinai dominated by [Zygophyllum album], usually forming on the lower parts of dune scarps.', '(Zohary, 1973: 460).');
    'Tall rush communities of coastal saltmarshes, lagoon fringes and inundatable depressions of the northern Sinai dominated by [Juncus rigidus] ([Juncus maritimus] var. [arabicus]), often occupying the central, wettest parts of less salty depressions, surrounded by [Halocnemum] and [Arthrocnemum] belts.', '(Zohary, 1973: 460).');
    'Frutescent and herbaceous halophilous communities of coastal saltmarshes and lagoon fringes of the desert coasts of the African Atlantic.', '(Adam, 1968a: 50; Knapp, 1973; Chapman, 1977a; Chapman, 1977b; White, 1983: 222-223).');
    'Frutescent and herbaceous halophilous communities of coastal saltmarshes and lagoon fringes of the Red Sea, of the Arabian Sea and of the Persian Gulf.', '(Adam, 1968a: 50; Zohary, 1973; Chapman, 1977a; Zahran, 1977; White, 1983: 222-223; Zahran and Willis, 1992: 278).');
    'Frutescent and herbaceous halophilous communities of inland saltmarshes and temporary waterbodies of the Sahara.', '(Knapp, 1973; White, 1983: 222-223; Zahran and Willis, 1992).');
    'Frutescent and herbaceous halophilous communities of inland saltmarshes and temporary waterbodies of the Arabian Desert.', '(Zohary, 1973).');
    'Formations of [Paspalum vaginatum], [Sesuvium portulacastrum], [Sporobolus virginicus], [Philoxerus vermicularis] of intertidal or inundatable areas of tropical coasts of the Palaearctic region.', '(Schnell, 1971b: 841-842).');
