    'Very open formations of annuals or, particularly in Mediterranean, and mostly East Mediterranean, representatives, of annuals and perennials, occupying accumulations of drift material and gravels rich in nitrogenous organic matter; characteristic are [Cakile maritima], [Salsola kali], [Atriplex spp.] (particularly [Atriplex glabriuscula]), [Polygonum spp.], [Euphorbia peplis], [Mertensia maritima], and, particularly in Mediterranean formations, [Glaucium flavum], [Matthiola sinuata], [Matthiola tricuspidata], [Euphorbia paralias], [Eryngium maritimum].', '(Zohary, 1973; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Géhu, 1984a, 1985; Costa, 1987; Korotkov y al., 1991; Påhlsson, 1994; Paradis and Piazza, 1995).');
    'Beach and upper beach formations, mostly of annuals of the low Arctic and high Arctic oceanic zones of the Palaearctic Atlantic, Pacific and Arctic oceans, occupying accumulations of drift material and gravels rich in nitrogenous organic matter; characteristic are [Cakile edentula], [Polygonum norvegicum] ([Polygonum oxyspermum] ssp. [raii]), [Atriplex longipes] [s.l.], [Atriplex glabriuscula], [Mertensia maritima]. ', '(Hadac, 1970: 136-137; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: 4.1.1.5 [p.]; Géhu, 1985: 39, 49; Påhlsson, 1994: 4.2.1.4 [p.]).');
    'Formations, predominantly of annuals, occupying accumulations of drift material and gravels rich in nitrogenous organic matter on nemoral and boreonemoral beaches of the Atlantic, the North Sea and the Baltic; characteristic are [Cakile maritima] ssp. [maritima], [Cakile maritima] ssp. [baltica], [Salsola kali], [Atriplex spp.] (particularly [Atriplex glabriuscula]), [Polygonum spp.], [Euphorbia peplis], [Mertensia maritima], [Glaucium flavum]. ', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: 4.1.1.5 [p.]; Géhu, 1985: 39, 50; Korotkov y al., 1991: 38; Påhlsson, 1994: 4.2.1.4 [p.]).');
    'Very open, low formations of annuals and perennials of Mediterranean, thermo-Atlantic and Black Sea gravel and shingle beaches, occupying accumulations of drift material, sandy gravels and gravels rich in nitrogenous organic matter; characteristic are [Cakile maritima] ssp. [aegyptiaca], [Cakile maritima] ssp. [euxina], [Enarthrocarpus arcuatus], [Matthiola sinuata], [Matthiola tricuspidata], [Salsola kali], [Atriplex spp.], [Polygonum spp.], [Euphorbia peplis], [Euphorbia paralias], [Glaucium flavum], [Eryngium maritimum].', '(Zohary, 1973: 447; Géhu y al., 1984b: 407-408; Géhu, 1985: 39, 56-59; Costa, 1987: 291; Korotkov y al., 1991: 39; Lovric, 1993a: 410; Paradis and Piazza, 1995: 58-61, 66-71, 76, 77).');
    'Formations of perennials or annuals occupying accumulations of drift material and gravels rich in nitrogenous organic matter on shingle beaches of the Pacific Basin, including those of southern Amurland, the Kuriles, Sakhaline.', '(Miyawaki and Suzuki, 1993: 169).');
