    'Sea-cliffs, their faces, ledges and associated caves, rocky shores and isolated seaside rocks of the tropical zone of the Atlantic, including the Cape Verde Islands and the southern coast of Mauritania, along which extends the major upwelling zone of the Canary Current. Tropical seabirds such as [Phaethon aethereus], [Sula leucogaster], [Phalacrocorax carbo lucidus] are characteristic. [Calonectris edwardsii] is endemic.', '(Bannerman, 1963; Watson, 1966; Löfgren, 1984).');
    'Sea-cliffs and rocky shores of the tropical Indian Ocean and its connected seas, comprising, in the Palaearctic region as here defined, those of the Red Sea, of the Arabian peninsula coast of the Gulf of Aden, of Socotra, of the Arabian Sea, of the Gulf of Oman and of the Persian Gulf. A major area of upwellings developed along the southern coast of the Arabian peninsula and Socotra inhances their importance as breeding sites for sea-birds. [Bulweria fallax], [Puffinus persicus], [Phalacrocorax socotranus], [Larus leucophthalmus], [Larus hemprichii] are endemic or near-endemic species of the region which do or may use sea-cliffs or rocky shores as breeding sites.', '(Löfgren, 1984).');
    'Sea-cliffs and rocky shores of the Chukchi Sea, the Bering Strait, the Bering Sea, the Commander Islands, Kamchatka, the northern and central Kuriles, the Sea of Okhotsk and the Tatar Straits, harbouring an exceptionally rich community of alcids, gulls and cormorants, in particular.', '(Löfgren, 1984).');
    'Sea-cliffs and rocky shores of the southern Kuriles, Honshu, Hokkaido, Shikoku and continental Korea.', '(Löfgren, 1984).');
    'Sea-cliffs and rocky shores of peninsular Korea, the Yellow Sea, the East China Sea, Kyushu, the Ryukyu Islands.', '(Löfgren, 1984).');
    'Sea-cliffs and rocky shores of the South China Sea.', '(Löfgren, 1984).');
    'Palaearctic sea-cliffs, or parts of sea-cliffs, and rocky shores colonized by disjunct assemblages of aerohaline chasmophytes or by more or less closed aerohaline grasslands with associated terrestrial invertebrate and vertebrate faunal communities. ', '(Vanden Berghen, 1964; Delvosalle, 1964; Horvat y al., 1974; Duvigneaud, 1977; Bramwell and Bramwell, 1983; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984a; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984b; Géhu y al., 1984c; Beeftink, 1984; Polunin and Walters, 1985; Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Hohenester and Welss, 1993; Santos Guerra, 1993).');
    'Vegetated cliffs of the northern Atlantic, the English Channel, the Irish Sea, the North Sea, the Baltic Sea, the Arctic Ocean and its seas, the northwest Pacific and its seas.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1964; Géhu, 1984a; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984b; Géhu y al., 1984c; Beeftink, 1984: 21; Polunin and Walters, 1985).');
    'Vegetated cliffs of the nemoral middle Atlantic, the English Channel, the Irish Sea and the North Sea, along the coasts of Iberia, France, Ireland, England, Wales, southern Scotland and Helgoland, colonized by relatively thermophile communities variously formed by [Crithmum maritimum], [Armeria maritima], [Armeria pubigera], [Limonium occidentale], [Limonium ovalifolium], [Brassica oleracea] ssp. [oleracea], [Silene vulgaris] ssp. [maritima], [Plantago maritima], [Festuca rubra] ssp. [pruinosa], [Daucus carota] ssp. [gummifer], [Daucus carota] ssp. [gadecaei], [Matricaria maritima], [Asplenium marinum], [Spergularia rupicola], [Inula crithmoides], [Sedum anglicum], [Lavatera arborea], [Frankenia laevis], [Anthyllis vulneraria] ssp. [corbierei], [Anthyllis vulneraria] ssp. [iberica], [Dactylis glomerata] ssp. [marina].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1964; Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1973; Ratcliffe, 1977b: 32-35; Laubier, 1983: 116; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984a, 1984b; Géhu y al., 1984c; Beeftink, 1984: 21; Polunin and Walters, 1985; Oberdorfer, 1990; Pott, 1992: 217; Julve, 1993: 43-44).');
    'Vegetated cliffs of the northern Atlantic, the northern North Sea, the Baltic, the Arctic Ocean and its seas, the Bering Sea, the Sea of Okhotsk, the northern and western Sea of Japan colonized by relatively cryophile communities. ', '(Ratcliffe, 1977b: 32-35; Laubier, 1983: 116; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984a, 1984b; Beeftink, 1984: 21; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Julve, 1993: 43; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Usually open, lacunar, relatively cryophile, moderately nitrophile aerohaline communities of sea-cliffs of the northern Atlantic and northern North Sea coasts of Scotland, the Faeroe Islands, Iceland and Scandinavia, mostly dominated by [Cochlearia officinalis], [Silene vulgaris] ssp. [maritima] ([Silene uniflora]), [Matricaria maritima], [Festuca rubra] ssp. [pruinosa], with [Armeria maritima], [Plantago maritima], [Cochlearia groenlandica], [Cochlearia fenestrata], [Agrostis stolonifera], [Poa pratensis], [Ligusticum scoticum], [Cerastium fortanum], [Rhodiola rosea], [Plantago maritima], [Sedum acre], [Asplenium marinum].', '(Ratcliffe, 1977b: 32-35; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984b; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 4.1.6.1 [p.], 1.1.2.1b; Polunin and Walters, 1985; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.1.1.1 [p.]).');
    'Uncommon, species-poor, often [Cochlearia officinalis]-dominated, communities occupying wet, shadowy recesses near the foot of cold, shaded cliffs in southwestern Britain and Brittany constitute extralimital, highly specialized representatives of unit 18.2121.', '(Ratcliffe, 1977b: 32-35; Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984b; Julve, 1993: 43).');
    'Species-rich, nitrophile, meadowlike or tall-herb communities colonizing seabird nesting cliffs of the northern Atlantic and the northern North Sea.', '(Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984b; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 4.1.6.2, 1.3.6.3; Påhlsson, 1994: units 4.1.1.4, 4.1.1.3).');
    'Species rich, nitrophile, often meadowlike communities of broad rock ledges and clifftops of the west coast of Norway, Iceland, the Faeroe Islands, characteristic of sites with seabird colonies; dominant species include [Cochlearia officinalis], [Festuca rubra] ssp. [pruinosa], [Matricaria maritima], [Rumex acetosa], with [Armeria maritima], [Silene vulgaris] ssp. [maritima] ([Silene uniflora]), [Silene dioica], [Saxifraga rivularis], [Saxifraga cespitosa], [Plantago maritima], [Oxyura digyna], [Anthriscus sylvestris], [Ligusticum scoticum], [Ranunculus acris], [Cerastium arcticum], [Cerastium fortanum], [Rhodiola rosea], [Plantago maritima], [Hieracium spp.], [Taraxicum spp.], [Agrostis stolonifera], [Puccinellia distans] ssp. [borealis], ([Puccinellia coarctata]), [Leymus arenarius], [Poa pratense] [s.l.], [Poa alpina], [Poa glauca], [Poa annua].', '(Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984b; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.6.2; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.1.1.4; Magnusson and Magnusson, 2000; Fridriksson, 2000).');
    'Luxuriant, nitrophile tall-herb communities of rock fissures and ledges of sea-cliffs occupied by seabirds, of Norway, southwest Sweden and the Faeroe Islands, dominated by [Angelica archangelica], [Anthriscus sylvestris], [Rumex acetosa], [Silene dioica], [Rhodiola rosea], [Achillea milletolium], with [Silene vulgaris] ssp. [maritima] ([Silene uniflora]), [Valeriana sambucifolia], [Viola tricolor], [Oxyria digyna], [Cochlearia officinalis], [Ligusticum scoticum], [Matricaria perfoliata], [Festuca rubra].', '(Géhu and Géhu-Franck, 1984b; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.6.3; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.1.1.3).');
    'Vegetated cliffs of the Baltic Sea, with [Silene vulgaris] ssp. [maritima] ([Silene uniflora]), [Ligusticum scoticum], [Armeria maritima], [Odontites litoralis] ssp. [litoralis], [Odontites litoralis] ssp. [fennica], [Matricaria maritima], [Senecio viscosus].', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 4.1.6.1 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 4.1.1.1 [p.]; Mossberg y al., 1995).');
