    'Dense low (to 1 m) thickets of the low and middle alpine levels of the southern, central and northern mountains of Scandinavia dominated by [Salix glauca], accompanied by [Salix lapponum], [Salix lanata], [Salix phylicifolia], with a heath and grass layer formed by [Vaccinium myrtillus], [Vaccinium vitis-idaea], [Betula nana], [Empetrum hermaphroditum], [Hieracium alpinum], [Rumex acetosa], [Pyrola minor], [Trientalis europaea], [Cerastium alpinum], [Carex bigelowii], [Festuca ovina], with mosses and with lichens of genera [Cetraria] and [Cladonia]. These formations often occur as a wreath around windswept heaths, in more sheltered locations than those occupied by [Empetrum] heaths, mainly on north-facing slopes on stony, gravelly nutrient-poor sediments with some fine soil and high moisture, in conditions of some snow protection with early thaw.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.7.3 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.7.3 [p.]).');
