    'Willow thickets of Iceland, of low or medium stature, formed by [Salix callicarpaea] ([Salix arctica]), [Salix lanata], [Salix phylicifolia], [Betula pubescens] ssp. [czerepanovii], with a tall herb, usually luxuriant, field layer. They are developed in the lowlands and in a few highland oases, colonizing in particular, small islands, islets, lake shores, river banks, streamsides, gullies, mostly in sheltered situations. The species cortŠge includes [Geranium sylvaticum], [Erysimum hieracifolium], [Angelica archangelica], [Alchemilla vulgaris], [Coeloglossum viride], [Deschampsia cespitosa], [Deschampsia flexuosa], and, in the highlands, sometimes, [Leymus arenarius].', '(Steindorsson, 1967: 53-58, 90; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.7.1 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.7.1 [p.]).');
    'Dense thickets of the lowlands of Iceland dominated by [Salix lanata], [Salix phylicifolia] and [Salix callicarpaea] ([Salix arctica]) developed on frequently inundatable sediments, primarily along lake shores and rivers, mainly in drier areas of the north central and northeastern regions, with a humid meadow species cortŠge in the herb layer, usually dominated by [Deschampsia cespitosa] or [Filipendula ulmaria], often confined to openings within the thicket.', '(Steindorsson, 1967: 53-58, 90; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.7.2 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.7.2 [p.]).');
