    'Willow-dominated dwarf heaths of the highlands of Iceland, often fairly open,  with an upper layer that may not exceed 5 cm in height, and is usually less than 50 cm. A number of distinctive communities develop on sandy, gravelly or loess substrates. [Salix callicarpaea] ([Salix arctica]) or [Salix lanata] can be the dominant shrub in the upper layer, the latter, in particular, on more sandy substrates. Frequent dominants or codominants in the lower layer are dwarf [Empetrum hermaphroditum], [Kobresia myosuroides], [Carex bigelowii], [Dryas octopetala], [Salix herbacea] and, in particular, on sand deposits, [Festuca richardsonii] or [Armeria maritima]. Common associates may include dwarf [Vaccinium uliginosum], [Betula nana], [Arctostaphylos uva-ursi], [Loiseleuria procumbens], [Polygonum viviparum], [Pedicularis flammea] and, in humidity-retaining areas, [Parnassia palustris], [Tofieldia pusilla], [Pinguicula alpina], [Calamagrostis neglecta], [Equisetum variegatum].', '(Steindorsson, 1966: 57-58, 64-78, 93, tables XXIII, XXIV, XXV, XXVI, XXVII; Steindorsson,1967: 61-64, table XXXV; Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 92-93; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 1.3.7.3 [p.], 1.3.7.4 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.7.3 [p.]).');
    'Willow-dominated formations of windswept detritic summits, slopes and plateaux of the highlands of Iceland, constituted, in a desert-like landscape, essentially of bare stony gravelly substrates, by scattered prostrate [Salix callicarpaea] ([Salix arctica]), associated with [Salix herbacea] and a few mostly cushion herbs, in particular, [Silene acaulis], [Thymus praecox] ssp. [arctica], [Armeria maritima], [Galium normanii].', '(Steindorsson,1967: 70-77, 90, table XXXVII; Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 92; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.7.4 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: 614).');
