    'Mostly supra-Mediterranean hedgehog-heaths colonizing superficial, eroded soils and windswept stations of calcareous Baetic and sub-Baetic ranges, comprising many cushion plants and generally physiognomically dominated by the large hemispherical shrubs of [Echinospartum boissieri].  ', '(Tüxen and Oberdorfer, 1958; Delvosalle and Duvigneaud, 1962; Rivas Goday and Rivas-Martinez, 1968; Polunin and Smythies, 1973; Ozenda, 1975, 1985; Ozenda y al., 1979; Izco, 1979; Quézel, 1981b; Noirfalise, 1987; Peinado Lorca and Rivas-Martinez, 1987).');
