    'Mixed sclerophyllous evergreen and deciduous shrub thickets of the periphery of the range of Mediterranean sclerophyllous scrublands. They include, in particular, shrub formations of the Balkan and Italic peninsulas intermediate between Mediterranean maquis and schibljak, resulting from the degradation of the [Ostryo-Carpinion], with a mixture of evergreen and deciduous bushes including [Quercus coccifera], [Juniperus oxycedrus], [Quercus trojana], [Carpinus orientalis], [Ostrya carpinifolia], [Pistacia terebinthus], [Buxus sempervirens], [Berberis cretica], [Paliurus spina-christi], [Pyrus spinosa], [Rosa spp.], similar Iberian formations with [Amelanchier ovalis], [Prunus lusitanica], [Ilex aquifolium], French and Italian formations with [Quercus pubescens] and [Quercus ilex], formations of Mediterranean Asia Minor and the Levant dominated by mixed deciduous and evergreen shrubs or small trees, in particular, [Quercus coccifera] ([Quercus calliprinos]) and [Pistacia palaestina].', '(Adamovic, 1906; Zohary, 1973; Jakucs, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Tomaselli, 1981a; Polunin and Walters, 1985; Strid, 1989; Bondev, 1991).');
    'Shrub formations intermediate between Mediterranean maquis and schibljak, resulting from the degradation of the [Ostryo-Carpinion] of the Helleno-Balkanic peninsula, distributed in particular in northern Greece, in the Maritsa, Tundja, Mesta, Struma and Vardar valleys of Bulgaria and the F.Y.R. of Macedonia, in the Lake Ohrid basin of Albania, along the Black Sea coasts of Bulgaria, and in the eastern Adriatic hills of Albania, Yugoslavia and Croatia, with a mixture of evergreen and deciduous bushes including [Quercus coccifera], [Juniperus oxycedrus], [Juniperus excelsa], [Quercus trojana], [Carpinus orientalis], [Ostrya carpinifolia], [Pistacia terebinthus], [Pistacia atlantica], [Berberis cretica], [Paliurus spina-christi], [Pyrus spinosa], [Buxus sempervirens], [Phillyrea media], [Prunus spinosa], [Prunus lusitanica], [Laurus nobilis], [Ligustrum vulgare], [Jasminum fruticans], [Crataegus monogyna], [Crataegus pycnoloba], [Pyracantha coccinea], [Rosa sempervirens], [Rubus ulmifolius].', '(Adamovic, 1906; Jakucs, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974: 142, 164-169, 175; Tomaselli, 1981a; Polunin and Walters, 1985; Strid, 1989; Bondev, 1991: units 119, 122, 123, 127, 128; Hoda y al., 1998: 16).');
    'French and Italian mixed sclerophyllous evergreen and deciduous shrub formations dominated by [Quercus pubescens] and [Quercus ilex].', NULL);
    'Mixed sclerophyllous evergreen and deciduous shrub formations of Iberia, with [Amelanchier ovalis], [Prunus lusitanica], [Ilex aquifolium].', NULL);
    'Formations of Mediterranean Asia Minor and the Levant dominated by mixed deciduous and evergreen shrubs or small trees, in particular, [Quercus coccifera] ([Quercus calliprinos]) and [Pistacia palaestina].   ', NULL);
    'Xerophytic scrub formations of the lower slopes of the Canary Islands, Madeira, the Salvagen Islands, the Cape Verde Islands and the western North African mediterraneo-Saharan transition zone rich in succulents, in particular cactiform or dendroid spurges [Euphorbia spp.], rosette-forming [Aeonium spp.] and composites.  ', '(Delvosalle, 1964; Duvigneaud, 1977; White, 1983; Bramwell and Bramwell, 1983; Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987: 526-529; Machado, 1989; Hohenester and Welss, 1993: 19-20). ');
    'Lower alpine heaths of southern Norway, with low, prostrate, [Arctostaphylos uva-ursi], [Empetrum hermaphroditum], [Vaccinium uliginosum], accompanied by  [Antennaria dioica], [Anthoxanthum odoratum], [Euphrasia frigida], [Betula pubescens], [Vacinium vitis-idaea], [Deschampsia flexuosa], [Carex vaginata] with mosses and lichens. Occurs on dry, poor, sandy or gravelly soils containing richer elements, though not on pure limestone, with a thin humus layer, in localities with strong insolation and early thaw.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.1.2.2 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.1.2.2 [p.]).');
    'Often low heaths of lower alpine levels of Fennoscandia dominated by [Phyllodoce caerulea] and [Vaccinium myrtillus], with [Betula nana], [Betula pubescens], [Empetrum hermaphroditum], [Vaccinium uliginosum], [Vaccinium myrtillus], [Juniperus nana], [Alchemilla alpina], [Trientalis europaea] and many mosses and lichens, on moist soils with a humus layer, protected by snow for short periods.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.1.1 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.1.1 [p.]).');
    'Heaths of the boreal and arctic zones of Fennoscandia, mostly under maritime climate, dominated by [Cornus suecica] and [Vaccinium uliginosum] accompanied by [Solidago vigaurea] and [Trientalis europaea], with [Calluna vulgaris], [Carex bigelowii] often covering extensive areas in alternance with grass heaths, on relatively poor soils, normally snow protected. ', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.1.1a [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.1.1a) [p.].');
    'Lower alpine heaths of western Fennoscandia, dominated by [Gymnocarpium dryopteris] and [Vaccinium myrtillus], with [Salix herbacea], [Trientalis europea], [Deschampsia flexuosa], [Rumex acetosa], occurring over small surfaces within the dwarf cornel-northern bilberry heaths of unit 31.4547, in the shelter of stones.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.1.1b [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.1.1b [p.]).');
    'Lower alpine heaths of Fennoscandia, dominated by low scrub (0.5-1m) of [Betula nana], [Juniperus nana], [Vaccinium myrtillus], with very common [Vaccinium vitis-ideae], on dry to mesic ground with low pH, somewhat snow protected.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.1.1c [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.1.1c [p.]).');
    'Lowland and alpine boreal heaths of Iceland, Spitzbergen and Greenland formed by low, compact or mat-forming shrubs of Ericaceae, [Empetrum hermaphroditum], [Betula nana], [Juniperus nana] and [Salix spp.] and alpine flora elements. ', '(Steindorsson, 1966; Hadac, 1972, 1985a; Bliss, 1979; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Lowland and alpine boreal heaths of Iceland formed by low, compact or mat-forming shrubs of Ericaceae, [Empetrum hermaphroditum], [Betula nana], [Juniperus nana] and [Salix spp.] and alpine flora elements. ', '(Steindorsson, 1966; Vanden Berghen, 1969b; Hadac, 1972, 1985a; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Dwarf heaths of Iceland, often sparse, dominated by [Loiseleuria procumbens], usually associated with [Empetrum hermaphroditum] and [Vaccinium uliginosum]. The ground layer is well developed, with a cover of the order of 30% to 50%, often dominated by [Rhacomitrium canescens] or [Rhacomitrium lanuginosum], accompanied by a diverse cortŠge of lichens. The community is characteristic of the lower alpine zone of northern and eastern Iceland, usually developed on shallow soils, in wind-exposed situations with reduced snow cover.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 66; Hadac, 1985a: 134-135; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.2.1.1 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.1.1.1 [p.]).');
    'Dwarf heaths of Iceland dominated by [Betula nana], usually associated with [Salix phylicifolia], [Vaccinium uliginosum], [Empetrum hermaphroditum], with [Salix callicarpaea] ([Salix arctica]), [Salix lanata], [Salix herbacea], [Loiseleuria procumbens], [Deschampsia flexuosa], [Kobresia myosuroides], [Juncus trifidus]. The muscinal layer is moderately developed, with a cover of the order of 30%. These heaths are mostly developed in the lowland and lower alpine zones, in wind-exposed situations with low snow cover, often on loess deposits.', '(Steindorsson, 1966: 58-59; Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 65; Hadac, 1985a: 137-139; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.1.1.2 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.1.1.4 [p.]).');
    'Xerophilous dwarf heaths of Iceland dominated by [Empetrum hermaphroditum], variously associated with [Vaccinium uliginosum], [Arctostaphylos uva-ursi], [Calluna vulgaris], [Betula nana], [Salix callicarpaea] ([Salix arctica]), [Salix lanata], [Salix herbacea], [Polygonum viviparum], [Kobresia myosuroides], [Carex bigelowii], [Festuca vivipara], [Festuca richardsonii], [Poa alpina], [Equisetum variegatum], with an often richly developed lichen layer. They are developed in the lowlands and lower alpine levels on a variety of substrates, including lavas, with relatively shallow soils. Where they occur alongside [Empetrum]-[Vaccinium] heaths of unit 31.2113 they occupy more wind-exposed, more snowfree surfaces, and differ by the lower stature of the erico¿ds, the often more open structure of the shrub layer and the lesser prominence of [Vaccinium spp.].', '(Steindorsson, 1966: 53-58, 93, table XXIII; Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 65, 94; Hadac, 1972: 358-361; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.2.1.3; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.1.1.2).');
    'Cushion-forming communities of the high altitudes of the Sierra Tramuntana of Mallorca, rich in endemics, among them [Teucrium subspinosum], [Teucrium asiaticum], [Pastinaca lucida], [Thymelaea velutina] and [Paeonia cambessedesii].', '(Bolos and Molinier, 1958; Meusel, 1973: 215-218; Rivas-Martinez and Costa, 1987: 496, 507; Straka y al., 1987: 1).');
    'Cushion-forming communities of wind-exposed plateaux and hills of Menorca with [Cistus creticus] and [Teucrium subspinosum] var. [spinescens].', '(Rivas-Martinez and Costa, 1987: 499-500).');
    'Expanses of small, compact bushes with [Astragalus sirinicus] ssp. [genargenteus], [Rosa serafinii], [Anthyllis hermanniae], [Thymus herba-barona], [Cerastium boissieri], [Genista salzmannii], [Genista corsica], [Berberis aetnensis], [Prunus prostrata] and [Daphne oleoides], of Sardinian and Corsican mountains. ', '(Ozenda y al., 1979; Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Chiappini, 1985a; Camarda and Valsecchi, 1990; Gamisans, 1991).');
    'Oro-Mediterranean [Astragalus sirinicus] ssp. [genargenteus] hedgehog-heaths of the Gennargentu and Monte Albo in Sardinia and of the high mountains of Corsica.  ', '(Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Chiappini, 1985a; Camarda and Valsecchi, 1990; Gamisans, 1991).');
    'Formations of windswept crests of Corsica and Sardinia dominated by the low spiny cushions of [Euphorbia spinosa].  ', '(Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Chiappini, 1985a; Camarda and Valsecchi, 1990; Gamisans, 1991).');
    'Formations of the mountains of Corsica and Sardinia dominated by the hemispherical cushions of the endemic [Thymus herba-barona]. ', '(Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Chiappini, 1985a; Camarda and Valsecchi, 1990; Gamisans, 1991).');
    'Hedgehog-heaths of high mountains of Corsica and Sardinia and secondary heaths of the montane level dominated by [Genista salzmannii] (including [Genista salzmannii] var. [lobelioides]) or [Genista corsica].  ', '(Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Chiappini, 1985a; Camarda and Valsecchi, 1990; Gamisans, 1991).');
