    'More or less dense, spiny brushes limited to very restricted areas of the Almerian and Carthagenian coasts of the arid Iberian Southeast, dominated by the shrub of African affinities [Maytenus senegalensis] var. [europaeus] with [Rhamnus oleoides] ssp. [angustifolia] and [Rhamnus oleoides] ssp. [velutinus], [Asparagus albus], [Asparagus stipularis], [Asparagus horridus], [Chamaerops humilis] and occasionally [Buxus balearica].  ', '(Delvosalle and Duvigneaud, 1962; Rivas Goday and Rivas-Martinez, 1968; Freitag, 1971; Rivas-Martinez, 1974a; Ferre Bueno y al., 1985; Alcaraz Ariza and Peinado Lorca, 1987).');
