    'Very local, impoverished [Sarcopoterium spinosum] formations of Capo St. Elia (southern Sardinian coast), of the Gulf of Taranto (Puglia, Calabria) and of the Maltese Islands.', '(Caniglia y al., 1974; Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Géhu y al., 1984a; Géhu y al., 1984b: 421-423; Lanfranco, 1989: 18; Schembri, 1999b).');
    'Very local [Genista acanthoclada] ssp. [sardoa]-dominated communities of northwestern Sardinia.', '(Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Camarda and Valsecchi, 1990). ');
    'Formations of the coasts of Mallorca and Minorca dominated by the cushion-forming Balearic endemics [Launaea cervicornis], [Astragalus balearicus], [Centaurea balearica], [Anthyllis fulgurans], [Anthyllis hermanniae] ssp. [hystrix], [Teucrium subspinosum].  ', '(Molinier and Molinier, 1955; Bolos and Molinier, 1958; Bolos y al., 1970; Nimis, 1981; Quézel, 1981b; Asensi Marfil and Diez Garretas, 1993: 365).');
    'Thermo-Mediterranean formations of headlands and peninsulas of Corsica and Sardinia dominated by cushion-forming spiny [Genista corsica] or [Genista morisii]. These endemic species participate in the constitution of hedgehog-heaths (unit 31.75) as well as in that of the coastal formations listed here, which assume an evident phrygana appearance; they may also enter in the composition of midelevation formations of less distinctive appearance which can be listed under unit 32.482.', '(Molinier and Molinier, 1955; Nimis, 1981; Pignatti, 1982; Gamisans, 1985; Gamisans, 1991: 80; Géhu y al., 1984b; Chiappini, 1985a, 1985b; Camarda and Valsecchi, 1990).');
    'Coastal formation of hemispherical shrubs with the Pantelleria endemics [Helichrysum saxatile] ssp. [errerae] and [Matthiola pulchella], vicariant of the west Mediterranean, Balearic and Sardinian clifftop phryganas.  ', '(Brullo y al., 1977).');
    'Thorny cushion communities of the Thracian wooded steppe zone enclaved between the Black Sea, the Sea of Marmora and the Aegean, with [Sarcopoterium spinosum] and [Astragalus thracicus].', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 351).');
    '[Sarcopoterium spinosum]-dominated phryganas of the Thracian steppe zone of northeastern Greece and Turkey-in-Europe.', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 351).');
    '[Dryas octopetala] or [Dryas octopetala]-[Arctostaphylos uva-ursi] dwarf heaths of the Inner Hebrides, recorded from Skye, Raasay and Rhum, associated with Durness or Jurassic limestone outcroppings.', '(McVean, 1964f: 578; Ratcliffe, 1980; Rodwell, 1992: unit CG13 [p.]; Lusby and Wright, 2001: 39).');
    '[Dryas octopetala] or [Dryas]-[Arctostaphylos] dwarf heaths of western Ireland, characteristic of the Burren, where they cover extensive surfaces of bare or thinly peat-covered Carboniferous limestones.', '(Ratcliffe, 1980; Lousley, 1990: 201-207; Lusby and Wright, 2001: 14, 39-42).');
    '[Dryas octopetala] heaths of the boreoalpine and arctoalpine levels of northern Palaearctic mountains of Scotland and Fennoscandia.', '(Ratcliffe, 1980; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Noirfalise, 1987; Rodwell, 1992; Påhlsson, 1994; Lusby and Wright, 2001).');
    'High-altitude species-rich [Dryas] cliff-ledge communities of the mica-shist hills of the central Highlands of Scotland, with fragmentary outposts in Lakeland and Snowdonia.  ', '(Ratcliffe, 1980; Rodwell, 1992: unit CG14; Lusby and Wright, 2001: 39-42).');
    '[Dryas octopetala] heaths of the boreoalpine and arctoalpine levels of the mountains of Fennoscandia.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Noirfalise, 1987; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Dense, closed, low heaths of Fenoscandian mountains dominated by [Dryas octopetala], with [Diphasiastrum alpinum], [Carex brunnescens] and [Omalotheca supina] ([Gnaphalium supinum]), installed on dry calcareous gravels, sands and rock pavements. Accompanying species vary over the very broad range of this habitat and include [Arctostaphylos uva-ursi], [Arctostaphylos alpina], [Betula nana], [Juniperus nana], [Salix reticulata], [Vaccinium uliginosum], [Astragalus alpinus], [Campanula rotundifolia], [Cerastium alpinum], [Draba norvegica], [Silene acaulis], [Minuartia stricta], [Parnassia palustris], [Pedicularis flammula], [Pedicularis oederi], [Potentilla nivea], [Pyrola norvegica], [Viola rupestris] ssp. [relicta], [Polygonum viviparum] ([Bistorta vivipara]), [Leucorchis albida] ssp. [straminea] ([Leucorchis straminea]), [Oxytropis lapponica], [Carex atrata], [Carex capillaris], [Carex rupestris], [Kobresia myosuroides], [Thalictrum alpinum]. The [Dryas] sometimes is so dense that no other species are present. A ground layer is often absent; the humus layer is often around 5 cm.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.2.3.2; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.1.3.2).');
    'Very low, open heaths of boreal mountains dominated by [Dryas octopetala] and [Kobresia myosuroides] occupying weathered calcareous gravels or pavements on windswept exposures with a thin humus layer, negligible snow cover and early thaw. Codominating species include [Carex fuliginosa], [Carex nardina] and, locally, [Festuca ovina], acompanied by [Draba fladnizensis], [Draba nivalis], [Draba norvegica], [Saxifraga cespitosa], [Saxifraga nivalis], [Saxifraga opositifolia], [Arnica alpina], [Campanula uniflora], [Diapensia lapponica], [Euphrasia lapponica], [Gentianella tenella], [Minuartia rubella], [Potentilla nivea], [Poa glauca], and, locally, [Carex glacialis], rich in lichens.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.2.3.1; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.1.3.1).');
    'Sparse [Dryas octopetala] heaths of the low to midalpine level of Fennoscandian mountains, with an abundant, often continuous ground cover of mosses, particularly [Tomentypmum nitens] and [Sphagnum warnstorfii], developed on calcareous substrates that are permanently moist or subjected to periodical near-surface ground water flow. [Viola biflora], [Carex norvegica], [Minuartia biflora], [Thalictrum alpinum] have a preference for this habitat.   ', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.4.2; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.4.2).');
