    'Xero-thermophile shrub communities of Western Europe and western Central Europe, occupying the southern part of the west European range of unit 31.812, within the main range of the [Quercion pubescenti-petraeae], as well as a few highly xero-thermic central European sites. [Prunus mahaleb] and [Acer monspessulanum] are characteristic species.', '(Bournérias, 1979: 391-392; Rameau y al., 1989; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1992b: 86-87; Pott, 1992; Wirth, 1993; Julve, 1993; Schubert y al., 1995: 134-135).');
