    'Formations dominated by medium or tall perennnial tuft-forming grasses or suffrutescents, with lacunar ground cover, together with their associated therophyte communities developed on moving or fixed sands of the steppe and wooded steppe belts of extreme eastern Europe and western Siberia, extending from the Volga-Kama system in the west to the Tarbagatai and western Altai in the east, including the Transvolgan steppes of Orenburg and Bachkiria, the Kurgan, Ishim, Baraba, Kulunda, Barnaul, Kirgiz, Kazakh steppes, and the mountain steppes of the Tarbagatai and the Altai (unit 34.93). Most of these formations are associated with inland dune systems and define subdivisions of habitats listed under unit 64.74.', '(Walter, 1974; Walter and Breckle, 1986; Korotkov y al., 1991).');
