    'Steppic grasslands of the Bohemian basin and of the middle German Saale-Mulde basin and their fringing hills, dominated by [Stipa capillata] or [Stipa joannis], developed on relatively deep calcareous or loess substrates, usually two-layered, with [Festuca valesiaca], [Festuca rupicola], [Koeleria macrantha], [Melica transsilvanica], [Elymus hispidus] ([Agropyron intermedium]), [Carex humilis], [Carex supina], [Artemisia campestris], [Achillea pannonica], [Astragalus exscapus], [Eryngium campestre], [Verbascum phoeniceum], [Centaurea stoebe], [Erysimum crepidifolium], [Potentilla arenaria], [Euphorbia cyparissias], [Stachys recta], [Dianthus carthusianorum], [Sedum maximum], [Adonis vernalis], [Teucrium chamaedrys], [Teucrium montanum], [Hippocrepis comosa], [Bupleurum falcatum], [Anthericum liliago].', '(Kolbek, 1975; Ellenberg, 1988; Schubert and Vent, 1990; Pott, 1992). ');
