    'Grasslands of subarctic affinities of the northern boreal and middle boreal zones of northern Scandinavia and northwestern Russia, of the alpine and arcto-alpine zones of the Caledonian chains of Scandinavia and of lowlands and hills of Iceland, composed of [Festuca spp.], [Agrostis capillaris], with  [Anthoxanthum odoratum], other grass species, often with [Polygonum viviparum] and other herbs.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 5.2.2.2a, 5.2.2.2b, 5.2.2.4, 52.2.5; Påhlsson, 1994: units 5.2.2.2a, 5.2.2.2b, 5.2.2.5, 5.2.2.6, 5.2.1.3a).');
    'Relatively short grasslands of lower mountain slopes of northern Scandinavia and of lowlands and hills of Iceland dominated by [Agrostis capillaris] or [Anthoxanthum odoratum], with [Polygonum viviparum] ([Bistorta vivipara]) and [Carex bigelowii]. These grasslands are strongly influenced by, and perhaps entirely dependent on, grazing or mowing.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 65; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.2.2a; Hadac, 1985a: 143-145; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 5.2.2.2a).');
    'Relatively short grasslands of lower mountain slopes of northern Scandinavia dominated by [Agrostis capillaris], [Polygonum viviparum] ([Bistorta vivipara]), [Carex bigelowii], occupying quite stony though well-developed soils, with a sufficient moisture supplied by prolonged snow cover.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.2.2a; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 5.2.2.2a).');
