    '[Nardus stricta]-dominated grasslands and related communities of the supra-mediterranean level of the mountains of the Mediterranean peninsulas, either developed on siliceous soils, or, rarely, on calcareous substrates.  ', '(Bonin, 1972; Horvat y al., 1974; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987).');
