    'Distinctive snow patch communities, endemic to the Eastern Carpathians, in particular, to the Rodnei Mountains, formed by the Carpathian endemics [Salix kitaibeliana] and [Soldanella hungarica] ssp. [hungarica], with [Luzula alpinopilosa], [Polygonum viviparum], [Oreochloa disticha], [Doronicum clusii], and, more sporadically, the Eastern Carpathian endemics [Poa deylii] and [Lychnis nivalis].', '(Coldea, 1991: 376-379).');
    'Espalier willow communities of calcareous stonefields in mountains in heavy-rainfall areas of boreal and arctic Scandinavia dominated by [Salix reticulata], often exclusively, and [Poa alpina], with a sparser participation of, among others, [Salix polaris], [Antennaria alpina], [Pinguicula alpina], [Silene acaulis], [Tofieldia pusilla], [Viola biflora], [Thalictrum alpinum], [Festuca vivipara], [Equisetum variegatum], [Selaginella selaginoides].', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.3.2.2; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.2.2.2).');
    'Calciphile or calcicline snowfield, snowbed and snow-patch communities of boreal and arcto-alpine mountains formed by small herbs, grasses or dwarf, underground-stemmed willows.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Chionophilous communities of boreal and arcto-alpine Palaearctic mountains and of islands of the polar basin dominated by, or rich in, [Salix polaris], associated with mosses and small forbs, developed, at least in the boreal and arcto-alpine regions, on calcareous substrates.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.4.2.1; Hadac, 1989: 150-158; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 1.3.2.1).');
    'Hygrophile tall herb strips of fertile alluvial stream banks of Western Europe and western Central Europe, with irradiations in sub-Mediterranean regions and in the hills of the Pannonic plain, mostly dominated by [Filipendula ulmaria].', '(Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1973; Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Mériaux, 1976; De Sloover and Lebrun, 1976; Noirfalise y al., 1980; Soo, 1980; Gorissen y al., 1983; Moravec y al., 1983; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 5.2.3.2 [p.], 5.2.3.2a [p.]; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987; Oberdorfer, 1990; Pott, 1992: 238-239; Rodwell, 1992: units M27, M28; Julve, 1993: 99; Ellmauer and Mucina, 1993: 324-329, 330; Påhlsson, 1994: units 5.2.3.2 [p.], 5.2.3.2a [p.]; Schubert y al., 1995).');
    'Hygrophile tall herb strips of fertile alluvial stream banks of Atlantic and sub-Atlantic Western Europe, western and northern Central Europe, with irradiations in sub-Mediterranean regions and in the hills of the Pannonic plain, mostly dominated by [Filipendula ulmaria], with [Achillea ptarmica], [Angelica sylvestris], [Cirsium palustre], [Deschampsia cespitosa], [Epilobium hirsutum], [Geranium palustre], [Eupatorium cannabinum], [Lysimachia vulgaris], [Lythrum salicaria], [Phalaris arundinacea], [Polygonum bistorta], [Valeriana officinalis], [Rumex acetosa], [Urtica dioica], [Vicia cracca].', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: units 126, 127; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1973; Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Mériaux, 1976; De Sloover and Lebrun, 1976; Noirfalise y al., 1980; Soo, 1980; Wheeler, 1980c; De Sloover y al., 1980: 59-62; Gorissen y al., 1983; Moravec y al., 1983; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 85; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: units 5.2.3.2 [p.], 5.2.3.2a [p.]; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b: 138-139, 216, 232; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987; Oberdorfer, 1990; Korotkov y al., 1991: 149; Trautmann, 1991: 44, Table 11c, d; Pott, 1992: 238-239; Rodwell, 1992: unit M27; Julve, 1993: 99; Ellmauer and Mucina, 1993: 324-329, 330; Robbe, 1993: 45; Påhlsson, 1994: units 5.2.3.2 [p.], 5.2.3.2a [p.]; Schubert y al., 1995: 297-298; Frankard y al., 1998: 36-37; Seliskar, 1998: 16).');
    'Hygrophile [Filipendula ulmaria]-dominated tall herb strips, often luxurient and species-rich, of the regions of Europe submitted to the most extreme Atlantic influence, enriched in [Iris pseudacorus] and, except in the far north, [Oenanthe crocata], known, in particular, from the western seaboard of Scotland, the Hebrides and the Orkneys.', '(Rodwell, 1992: unit M28).');
    'Hygrophile tall herb strips of fertile alluvial stream banks of eastern Central Europe and Eastern Europe, richer in species, in particular of continental affinities, than their western counterparts of unit 37.111; [Filipendula ulmaria], notably [Filipendula ulmaria] ssp. [picbaueri], is accompanied by [Veronica longifolia], [Scutellaria hastifolia], [Euphorbia lucida], [Stachys palustris], [Thalictrum flavum]. They are associated with grasslands of the [Cnidion], as the formations of unit 37.111 are with those of the [Calthion] or the [Molinion].', '(Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Moravec y al., 1983; Balatova-Tulackova and Venanzoni, 1989; Oberdorfer, 1990; Schubert and Vent, 1990; Korotkov y al., 1991: 149-150; Pott, 1992: 239; Julve, 1993: 99; Ellmauer and Mucina, 1993: 338-339).');
    'Tall herb stands ([Filipendula ulmaria], [Angelica sylvestris]) colonizing humid hay meadows and pastures after more or less long discontinuation of mowing or grazing. ', '(Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; De Sloover and Lebrun, 1976; Noirfalise y al., 1980; De Sloover y al., 1980: 59-62; Oberdorfer, 1990).');
    'Stands of [Equisetum telmateia], often forming tall, dense, extensive colonies, pure or associated with humid tall herb community components such as [Filipendula ulmaria], [Heracleum sphondylium], [Galium palustre], [Achillea ptarmica], [Angelica sylvestris], [Cirsium palustre], [Deschampsia cespitosa], [Epilobium hirsutum], [Geranium palustre], [Eupatorium cannabinum], [Caltha palustris], [Lysimachia vulgaris], [Lythrum salicaria], [Phalaris arundinacea], [Polygonum bistorta], [Polygonum hydropiper], [Pulicaria dysenterica], [Valeriana officinalis], [Juncus inflexus], [Carex remota], [Carex riparia], of damp clay substrates, often on slopes and canal or railway banks, or along hedgerows.', '(Page, 1988: 113-115; Julve, 1993: 99).');
    'River bank and humid depression tall herb communities of the lowlands of the boreal zone dominated by [Filipendula ulmaria], with, among others, [Achillea ptarmica], [Dactylorhiza fuschii], [Galium uliginosum], [Geum rivale], [Lysimachia vulgaris], [Trollius europeaus], [Valeriana sambucifolia].', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.3.2 [p.]; Ellenberg, 1988: 582; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 5.2.3.2 [p.]).');
