    'River-bank and humid depression tall herb communities of the Far Eastern deciduous forest region and its zones of influence.', '(Walter and Breckle, 1991c: 328-329; Korotkov y al., 1991).');
    'Meadows developed on moderately to very nutrient-rich, alluvial or fertilized, wet or damp soils, often inundated at least in winter, and relatively lightly mowed or grazed, in deciduous forest and steppe zones of Eurasia. They form a transition between the mesophile meadows, the oligotrophic humid grasslands and the small sedge and large sedge communities. They include a large number of distinctive and often species-rich communities, many of which harbour specialized, rare and threatened species of plants and animals. ', '(Zeidler, 1954; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Horvat y al., 1974; Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Bournérias, 1979, 1984; Noirfalise y al., 1980, 1985; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1980; Balatova-Tulackova, 1983; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Oberdorfer, 1990; Korotkov y al., 1991; Coldea, 1991; Rodwell, 1991b, 1992; Ellmauer and Mucina, 1993; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Mesophile calcareous grasslands of the Swabian Alb and adjacent areas. ', '(Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Wolkinger and Plank, 1981; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1993a).');
    'Closed mesophile calcareous grasslands of the Franconian Alb, Franconian plateaux and adjacent areas. ', '(Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Wolkinger and Plank, 1981; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1993a).');
    'Hill and montane mesophile grasslands of the northwestern calcareous pre-Alps. ', '(Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Braun-Blanquet, 1976; Wolkinger and Plank, 1981; Ozenda, 1981; Chas, 1989; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1993a).');
    'Hill and montane mesophile calcareous grasslands of the Isar valley, the Bavarian plateau, the Bavarian pre-Alps, the Austrian northern, eastern and southeastern pre-Alps. ', '(Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Braun-Blanquet, 1976; Wolkinger and Plank, 1981; Ozenda, 1981; Zimmermann y al., 1989; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1993a; Mucina and Kolbek, 1993a: 424-433, 434-436).');
