    'Steppes of the plain of the western Black Sea, west of the Dniester, of its associated basins, including those of the lower Danube, of Transylvania and of northern Thrace, of the southern edge and valleys of the Podolian, Central Russian and Volga plateaux, with [Stipa capillata], [Kochia prostrata], [Koeleria lobata] ([Koeleria degenii]), [Stipa lessingiana], [Festuca valesiaca], [Dichanthium ischaemum] ([Bothriochloa ischaemum]), [Medicago minima].', '(Saphronova, 1964a; Saphronova, 1964b; Saphronova, 1964c; Walter, 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Bondev, 1991; Korotkov y al., 1991; Ozenda, 1994: 145-151).');
    'Steppes of the plain of the western Black Sea, west of the Dniester, of the basin of the lower Danube and of the northern Thracian basin of the middle Maritsa and the Tundzha, with [Pimpinella tragium], [Thymus zygioides], [Stipa lessingiana], [Stipa capillata], [Agropyron pectiniforme].', '(Saphronova, 1964a: units 49-50; Saphronova, 1964c: units 70-71; Dihoru and Donita, 1970; Walter, 1974: 163, unit 1).');
    'Very open steppes of the western Pontic region, with chamaephytes, on leached shallow soils, with [Pimpinella lithophila], [Thymus zygioides], [Stipa lessingiana], [Koeleria lobata], [Potentilla bornmuelleri], [Satureja coerulea], [Ornithogalum amphibolum].', '(Dihoru and Donita, 1970; Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Very open, semidesert-like steppes of the western Pontic region and the Transylvanian basin, developed on soils with fluctuating moisture, dominated or codominated by [Artemisia spp.]', '(Soo, 1959; Walter, 1974; Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Steppes of the western Pontic region and the Transylvanian basin developed on deeper chernozem soils.', '(Walter, 1974; Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Steppes of the southern edge and valleys of the Podolian, Central Russian and Volga plateaux, forming a wooded steppe belt north of the Pontic plains, extending west to the upper Prut basin of Romanian Moldavia and east to the Volga-Kama trough, composed of [Stipa lessingiana], [Stipa joannis], [Stipa pulcherrima], [Stipa ucrainica], [Koeleria macrantha], [Agropyron cristatum], [Festuca valesiaca], [Astragalus onobrychis]. 

', '(Ravarut y al., 1956; Saphronova, 1964a: unit 48; Saphronova, 1964c: unit 69; Walter, 1974: 163, units 2a, 2b; Tolmatchev, 1980: unit 21 [p.]).');
    'Steppes of the northern Black Sea-Sea of Azov plain, of the basins of the Dnieper and the Don, extending west to the Dniestr, northeast to the Volga, east to the Caspian deserts and semideserts, southeast to the pre-Caucasian hills in the basins of the Kouban, the Manytch, the upper Kuma and upper Terek.  ', '(Saphronova, 1964a: units 49-50; Saphronova, 1964c: units 70-71; Walter, 1974: 163, units 3a, 3b).');
