    'Grasslands rich in, or dominated by, [Nardus stricta], with [Festuca nigricans], [Festuca airoides], [Poa media] and regional species [Viola declinata], [Scorzonera rosea], [Potentilla aurea] ssp. [chrysocraspeda] ([Potentilla ternata]), [Campanula abietina], [Campanula serrata], of flats and gentle slopes of the subalpine and lower alpine levels of the Eastern and Southern Carpathians.
', '(Coldea, 1987, 1991: 385-389).');
    'Acidophilous grasslands dominated by [Nardus stricta] of higher, mostly subalpine, sometimes alpine, elevations of the Balkan Range, the Rhodopides, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains and the Pelagonides.', '(Simon, 1958; Penev, 1964; Horvat y al., 1974: 527-528, 626; Bondev, 1991: units 6, 8, 26 [p.]; Hoda y al., 1998: 12).');
