    '[Quercus petraea]-[Carpinus betulus] forests of plains and low hills of the Bohemian basin and adjacent areas of northeastern Lower Austria.', '(Moravec y al., 1982: 104-118, 135-152; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 128-131; Chytry and Vicherek, 1995; Kolbek y al., 1997; Neuh¿uslova, 1998: 85-92, 101-102).');
    'Oak-hornbeam forests widespread in the Bohemian basin and neighbouring regions, particularly in the plains and low hills of the Bohemian Elbe-Vltava system, in the southwestern Moravian hills and valleys of the Dyje system and of the Thaya valley, and in northeastern Lower Austria (Kamp valley, Thaya valley, eastern edges of Waldviertel), with northern outposts in the Bohemian foothills of the Krusne Hory (Metallic Mountains) and in the Smida basin, in the western approaches to the Jizerske (western Sudeten). The tree layer is dominated by [Quercus petraea] and [Carpinus betulus] variously associated with [Tilia cordata], [Quercus robur], [Fagus sylvatica], sometimes [Fraxinus excelsior], [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Acer campestre], [Abies alba]. The shrub layer is species-rich, mostly formed by young individuals of the tree-layer species, with [Acer campestre], [Crataegus oxyacantha]. The herb layer has a somewhat continental and thermophile species cortŠge in which [Anemone nemorosa], [Poa nemoralis], [Stellaria holostea], [Galium sylvaticum], [Convallaria majalis] may form facies. [Melampyrum nemorosum], although not usually dominant, reaches its highest frequency within forest habitats in this community.', '(Moravec y al., 1982: 104-118, unit 1; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 133-135; Chytry and Vicherek, 1995: 40-46; Kolbek y al., 1997: 57-65; Neuh¿uslova, 1998: 85-89, unit 7).');
    'Local and threatened oak-lime forests of the central Bohemian basin, limited to the Elbe and lower Vltava basins where it occupies terrace sands, sandy aeolian deposits and decalcified loess loams under warm, dry subcontinental climate conditions. [Quercus petraea], or sometimes [Quercus robur], associated with [Tilia cordata], dominate the tree layer. [Carpinus betulus] is rare. The species cortŠge, of which [Poa angustifolia], [Carex palescens], [Holcus mollis], [Deschampsia flexuosa], [Hypericum montanum], [Carex pilulifera], [Carex umbrosa] are characteristic, contains numerous acidophilous species.', '(Moravec y al., 1982: 143-148, unit 5; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 131; Neuh¿uslova, 1998: 90-92, 284, unit 8).');
    'Local and threatened oak-lime forests of the southern Bohemian basin, limited to the middle Otava valley and the foothills of the Sumava, developed on relatively rich soils of plains or moderate to steep slopes at the collinar level. The tree layer is dominated by [Quercus robur] and [Tilia cordata], associated with [Sorbus aucuparia], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Acer platanoides]. [Carpinus betulus] is absent. [Corylus avellana] may be well represented in the shrub layer. The herb layer is usually dominated by hygro-mesophilous species, in particular, [Stellaria holostea], [Lamium galeobdolon], [Poa nemoralis]; acidophilous species, notably [Luzula luzuloides], [Carex brizoides] are frequent, the latter sometimes forming facies. Other characteristic species include [Hepatica nobilis], [Convallaria majalis], [Aegopodium podagraria], [Oxalis acetosella], [Milium effusum], [Lilium martagon], [Euphorbia dulcis], [Lathyrus vernus]. Some stands are dominated by [Tilia cordata] (unit 41.G1 x 41.2653).', '(Moravec y al., 1982: 148-152, unit 6; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 131; Neuh¿uslova, 1998: 101-102, 285, unit 12).');
