    'Formations of the alluvial banks of small streams, characteristic of collinar and low montane levels of the Alpine system and the Hercynian ranges of Western and Central Europe and of northern Eastern Europe, constituted by [Petasites hybridus] ([Petasites officinalis]), [Petasites albus], [Petasites kablikianus] ([Petasites glabratus]), sometimes by [Chaerophyllum hirsutum] or [Equisetum telmateia], occasionally accompanied by various tall herbs, in particular, [Cirsium oleraceum], or by ferns.', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: unit 130; Soo, 1961, 1980; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Sanda y al., 1980: 58; Korotkov y al., 1991: 146; Mucina, 1993c: 231-239; Frankard y al., 1998: 39-40; Seliskar, 1998: 12).');
    'Screens or veils of perennial tall herbs, [Senecio fluviatilis], [Eupatorium cannabinum], [Epilobium hirsutum], [Sonchus palustris], [Urtica dioica], small bushes and lianas, [Calystegia sepium], [Cuscusta europaea], lining lowland watercourses, and sometimes other water bodies, of Western, Central and northern Eastern Europe, outside of the steppe and wooded-steppe zones, with many ruderal and introduced plants, such as [Aster spp.], [Rudbeckia spp.], [Solidago spp.], [Helianthus spp.], [Impatiens spp.], [Reynoutria japonica].', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: units 32, 33; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Duvigneaud, 1967; Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1973; Sanda y al., 1980: 104; Moravec y al., 1983: 93-94; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 70; Géhu, 1984a; Delescaille, 1987: 77; Oberdorfer, 1990; Korotkov y al., 1991: 146; Mucina, 1993c: 231-239; Hoda y al., 1998: 10).');
    'Screens or veils of perennial tall herbs, [Senecio fluviatilis], [Eupatorium cannabinum], [Epilobium hirsutum], [Sonchus palustris], [Urtica dioica], small bushes and lianas, [Calystegia sepium], [Cuscusta europaea], lining lowland watercourses, and sometimes other water bodies, of the steppe and wooded-steppe zones of Eurasia, including, in the west, the Pannonic basin and the lower Danube valley, with many ruderal and introduced plants, such as [Aster spp.], [Rudbeckia spp.], [Solidago spp.], [Helianthus spp.], [Impatiens spp.], [Reynoutria japonica].', '(Soo, 1961, 1980; Sanda y al., 1980: 104).');
