    'Isolated, species-rich beech forest of the Sainte-Baume range of Provence, characterized by the strong representation of evergreen undergrowth, the development of the vegetation strata and the multiple waves of flowering.  Among accompanying species are [Taxus baccata], [Ilex aquifolium], [Acer opulifolium], [Viburnum lantana], [Coronilla emerus], [Ruscus aculeatus], [Mycelis muralis], [Lilium martagon], [Neottia nidus-avis], [Helleborus foetidus], [Digitalis lutea]. ', NULL);
