    'Neutrophile [Fagus sylvatica] forests, sometimes with a small admixture of [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Picea abies] and [Abies alba], with a rich [Fagetalia] flora and regionally characteristic Dacian species including [Symphytum cordatum], [Cardamine glanduligera] ([Dentaria glandulosa]), [Pulmonaria rubra], [Hepatica transsilvanica], [Ranunculus carpaticus], widespread on rich soils throughout the Romanian and Ukrainian Carpathians, where they form the zonal forests of the lower and middle montane belt, between 600 and 1100 metres.', '(Beldie, 1951; Vida, 1963; Soo, 1964; Sanda y al., 1980; Boscaiu y al., 1982; Coldea, 1991: 498, 1992; Donita and Coldea, 1992; Sanda y al., 1992; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992; Sanda and Popescu, 1993).');
    'Neutrophile [Fagus sylvatica-Abies alba] forests with a rich [Fagetalia] flora and Dacian regional species such as [Pulmonaria rubra], [Cardamine glanduligera] ([Dentaria glandulosa]), [Symphytum cordatum], [Hepatica transsilvanica], [Ranunculus carpaticus], [Campanula abietina], widely distributed throughout the Romanian and Ukrainian Carpathians, on rich brown, leached or acid soils of steep slopes at altitudes comprised between 700 and 1300 m.', '(Beldie, 1951; Soo, 1962, 1964; Vida, 1963; Sanda y al., 1980; Boscaiu y al., 1982; Coldea, 1991: 499, 1992; Donita and Coldea, 1992; Sanda y al., 1992; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992).');
    'Acidocline [Fagus sylvatica]-[Picea abies] forests of the high southeastern Carpathians, occupying the upper fringe of the montane beech forests, at altitudes between 800 and 1350 metres, on acid brown soils, with [Leucanthemum waldsteinii] and a cortŠge otherwise typical of the [Symphyto-Fagenion], including [Oxalis acetosella], [Symphytum cordatum], [Pulmonaria rubra], [Cardamine glanduligera].', '(Coldea, 1991: 499-500; Donita and Coldea, 1992; Sanda and Popescu, 1993).');
    'Forests of [Fagus sylvatica], or sometimes [Fagus moesiaca] and [Carpinus betulus], occasionally of [Fagus sylvatica] without [Carpinus betulus], of the montane level of the Romanian, Ukrainian and eastern Serbian Carpathians and pre-Carpathian hills, accompanied by an eastern [Carpinion] cortŠge that includes [Tilia cordata], [Prunus avium], [Lathyrus hallersteinii], [Melampyrum bihariense], [Aposeris foetida], [Stellaria holostea], [Ranunculus auricomus], [Galium schultesii], [Carex pilosa], [Dactylis glomerata]. ', '(Boscaiu y al., 1974; Coldea, 1991: 487; Donita, 1992).');
    'Neutrophile forests of [Fagus sylvatica], or sometimes [Fagus moesiaca], and [Carpinus betulus], often with an admixture of [Quercus petraea], or, in more thermophile variants, [Quercus cerris], widely distributed in the lower montane belt of the Romanian and Ukrainian Carpathians and high pre-Carpathian hills, mostly above 500-600 metres, with a typical [Lathyro-Carpinion] cortŠge formed by, in particular, [Galium schultesii], [Carex pilosa], [Melampyrum bihariense], [Aposeris foetida], [Stellaria holostea], [Ranunculus auricomus], accompanied by Dacian elements such as [Cardamine glanduligera] ([Dentaria glandulosa]), [Symphytum cordatum], [Helleborus purpurascens].', '(Pauca, 1941; Vida, 1963; Soo, 1964; Boscaiu y al., 1982; Coldea, 1991: 487-492; Coldea, 1992; Donita and Coldea, 1992; Sanda y al., 1992; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992; Coldea and Chifu, 1994).');
    'Neutrophile [Fagus sylvatica]-[Carpinus betulus] beech forests with [Lathyrus hallersteinii] in the herb layer, of limited distribution in the southern Apuseni Mountains and the Petrosani Depression.', '(Gergely, 1968; Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Orchid-rich [Fagus sylvatica-Carpinus betulus] forests developed on calcareous substrates with rendzina-type soils of the montane belt of the Romanian Carpathians and pre-Carpathian hills, Dacian vicariant of the northern and central Central European [Carici-Fagetum], with [Cephalanthera rubra], [Cephalanthera damasonium], [Epipactis microphylla], [Epipactis helleborine], [Helleborus purpurascens], [Daphne mezereum], [Cardamine bulbifera], [Hepatica nobilis], [Mycelis muralis], [Salvia glutinosa], [Campanula rapunculoides], [Melica nutans].', '(Coldea, 1991: 487; Coldea and Chifu, 1994).
');
    'Neutrophile [Fagus sylvatica] forests of high pre-Carpathian hills, with a distinct medio-European character and an impoverished Dacian floral element, somewhat transitional between more western communities of the [Fagion medio-Europaeum] and the Dacian [Lathyro-Carpinion] and [Symphyto-Fagion], an intermediate position illustrated by the prevalence of [Cardamine bulbifera] ([Dentaria bulbifera]) and [Carex pilosa] combined with the absence of [Carpinus betulus] and of Dacian montane elements.', '(Sanda y al., 1980).');
    'Local [Fagus sylvatica] and [Fagus sylvatica]-[Picea abies] forests of the tree-limit in the upper montane or subalpine level of the high southern Carpathians, developed where subalpine [Picea abies] forests do not form an uninterrupted zone, less well individualized than more western formations of the [Aceri-Fagion], though, like them, characterized by the admixture of [Acer pseudoplatanus] in the canopy and of [Adenostyletalia] megaphorb species in the understorey.', '(Sanda y al., 1980; Ozenda, 1985: 316; Jahn, 1991: 469, 470; Coldea, 1991: 488-493; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992: 60, 213-216).');
    'Neutrophile to weakly acidophile [Fagus sylvatica-Picea abies] forests with a mixed cortŠge composed of [Fagetalia]  species, in particular [Symphyto-Fagion] characteristics, and of [Vaccinio-Piceetalia] and [Adenostyletalia] species, of the subalpine or upper montane level of high mountains of the southern Carpathians.', '(Domin, 1933; Vida, 1963; Boscaiu y al., 1982; Coldea, 1991).');
    'Mixed forests of colluvions and screes of humid, shady river valley slopes of the Hercynian ranges and the Western Carpathians, transitional between ravine forests and [Carpinion betuli] communities, formed by [Quercus robur], [Quercus petraea], [Fagus sylvatica], [Ulmus glabra], [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Acer platanoides], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Carpinus betulus], [Alnus glutinosa].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1953; Duvigneaud and Mullenders, 1962; Tanghe, 1964a, 1964b, 1968, 1970; Duvigneaud and Denayer-De Smet, 1970; Moravec y al., 1982; Moravec y al., 1983; Noirfalise, 1984; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993; Husova, 1998).');
    'Mixed forests of [Quercus robur], [Quercus petraea], [Fagus sylvatica], [Ulmus glabra], [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Acer platanoides], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Carpinus betulus], [Alnus glutinosa], with [Hedera helix], [Polygonatum verticillatum], [Galium odoratum], [Ranunculus platanifolius], [Centaurea montana], [Poa chaixii], [Pulmonaria montana], [Circaea alpina], [Sambucus racemosa] of large, shaded slopes of the Hercynian ranges and their periphery, within the zone of transition from oceanic to continental climates. ', '(Vanden Berghen, 1953; Tanghe, 1959, 1964a, 1964b, 1968, 1970; Duvigneaud and Mullenders, 1962; Duvigneaud and Denayer-De Smet, 1970; Noirfalise, 1984).');
    'Mixed forests dominated by [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Acer platanoides], [Ulmus glabra], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Fraxinus excelsior], with [Carpinus betulus], and, locally, [Quercus robur], [Quercus petraea], [Fagus sylvatica], [Tilia cordata], [Abies alba], [Taxus baccata], widespread in the oak-hornbeam level of the Bohemian plateau and its northern, southern and eastern limiting ranges, extending to the southern side of the Bohemian Quadrangle in Upper and Lower Austria and to the Western Carpathians of Slovakia. They are developed in shady, humid slopes of river and stream valleys, on siliceous or calcareous substrates.', '(Moravec y al., 1982: 153-163, unit 1; Moravec y al., 1983; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 121-123; Husova, 1998: 103-107, unit 13 [p.]).');
    'Mixed slope forests of the montane and submontane beech level of the Bohemian Quadrangle, with very local occurrences in the Western Carpathians and in the Jaunitztal of Upper Austria, formed by [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Ulmus glabra], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Acer platanoides], [Fagus sylvatica], with [Galium odoratum], [Lamiastrum galeobdolon] ssp. [montanum], [Mercurialis perennis], [Dryopteris filix-mas], [Oxalis acetosella].', '(Moravec y al., 1982: 182-187, unit 5; Moravec y al., 1983; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 108; Husova, 1998: 103-107, unit 13 [p.]).');
    'Mixed forests of [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Fraxinus excelsior] and [Ulmus glabra], developed on colluvial deep soils at the foot of very rainy slopes and on rarely inundated river sediments of the submontane to high montane levels of the northern pre-Alps and their piedmont, with [Prunus avium], [Prunus padus], [Alnus incana], [Alnus glutinosa], [Fagus sylvatica], [Carpinus betulus], [Quercus robur], [Corylus avellana], [Mercurialis perennis], [Aegopodium podagraria], [Cirsium oleraceum], [Deschampsia cespitosa], [Filipendula ulmaria], [Carex pendula], [Equisetum telmateia], [Matteuccia struthiopteris], [Primula elatior], [Brachypodium sylvaticum], [Cardamine trifolia], [Carex sylvatica], [Paris quadrifolia], [Stachys sylvatica].  ', '(Mayer, 1974; Ellenberg, 1988; Jahn, 1991: 423; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 110-112).');
    'Mixed forests of [Ulmus glabra], [Acer campestre], [Acer opalus], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Fagus sylvatica], [Quercus petraea], [Quercus robur], [Tilia cordata], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Sorbus aria], [Sorbus mougeotii], [Alnus glutinosa], [Pinus sylvestris], [Hedera helix], with an understorey comprising numerous shrubs, such as [Corylus avellana] and [Crataegus monogyna], and a rich and luxuriant herb layer including numerous ferns, characteristic of the bottom colluvions of steep, shaded valleys, canyons and gorges of the collinar to montane levels of the Pyrenean and Cantabrian ranges. ', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969a; Vigo and Ninot, 1987). ');
    'Thermophilous forests of [Tilia cordata], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Acer platanoides], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Ulmus glabra], [Fagus sylvatica] with [Euonymus latifolius], [Corylus avellana], most typical of the warm valleys of the Alpine system and some peripheral ranges, characterized by [Asperula taurina], [Cyclamen purpurascens] and numerous transgressives of the [Quercetalia pubescenti-petraeae]. These remarkable relict forests are particularly characteristic of the f¿hn valleys of the Insubrian and northern Alps; they occur in similar situations in the Jura and the Hercynian ranges, north to the Harz.', '(Mayer, 1974; Ellenberg, 1988: 143-145; Jahn, 1991: 423). ');
    'Forests dominated by [Tilia platyphyllos] and [Fraxinus excelsior], sometimes by [Acer pseudoplatanus], with [Ulmus glabra], characteristic of warm, humid f¿hn valleys of the northern face of the Alps. [Corylus avellana] often dominates the understorey, which also includes [Tamus communis], and an abundance of [Asperula taurina] ssp. [taurina], [Mercurialis perennis], [Lamiastrum galeobdolon] ssp. [montanum], [Aegopodium podagraria], [Brachypodium sylvaticum], [Galium odoratum], [Salvia glutinosa], [Viola reichenbachiana] and [Cyclamen purpurascens].', '(Mayer, 1974; Ellenberg, 1988; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 126-127).');
    'Forests dominated by [Acer pseudoplatanus] and [Tilia platyphyllos] developed on unstable substrates of steep slopes in warm and summer-dry regions and microclimatic stations in the Jura, the Hercynian ranges, the northern and northeastern pre-Alps and neighbouring plateaux.', '(Ellenberg, 1988; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 124).');
    'Extensive [Quercus cerris]-dominated forests of the hills and low mountain slopes of the Pelagonids, the Pindus, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, the Rhodopids, the Thessalian mountains, in particular of the supra-Mediterranean level of northern and middle Greece (Macedonia, Thrace, Epiros, Thessaly, Central Greece), of the xerothermal oak belt of southern and southwestern Bulgaria, of the F.Y.R. of Macedonia and of Albania.', '(Em, 1964b, 1968; Debazac and Mavrommatis, 1971; Horvat y al., 1974: 226-227; Lakushik, 1976, 1980; Gamisans and Hébrard, 1979; Ozenda y al., 1979; Noirfalise, 1986, 1987; Bondev, 1991: units 91, 93, 96, [p.]; Hoda y al., 1998: 16; Micevski, 1999).');
    'Extensive [Quercus frainetto]-dominated forests of the hills and low mountain slopes of the Pelagonids, the Pindus, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, the Rhodopids, the Thessalian mountains, in particular of the supra-Mediterranean level of northern and middle Greece (Macedonia, Thrace, Epiros, Thessaly, Central Greece), of the xerothermal oak belt of southern and southwestern Bulgaria, of the F.Y.R. of Macedonia and of Albania.', '(Fukarek, 1970; Debazac and Mavrommatis, 1971; Horvat y al., 1974: 226-227; Gamisans and Hébrard, 1979; Ozenda y al., 1979; Noirfalise, 1986, 1987; Bondev, 1991: units 91, 93, 100, 101, 105, [p.]; Hoda y al., 1998: 16).');
    '[Quercus dalechampii]-dominated forests of the hills and mountain slopes of the Pelagonids, the Pindus, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, the Rhodopids. They include, in particular, the xero-mesophile [Quercus dalechampii]-dominated forests, sometimes mixed with [Quercus cerris], [Quercus frainetto] or [Fraxinus excelsior], with [Carpinus orientalis], [Ostrya carpinifolia] or [Fraxinus ornus] often present and sometimes abundant, widespread in the durmast oak-hornbeam, 600-1200 metre, belt of the Rhodopides and the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, drier than the [Carpinus betulus]-[Quercus dalechampii] forests of unit 41.2C35. [Ruscus aculeatus] is often present and sometimes subdominant in their undergrowth. They also include local formations of the upper supra-Mediterranean level of northern and middle Greece, mostly of the Pindus and of crystalline or metamorphic ranges of the southern Moeso-Macedonian mountains and Rhodopides, likewise altitudinally inserted between [Quercus frainetto] and beech forests. ', '(Debazac and Mavrommatis, 1971; Horvat y al., 1974:226-227; Gamisans and Hébrard, 1979; Bondev, 1991: 85-86, units 58-62 [p.]).');
    'Rare forests of the hills and low mountain slopes of the Pelagonids, the Pindus, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, the Rhodopids, in particular of the supra-Mediterranean level of northern and middle Greece, of the hornbeam-durmast oak belt of southwestern Bulgaria, the F.Y.R. of Macedonia and Albania, dominated by rare, endemic oak species, in particular [Quercus protoroburoides], or by highly disjunct populations of more northern species, in particular [Quercus petraea]. ', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 239-242; Andreev y al., 1992).');
    'Rare [Quercus petraea]-dominated forests of the hills and low mountain slopes of the Pelagonids, the Pindus, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, the Rhodopids, in particular of the supra-Mediterranean level of northern and middle Greece and of the hornbeam-durmast oak belt of southern and southwestern Bulgaria, the F.Y.R. of Macedonia and Albania.', '(Em, 1968; Horvat y al., 1974: 239-242; Andreev y al., 1992; Hoda y al., 1998: 16; Micevski, 1999).');
    'Endemic [Quercus protoroburoides] forests of the upper montane level of Rila.', '(Meshinev y al., 1993: 129; Spirodonov, 1994).');
    'Local [Quercus virgiliana]-dominated forests of the hills and low mountain slopes of the Pelagonids, the Pindus, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, the Rhodopids, the Thessalian mountains, in particular of the supra-Mediterranean [Quercion frainetto] level of northern and middle Greece (Macedonia, Thrace, Epiros, Thessaly, Central Greece) and of the "[Querceta frainetti]" component of the xerothermal oak belt of southern and southwestern Bulgaria. ', '(Bondev, 1991: unit 102 [p.]).');
    'Local [Quercus pedunculiflora]-dominated forests of the supra-Mediterranean level of northern and middle Greece. ', NULL);
    'Local [Quercus polycarpa]-dominated forests of the supra-Mediterranean [Quercion frainetto] level of Greece. ', NULL);
    'Xerophile or xeromesophile forests of [Quercus frainetto], [Quercus cerris], [Quercus petraea] and related deciduous oaks, of the subcontinental central and eastern Balkan peninsula, mostly of the xerothermal oak and hornbeam-durmast oak belts of Serbia and northern and central Bulgaria, in particular on the slopes of the Balkan Range and its associated hills and plateaux; irradiations extend into southern Romania. The associated flora has a marked southeastern European character and includes [Carpinus orientalis], [Fraxinus ornus], [Piptatherum virescens], [Paeonia peregrina], [Mercurialis ovata].', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 226-242; Sanda y al., 1980; Bondev, 1991).');
    'Oak forests of the lower level of the [Quercion frainetto] zone of the central and eastern Balkan peninsula, mostly dominated by [Quercus frainetto] and [Quercus cerris]. ', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 226-238; Bondev, 1991: units 90-105).');
    'Lowland mesophile hay meadows of the Atlantic domaine of Europe, characteristic of the British Isles and western France.', '(Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1973; Rodwell, 1992: units MG1, MG4; Rameau y al., 1993; Julve, 1993: 83-84).');
    'Lowland mesophile hay meadows of the British Isles and western France rich in, or dominated by [Arrhenatherum elatius] accompanied by [Dactylis glomerata] and [Holcus lanatus] with [Centaurea debeauxii] ssp. [nemoralis] ([Centaurea nigra], [Centaurea nemoralis]), [Rhinanthus lanceolatus], [Oenanthe pimpinelloides], [Gaudinia fragilis], [Linum bienne], [Brachypodium pinnatum].', '(Rodwell, 1992: unit MG1; Rameau y al., 1993; Julve, 1993: 83-84).');
    'Lowland mesophile hay meadows of England, characteristic of areas where traditional hay meadow treatment has been applied to seasonally flooded alluvial soils, formed by [Alopecurus pratensis], [Festuca rubra], [Cynosurus cristatus], [Lolium perenne], with less abundant or less constant [Holcus lanatus], [Anthoxanthum odoratum], [Dactylis glomerata], [Trisetum flavescens], [Agrostis stolonifera], [Bromus hordeaceus], [Arrhenatherum elatius], [Deschampsia cespitosa], [Festuca arundinacea], with many dicots, among which [Sanguisorba officinalis], [Filipendula ulmaria], [Leontodon spp.], [Taraxacum spp.] are often abundant and [Fritillaria meleagris] particularly noteworthy.', '(Rodwell, 1992: unit MG4; Rameau y al., 1993; Julve, 1993: 83-84).');
    'Mesophile lowland hay meadows of sub-Atlantic Western Europe, of western and northern Central Europe, of the humid Illyrian region and of the eastern Carpathian system, with [Arrhenatherum elatius], [Daucus carota], [Crepis biennis], [Knautia arvensis], [Leucanthemum vulgare], [Pimpinella major], [Trifolium dubium], [Geranium pratense], [Alchemilla xanthochlora], [Campanula patula], [Pastinaca sativa], [Galium album], [Equisetum arvense], [Medicago sativa], [Picris hieracioides], [Sanguisorba officinalis].', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: unit 133; Sougnez, 1951; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Archiloque y al., 1969; Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974: 221, 270-271, 396-398, 489; Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Matuszkiewicz and Matuszkiewicz, 1975: 106; Bournérias, 1979, 1984; Noirfalise y al., 1980, 1985; Sanda y al., 1980; Soo, 1980; De Sloover y al., 1980: 42-44; Moravec y al., 1983: 47; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.2.1; Delescaille, 1987: 76; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1993b; Coldea, 1991; Korotkov y al., 1991: 162-163; Ellmauer and Mucina, 1993; Påhlsson, 1994: units 5.2.2.1, 5.2.2.3, 5.2.2.3a; Krahulec y al., 1996: 40; Seliskar, 1998: 17).');
    'Drier, more thermophile, swards of the lowland sub-Atlandic mesophile hay meadows of Western Europe and Central Europe, dominated by [Arrhenatherum elatius], and with a species composition that includes [Festuco-Brometea] dry grassland species, in particular, [Salvia pratensis], [Bromus erectus], [Ranunculus bulbosus], [Dianthus carthusianorum], [Pimpinella saxifraga], [Plantago media], [Galium verum], [Euphorbia cyparissias], [Linum catharticum].', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: units 133d, 133e, 133f; Thill, 1964: 48-49; De Sloover y al., 1980: 42-44; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.2.1; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1993b; Korotkov y al., 1991: 163; Ellmauer and Mucina, 1993: 346-348; Påhlsson, 1994: units 5.2.2.1, 5.2.2.3, 5.2.2.3a; Kwiatkowski, 1997: 276-278; Seliskar, 1998: 17).');
    'More humid, or temporarily more humid, swards of the lowland sub-Atlandic mesophile hay meadows of Western Europe and Central Europe, dominated by [Arrhenatherum elatius] and [Alopecurus pratensis], or by the latter alone, and with a species composition intermediate between that of mesophile and humid meadows (37) with [Cirsium oleraceum], [Angelica sylvestris], [Sanguisorba officinalis], [Ranunculus repens], [Myosotis palustris], [Glechoma hederacea], [Lychnis flos-cuculi], [Ajuga reptans], [Cardamine pratensis], [Lysimachia nummularia], [Geranium pratense], [Campanula patula], [Pastinaca sativa], [Heracleum sphondylium], [Anthriscus sylvestris]. Towards the east, in more continental climates, the [Alopecurus] meadows communities increasingly take the character of humid riverine meadows; they have been included in 37 from the Pannonic region eastwards, in the range of the mesophile meadows of 38.5.', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: units 133a, 133b, 133c, 133g; Thill, 1964: 48-49; De Sloover y al., 1980: 42-44; Oberdorfer, 1990, 1993b; Korotkov y al., 1991: 163; Ellmauer and Mucina, 1993: 344-346, 348-349; Seliskar, 1998: 17).');
    'Mesophile grasslands of middle European Hercynian hills, of the middle elevations of the greater Hercynian ranges, the Jura, the pre-Alps, the Dinarides, the Pelagonides, the Carpathians, the Pyrenees, the mountains of the northwestern Iberian peninsula, intermediate between the lowland meadows of unit 38.22 and the montane meadows of unit 38.3.', '(Sougnez, 1951; Tüxen and Oberdorfer, 1958; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Horvat y al., 1974; Noirfalise y al., 1980, 1985; De Sloover y al., 1980: 44-46; Moravec y al., 1983; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987; Diaz Gonzalez and Fernandez Prieto, 1987: 103; Bolos y Capdevila, 1987: 316; Coldea, 1991; Oberdorfer, 1993b: 418-422).');
    'Hay meadows of higher elevations of the lesser Hercynian ranges, with [Meum athamanticum], [Festuca nigrescens], [Geranium sylvaticum], [Lathyrus montanus], [Phyteuma spicatum], [Potentilla erecta], [Galium saxatile], [Ranunculus bulbosus], [Pimpinella saxifraga], [Lotus uliginosus].
', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: unit 134; Sougnez, 1951; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Noirfalise y al., 1980, 1985; De Sloover y al., 1980: 44-46; Oberdorfer, 1993b; Frankard y al., 1998: 30-33).');
    'Hay meadows of mid-elevations of the great Hercynian ranges of Central Europe and of the hills of the eastern Germano-Baltic Plain, in particular, of the Baltic States. ', '(Moravec y al., 1983: 47; Korotkov y al., 1991: 163; Krahulec y al., 1996: 40-43).');
    '[Fagus sylvatica] forests with [Acer pseudoplatanus] characterized by the presence of [Ribes uva-crispa], [Glechoma hirsuta], [Lamium maculatum] and [Ulmus glabra], on very damp slopes of the subalpine or upper montane level of  the southern and southwestern Carpathians.', '(Coldea, 1991: 488-493, 501).');
    '[Fagus sylvatica] forests developed on limestones of the eastern and southern Carpathians and pre-Carpathian hills, harbouring a strongly calciphile and thermophile cortŠge.
', '(Boscaiu y al., 1982).');
    'Calcicolous [Fagus sylvatica] forests of mountains and high hills in the western part of the southern Carpathians and in the Apuseni mountains, developed on rendzinas, over limestone substrates, with an abundant representation of the calcicline segment of the [Fagetalia] cortŠge, in particular, [Mercurialis perennis], [Sanicula europaea], [Actaea spicata], accompanied by thermophile species such as [Fraxinus ornus] and [Aristolochia pallida], and by numerous orchids, among which [Epipactis helleborine], [Epipactis microphylla], [Cephalanthera rubra], [Cephalanthera damasonium]. ', '(Resmerita, 1972; Sanda y al., 1980; Boscaiu y al., 1982; Donita and Coldea, 1992: 148-149).');
    'Xero-mesophile, neutrophile to basiphile [Fagus sylvatica] woods developed on  rendzina soils over limestone rocks in low mountains of the western and southern Romanian Carpathians, characterized by the dominance of [Sesleria rigida] in the field layer, accompanied by calciphile herbs, notably [Epipactis atrorubens].
', '(Soo, 1969; Sanda y al., 1980; Coldea, 1991).');
    '[Fagus sylvatica] or [Fagus moesiaca] forests of the southwestern and southern Carpathians and pre-Carpathian hills, with southern European floristic elements, including [Aremonia agrimonoides], [Festuca drymeja], [Helleborus odorus], [Tilia tomentosa], [Corylus colurna], of Illyrian or Moesian affinities.', '(Borza, 1931b, 1958; Horvat, 1950; Boscaiu, 1971; Horvat y al., 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Coldea, 1991).');
    'Neutrophile or basicline montane [Fagus sylvatica] forests widespread in the southwestern Carpathians, characterized by the presence of thermophile species of Illyrian affinities, in particular, [Aremonia agrimonoides], [Potentilla micrantha], [Fraxinus ornus], [Tamus communis] and the extreme rarefaction of typical [Symphyto-Fagion] Carpathian species.
', '(Boscaiu, 1971; Sanda y al., 1980; Coldea, 1991: 499; Donita and Coldea, 1992).');
    'Neutrophile low montane [Fagus moesiaca] forests with [Corylus colurna] and a cortŠge of southern species, including [Primula columnae], [Fraxinus ornus], [Lathyrus venetus], [Knautia drymeia], [Ruscus hypoglossum], occupying small surfaces in a few localities of the southwestern Carpathians, south to the Rtanj range of eastern Serbia; they are related to Moesian formations of unit  41.19, in particular unit 41.1934.', '(Borza, 1958; Borhidi, 1963; Horvat y al., 1974: 507-509; Donita and Coldea, 1992).');
    'Neutrophile to weakly acidophile [Fagus moesiaca] forests, of low mountains and hills of the southwestern Romanian Carpathians and pre-Carpathian ranges, with a cortŠge of southern, in part Illyrian, species, including [Helleborus odorus], [Asperula taurina], [Daphne laureola], [Ruscus aculeatus], [Tamus communis], [Tilia tomentosa].', '(Soo and Borhidi, 1960; Soo, 1960; Sanda y al., 1980; Donita and Coldea, 1992).');
    'Weakly acidophile to acidophile [Fagus sylvatica] or [Fagus moesiaca] forests of the upper part of sunny slopes of the mountains and hills of the southern and southwestern Carpathians, with an herb layer dominated by [Festuca drymeja] and in which [Luzula luzuloides] is always present and the [Symphyto-Fagenion] species poorly represented.', '(Morariu y al., 1968; Coldea, 1991: 498-499; Donita and Coldea, 1992).');
    'Forests of [Fagus sylvatica], [Fagus taurica] and [Fagus orientalis] of hills and low mountains of the eastern flank of the southeastern Carpathians, of the central plateau of Romanian Moldavia and the Republic of Moldova, of the Podolian plateau of the western Ukraine, mostly with a cortŠge comprised of southern European elements, including [Tilia tomentosa], [Cornus mas], [Potentilla micrantha], [Carex brevicollis], [Corydalis bulbosa] ssp. [marshalliana] ([Corydalis marshalliana]), [Lathyrus venetus], [Lathyrus aureus], [Cardamine quinquefolia] ([Dentaria quinquefolia]).', '(Dobrescu and Kovacs, 1973; Sanda y al., 1980; Jahn, 1991: 453).');
    'Tall neutrophile forests of hills and low mountain slopes of the eastern flank of the southeastern Carpathians, of the central plateau of Romanian Moldavia and the Republic of Moldova, at an altitude of 200-400 metres, with an upper canopy formed by [Fagus sylvatica], [Fagus taurica] and [Fagus orientalis], mixed with [Tilia tomentosa], [Tilia cordata], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Quercus petraea], [Acer pseudoplatanus], and a lower stratum of [Carpinus betulus], [Acer platanoides], [Acer campestre], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Prunus avium], varied shrub and liana strata comprising [Corylus avellana], [Hedera helix] and a species-rich herb layer with [Carex pilosa], [Carex brevicollis] and the regional differential taxa [Corydalis bulbosa] ssp. [marshalliana] ([Corydalis marshalliana]), [Lathyrus venetus], [Lathyrus aureus], [Cardamine quinquefolia] ([Dentaria quinquefolia]).
', '(Dobrescu and Kovacs, 1973; Sanda y al., 1980; Jahn, 1991; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992; Coldea and Chifu, 1994).');
    'Forests dominated by [Acer pseudoplatanus] and [Tilia platyphyllos] developed on unstable substrates of steep slopes in warm and summer-dry regions and microclimatic stations in the Jura, the Hercynian ranges, the northern and northeastern pre-Alps and neighbouring plateaux, with [Acer campestre], [Acer platanoides], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Quercus petraea], [Quercus pubescens], [Carpinus betulus], [Prunus avium], [Sorbus aria], [Corylus avellana], [Cornus mas], [Lonicera xylosteum], [Lonicera alpigena], [Staphylea pinnata], [Lamiastrum galeobdolon] ssp. [montanum], [Mercurialis perennis], [Arabis turrita], [Carex alba], [Convallaria majalis], [Laser trilobum], [Buphthalmum salicifolium], [Campanula persicifolia], [Epipactis atrorubens], [Euphorbia cyparissias], [Fragaria moschata], [Gymnocarpium robertianum], [Laserpitium latifolium], [Sesleria albicans], [Silene vulgaris], [Viola hirta], [Vincetoxicum hirundinaria], [Stachys sylvatica], [Aegopodium podagraria].', '(Ellenberg, 1988; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 124).');
    'Thermophile slope forests of the western Jura of Switzerland, of more distinctly sub-Mediterranean character than those of unit 41.4521, dominated by [Tilia spp.] and [Quercus spp.]', '(Kissling, 1983; Oberdorfer, 1992b: 181).');
    'Thermophilous forests of [Tilia cordata], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Acer platanoides], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Ulmus glabra] of warm valleys with high rainfall of the southern Alps, where, within a context of warmer regional climate, they are associated with relatively cool stations, such as north-facing slopes, in contrast with their warm-exposure linked northern counterparts.', '(Mayer, 1974; Jahn, 1991: 464-465).');
    'Thermophilous forests of [Tilia cordata], [Tilia platyphyllos], [Acer pseudoplatanus], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Ulmus glabra], [Ostrya carpinifolia], [Castanea sativa], [Fraxinus ornus], of the valleys of the Insubrian Alps, with [Euonymus latifolius], [Corylus avellana], [Daphne laureola], [Ligustrum vulgare], [Viburnum lantana], [Ruscus aculeatus], [Asperula taurina], [Cyclamen purpurascens], [Lamiastrum galeobdolon], [Cirsium erisithales], [Viola reichenbachiana], [Galium sylvaticum], [Geranium sanguineum].', '(Mayer, 1974; Ellenberg, 1988; Jahn, 1991: 464-465).');
    'Thermophile slope and ravine forests of the southwestern Alps, of distinctively submediterranean character, dominated by [Acer opalus], [Tilia spp.] and [Quercus spp.]', '(Braun-Blanquet y al., 1952; Oberdorfer, 1992b: 181).');
    'Forests of [Tilia platyphyllos], sometimes with [Fraxinus excelsior], of steep slopes of submontane to high montane levels of the Hungarian Central Range and of adjacent Carpathian hills of middle Slovakia. Forests of the same area, similarly dominated by [Tilia platyphyllos] and [Fraxinus excelsior], but with the character of steppe forests and developed on exposed crests, have been listed under unit 41.842 (oro-Pannonic steppe ash-lime forests, [Tilio-Fraxinetum]).', '(Soo, 1980; Oberdorfer, 1992b: 181).');
    'Forests dominated by [Tilia platyphyllos] ssp. [subrubra] and [Fraxinus excelsior] developed on unstable limestone block slopes with humus rich, deep soils, of submontane regions of the Hungarian Central Range and middle Slovakia, with a well developed shrub layer and and an herb layer characterized by [Waldsteinia geoides], [Scutellaria columnae], [Gagea minima] and the endemic [Hesperis vrabelyiana].
', '(Zolyomi, 1958; Fekete and Komlodi, 1982; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 124; Fekete y al., 1995).');
    'Very rare forests of [Tilia platyphyllos] of very steep ravine slopes of higher montane levels of the Northern Hungarian Range, developed in the absence of the Carpathian [Picea abies] subalpine belt, with an understorey comprising numerous locally rare, relict species, including [Viola biflora], [Valeriana tripteris], [Cimicifuga europaea] ([Cimicifuga foetida]), and the endemic [Sorbus austriaca] ssp. [hazslinszkyana] ([Sorbus hazslinszkyana]). ', '(Zolyomi y al., 1954; Soo, 1980; Oberdorfer, 1992b).');
    'Ravine and steep slope forests of the Dinarides, the Eastern Carpathians, the Balkan Range, the Pelagonids, the Moeso-Macedonian mountains, the Rhodopids, the Pindus, the Thessalian mountains, within the range of the [Fagion moesiacum], [Fagion hellenicum], [Fagion dacicum] and [Fagion illyricum]. ', '(Horvat y al., 1974; Boscaiu y al., 1982; Bergmeier, 1990; Jahn, 1991; Bondev, 1991; Coldea, 1991; Oberdorfer, 1992b; Wallnöfer y al., 1993: 112-113).');
    'Ravine and steep slope forests of the southern Pelagonids, Moeso-Macedonian mountains and Rhodopids, of the Pindus, of the Thessalian mountains, within the range of the southern [Fagion moesiacum] and of the [Fagion hellenicum], in areas of strong sub-Mediterranean influence. ', '(Horvat y al., 1974; Bergmeier, 1990; Jahn, 1991; Oberdorfer, 1992b).');
    'Formations of [Aesculus hippocastanum], [Juglans regia], [Fraxinus excelsior] of narrow, warm, humid, shaded ravines, gorge walls and abrupt slopes of the beech zone of the Pindus and the Thessalian mountains. ', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 73, 509-511; Bergmeier, 1990; Jahn, 1991: 490; Oberdorfer, 1992b: 181).');
    'Forests of scree and rock slopes of Chalkidiki, dominated by [Castanea sativa] and [Tilia tomentosa].', '(Dafis, 1973; Oberdorfer, 1992b: 181).');
    'Meso-xerophile, neutrophile forests of [Quercus frainetto] and [Quercus cerris] of the sub-continental central and eastern Balkan peninsula, mostly of the xero-thermal oak belt of Serbia and northern and central Bulgaria, in particular on the northern and southern slopes of the Balkan Range and their  associated hills and plateaux, extending to low mountains of the Danube Iron Gates region of Romania, accompanied by [Fraxinus ornus], [Carpinus orientalis], [Acer campestre], [Cornus mas], [Lychnis coronaria], [Rubus tomentosus], [Lathyrus niger], [Lathyrus venetus], [Helleborus odorus].', '(Jovanovic, 1955; Horvat y al., 1974; Boscaiu, 1971; Bondev, 1991: units 91, 93, [p.]).');
    'Meso-xerophile, neutrophile forests of [Quercus cerris], [Fraxinus ornus] and [Carpinus orientalis] of the subcontinental central and eastern Balkan peninsula, mostly of the xerothermal oak belt of Serbia and northern and central Bulgaria, in particular of the lower Danube basin and its fringing plateaux, extending north into Romania to low mountains of the Danube Iron Gates region and of the southwestern Dobrogea, with [Cornus mas], [Cotinus coggygria] and sub-Mediterranean species, including [Mercurialis ovata], [Buglossoides purpurocaerulea] ([Lithospermum purpurocaeruleum]), [Piptatherum virescens], [Vincetoxicum hirundinaria] ([Cynanchum vincetoxicum]).', '(Oberdorfer, 1948; Boscaiu, 1971; Bondev, 1991: units 97-99). ');
    'Mesoxerophile, neutrophile mixed oak forests of [Quercus frainetto], accompanied by some [Quercus dalechampii], [Quercus polycarpa], [Quercus pubescens], [Quercus virgiliana], [Fraxinus ornus], [Carpinus orientalis], [Tilia tomentosa] in the tree layer, [Cornus mas], [Cotinus coggygria] in the shrub layer and many sub-Mediterranean species, including [Paeonia peregrina], [Mercurialis ovata], [Piptatherum virescens], [Lychnis coronaria], in the herb layer, limited to small insular surfaces in the lower Danube valley of Bulgaria and in the Romanian Dobrogea.', '(Dihoru and Donita, 1970; Sanda y al., 1980; Bondev, 1991: unit 104 [p.]).');
    'Forests mostly dominated by [Quercus frainetto] and [Quercus petraea] [s.l.], of the upper level of the [Quercion frainetto] zone of the central and eastern Balkan peninsula. 

', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 227, 240-242; Bondev, 1991: units 58-63).');
    'Xero-mesophile [Quercus dalechampii]-dominated forests, sometimes mixed with [Quercus cerris], [Quercus frainetto] or [Fraxinus excelsior], with [Carpinus orientalis], [Ostrya carpinifolia] or [Fraxinus ornus] often present and sometimes abundant, widespread in the durmast oak-hornbeam, 600-1200 metre, belt of the Balkan Range and neighbouring hills, drier than the [Carpinus betulus-Quercus dalechampii] forests of 41.2C35.  [Ruscus aculeatus] is often present and sometimes subdominant in the undergrowth.', '(Bondev, 1991: 85-86, units 58-62 [p.]).');
    'Acidophile [Quercus petraea] [s.l.] forests of the southern and southwestern pre-Carpathian foothills, with [Galium pseudaristatum], [Luzula luzuloides], [Veronica officinalis], [Poa nemoralis], [Festuca heterophylla] in the herb layer.
 
', '(Roman, 1974; Sanda and Popescu, 1981).');
    'Oak forests of the Romanian Dobrogea dominated by [Quercus dalechampii], [Quercus polycarpa] or [Quercus pedunculiflora], rich in [Carpinus orientalis], [Tilia tomentosa], [Fraxinus ornus], [Fraxinus excelsior], of mixed Moesian and Pontic affinities, developed in stations ecologically intermediate between those that support [Carpinion betuli] forests of 41.72 and those that harbour steppe forests of 41.7A.', '(Dihoru and Donita, 1970; Sanda y al., 1980; Donita and Ivan, 1992: 94).');
    'Neutrophile [Quercus dalechampii] forests, limited to low hills of the Romanian Dobrogea, accompanied by [Fraxinus excelsior] ssp. [excelsior], [Fraxinus excelsior] ssp. [coriariifolia] ([Fraxinus coriariifolia]), [Fraxinus ornus], [Tilia tomentosa], [Carpinus orientalis] in the tree layer, with [Cornus mas] in the shrub layer, and [Paeonia peregrina] and other sub-Mediterranean species, including [Mercurialis ovata], [Piptatherum virescens], [Buglossoides purpurocaerulea] ([Lithospermum purpurocaeruleum]), in the herb layer.', '(Dihoru and Donita, 1970; Sanda y al., 1980; Donita and Ivan, 1992: 94).');
    'Xero-mesophile, neutrophile [Quercus dalechampii] and [Quercus polycarpa] forests of the northern Dobrogean plateaux, with [Tilia tomentosa], [Carpinus orientalis], [Carpinus betulus], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Fraxinus coriariifolia], [Fraxinus ornus], accompanied by numerous sub-Mediterranean species including [Nectaroscordum dioscoridis], [Lychnis coronaria], [Digitalis lanata], [Myrrhoides nodosa], [Mercurialis ovata], [Piptatherum virescens], and a few [Fagetalia] species, such as [Zerna benekenii], [Pulmonaria obscura], [Cardamine bulbifera].', '(Dihoru and Donita, 1970; Sanda y al., 1980; Donita and Ivan, 1992: 94).');
    'Xero-mesophile, neutrophile mixed [Quercus pedunculiflora] forests of the northern Dobrogea plateaux, with [Tilia tomentosa], [Carpinus orientalis], [Carpinus betulus], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Fraxinus ornus] in the tree layer, numerous sub-Mediterranean species, including [Ornithogalum fimbriatum], [Viola jordanii], [Paeonia peregrina], [Myrrhoides nodosa], [Mercurialis ovata], [Piptatherum virescens], and a few [Fagetalia] species, [Zerna benekenii], [Pulmonaria obscura], in the herb layer.', '(Dihoru and Donita, 1970; Sanda y al., 1980; Donita and Ivan, 1992b: 94).');
    'Mesophile hay meadows of low altitudes of Europe, fertilized and well-drained, with [Arrhenatherum elatius], [Trisetum flavescens], [Anthriscus sylvestris], [Heracleum sphondylium], [Daucus carota], [Crepis biennis], [Knautia arvensis], [Leucanthemum vulgare], [Pimpinella major], [Trifolium dubium], [Geranium pratense]; they are most characteristic of the Euro-Siberian zone, but extend to Atlantic Iberia, the Cordillera Central and Montseny, to the Apennines and to the supramediterranean zone of Greece.  ', '(Sougnez, 1951; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Ilijanic, 1965; Archiloque y al., 1969; Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Westhoff and den Held, 1975; Bournérias, 1979, 1984; Noirfalise y al., 1980, 1985; Soo, 1980; Moravec y al., 1983; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987; Diaz Gonzalez and Fernandez Prieto, 1987; Bolos y Capdevila, 1987; Oberdorfer, 1990; Korotkov y al., 1991; Rodwell, 1992; Påhlsson, 1994; Seliskar, 1998: 17).');
    'Hay meadows of mid-elevations of the great Hercynian ranges of Central Europe. ', '(Moravec y al., 1983: 47; Krahulec y al., 1996: 40-43).');
    'Hay meadows of siliceous substrates of the hills of the eastern Germano-Baltic Plain, in particular, of the Baltic States.', '(Korotkov y al., 1991: 163).');
    'Hay meadows of calcareous substrates of the hills of the Baltic States. ', '(Korotkov y al., 1991: 163).');
    'Hay meadows of the submontane level of the Carpathians, at about 600-700 m.', '(Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Coldea, 1991).');
    'Endemic community of the western Carpathians, with [Alchemilla walasii], [Alchemilla micans], [Alchemilla pastoralis], [Centaurea oxylepis], [Gladiolus imbricatus], [Viola saxatilis] var. [decorata].', '(Matuszkiewicz, 1980, 1984: 86, 172).');
    'Species-rich hay meadows of the Pienini and the Beskides, limited to thermophilous stations on deep calcareous soils, with [Medicago falcata], [Polygala comosa], [Thymus pulegioides], [Salvia verticillata], [Ranunculus polyanthemos].', '(Matuszkiewicz, 1980, 1984: 86, 172).');
    'Submontane mesophile meadows of the Romanian Carpathians, developed on nutrient-rich acid brown soils, dominated by [Trisetum flavescens], accompanied by [Arrhenatherum elatius] and a species cortŠge characteristic of the [Arrhenatherion], including [Campanula patula], [Trifolium repens], [Leucanthemum vulgare], [Lotus corniculatus].', '(Coldea, 1991: 465-468).');
