    'Humid, epiphyte-clad, dense, relict [Quercus faginea] forests of Portugal, restricted to a very few isolated localities. ', '(Braun-Blanquet y al., 1956).');
    'Humid and hyper-humid, luxuriant [Quercus canariensis] forests of the sierras of extreme southern Spain, limited to the Aljibe and a very few localities in the Serrania de Ronda. ', '(Rivas-Martinez, 1974a; Asensi Marfil and Diez Garretas, 1987: 219-220).');
    'Formations of Catalonia rich in [Quercus canariensis]. ', '(Rivas-Martinez, 1974a; Bolos y Capdevila, 1987).');
    'Relict formations of Mallorca dominated by, or rich in, [Quercus faginea]. ', '(Bolos and Molinier, 1958). ');
    'Montane forests, sometimes tall and closed canopied, of [Quercus canariensis] ([Quercus faginea] ssp. [baetica], [Quercus mirbeckii], [Quercus nordafricana], [Quercus faginea] ssp. tlemcenensis]), pure, or accompanied by [Quercus suber] or [Quercus afares], occupying cool, rainy slopes and tops of the Rif, the Middle Atlas, the Oulmes plateau, the Tell, the Kroumirian mountains, and, very locally, the High Atlas and the Aures. The shrub layer is rather sparce and includes, besides saplings of the dominant species, [Erica arborea], [Crataegus monogyna], [Myrtus communis], [Arbutus unedo], [Cytisus villosus], [Rubus ulmifolius], [Daphne gnidium], [Lonicera etrusca], [Hedera helix], and in very humid valleys, [Laurus nobilis]. The herb layer is abundant and rich, comprising the vernal [Ranunculus ficaria] ssp. [ficariiformis] ([Ficaria grandiflora]) and [Chrysanthemum], as well as [Agrimonia eupatoria], [Achillea ligustica], [Cyclamen africanum], [Satureja vulgaris] Fritsch, [Polystichum aculeatum], [Galium aparine], [Prunella vulgaris], [Carex remota], locally, [Pteridium aquilinum], [Sanicula europaea] or [Hypericum androsaemum]. Epyphytic growth is moderate, notably of [Polypodium vulgare] and lichens.', '(Quézel and Santa, 1963; Gounot and Schoenenberger, 1967; Herbauts, 1973: 348-349; Knapp, 1973: 477-479; White, 1983: 157; Walter and Breckle, 1991c: 41; Foucault, 1993b: 268; Benabid and Fennane, 1999: 82-83).');
    '[Quercus afares] stands or forests, pure or associated with [Quercus canariensis], limited to high altitudes in the Tell and the eastern Kroumirian mountains, in somewhat drier situations than those occupied by [Quercus canariensis] forest, though more humid than those characteristic of [Quercus suber] forests; the understorey includes [Cytisus villosus], [Erica arborea], [Genista tricuspidata], [Ilex aquifolium], [Ruscus aculeatus], [Paeonia atlantica], [Sanicula europaea], [Brachypodium sylvaticum], [Ampelodesmos mauritanica].', '(Quézel and Santa, 1963; Gounot and Schoenenberger, 1967; Knapp, 1973: 479; White, 1983: 157; Walter and Breckle, 1991c: 41).');
    'Xero-thermophilous oak woods of the southern wooded steppe zone, extending from northern Bulgaria and eastern Romania through the Ukraine and southern Russia to the Urals and the lower Volga. ', '(Zolyomi, 1957; Horvat y al., 1974).');
    'Subcontinental, xerophile-thermophile wooded steppe oak woods on leached chernozem soils of low hills and plains of southern and southeastern Romania and northeastern Bulgaria, with [Quercus pedunculiflora], [Acer tataricum], [Pyrus pyraster] in the tree layer, [Crataegus monogyna], [Ligustrum vulgare] in the shrub layer and [Vincetoxicum hirundinaria] ([Cynanchum vincetoxicum]), [Pulmonaria mollis], [Thalictrum minus], [Fragaria viridis], [Teucrium chamaedrys], [Viola hirta], [Buglossoides purpurocaerulea] ([Lithospermum purpurocaeruleum]) in the herb layer.', '(Borza, 1937; Bondev, 1991: 140-141, [p.]).');
    'Subcontinental, xerophile-thermophile wooded steppe oak woods, on leached chernozem soils, of low hills and plains of eastern and southern Romania, with [Quercus pubescens], [Acer tataricum], [Pyrus pyraster] in the tree layer, [Cotinus coggygria] in the shrub layer and [Buglossoides purpurocaerulea] ([Lithospermum purpurocaeruleum]), [Carex michelii], [Thalictrum minus], [Festuca rupicola], [Vicia tenuifolia] in the herb layer.', '(Borza, 1937; Barca, 1973; Jahn, 1991; Jahn, 1991: 453, 456). ');
    'Subcontinental, xerophile-thermophile woods of [Quercus pedunculiflora], [Quercus cerris], [Acer tataricum], [Pyrus pyraster] on leached chernozem soils of the plains of southern Romania, with [Prunus spinosa], [Ligustrum vulgare], [Crataegus monogyna] in the shrub layer and [Buglossoides purpurocaerulea] ([Lithospermum purpurocaeruleum]), [Vincetoxicum hirundinaria] ([Cynanchum vincetoxicum]), [Iris variegata], [Teucrium chamaedrys], [Fragaria viridis], [Polygonatum latifolium], [Lychnis coronaria] in the herb layer.', '(Morariu, 1944; Popescu y al., 1984).');
    '[Pinus uncinata] forests of the inner Alps, of the western outer Alps and the Jura, and of Pyrenean adrets, accompanied by a shrubby undergrowth in which [Rhododendron ferrugineum] is absent or rare, while [Juniperus nana], [Juniperus hemisphaerica], [Arctostaphylos uva-ursi], [Arctostaphylos alpinus], [Erica herbacea], [Rhododendron hirsutum], [Cotoneaster integerrimus], [Daphne striata], [Dryas octopetala] or [Polygala chamaebuxus] may be prominent. ', '(Gruber, 1978; Ozenda, 1981, 1985; Richard and Pautou, 1982; Dupias, 1985; Noirfalise, 1986, 1987; Vigo and Ninot, 1987; Bolos y Capdevilla, 1987). ');
