    'Timberline [Carpinus caucasica]-[Quercus macranthera] forests of the 1800 to 2000 metre level of northeastern slopes of the Central Caucasus of central Georgia, with [Sorbus caucasigena], [Daphne mezereum], [Lonicera caucasica], [Astrantia maxima], [Geranium sylvaticum], [Pulmonaria dacica], [Astrantia major], [Euphorbia macroceras], [Pimpinella rhodanta], [Betonica grandiflora], [Scutellaria altissima], [Vicia truncatula], [Campanula latifolia], [Calamagrostis arundinacea].', '(Korotkov y al., 1991: 307).');
