    'Species-rich mixed forests mostly of damp, poorly drained soils of the lowlands in the region of the southern end of the Caspian Sea, with an often dense, jungle-like understorey of tall shrubs, lianas, low shrubs and herbaceous plants. The species cortŠge includes, among others, the trees and tall shrubs [Alnus subcordata], [Alnus glutinosa], [Fraxinus excelsior], [Pterocarya fraxinifolia], [Populus caspica], [Diospyros lotus], [Ficus carica], [Salix fragilis], [Buxus sempervirens], [Albizia julibrissin], [Celtis australis], [Acer insigne], [Prunus caspica], [Prunus laurocerasus], [Mespilus germanica], [Paliurus spina-christi], [Punica granatum], lower shrubs, notably [Epimedium pinnatum], [Sambucus ebulus], [Andrachne calchiica], [Hypericum androsaemum], [Teucrium hercanum], [Ruscus hyrcanus], and climbers, in particular, [Periploca graeca], [Vitis sylvestris], [Clematis vitalba], [Hedera colchica], [Jasminum officinale], [Tamus communis], [Rubus caesus], [Solonum dulcamara].', '(Zohary, 1973: 566-567; Röhrig, 1991h: 533-534; Walter and Breckle, 1991c: 241-243).');
