    'Boreal and boreonemoral larch forests of Siberia, extending from the Urals, eastwards, dominated by [Larix sibirica] west of the Yenisei, were they are relatively uncommon, by [Larix dahurica] ([Larix gmelinii]) east of the Yenisei, where they constitute the dominant forest type.', '(Saphronova, 1964b: units 6, 7, 12, 15, 16, 20; Saphronova, 1964c: units 21-23, 28, 31-36, 41; Tikhomirov, 1970: 37; Birot, 1970: 115-118, 127-128, 159-160, 170-171; Walter, 1974: 79-104; Ehrenreich y al., 1982: 36; Walter and Breckle, 1986: 362-372, 387-405, 453-459; Rushforth, 1987; Rieley and Page, 1990; Molotkov and Patlaj, 1991; Boratynski, 1991; Korotkov y al., 1991: 276-278, 287-288, 288-292; Shugart y al., 1992; Huetz de Lemps, 1994: 85-87; Krassilov, 1995: 40).');
