    'Endemic [Betula aetnensis] formations of Mount Etna lavas, limited to the 1200-2000 metre level, mostly within the 1600-1750 metre range, at northern to eastern exposures. The accompanying cortŠge includes [Adenocarpus complicatus], [Genista aetnensis], [Juniperus hemisphaerica], [Festuca circummediterranea].', '(Fenaroli, 1970; Pignatti, 1982; Ferioli, 1989; Pignatti, 1998: 306).');
