    '[Pinus halepensis] forests of the Maltese Islands. Natural forests, formerly widespread, were cut to extinction. A near-natural self-regenerating woodland,  originating from replantation exists on Malta (Buskett). It has a rich undergrowth of [Quercus ilex], [Olea europaea] var. [sylvestris], [Ceratonia siliqua], [Pistacia lentiscus] and other thermomediterranean shrubs, herbs and climbers.', '(Lanfranco, 1999a; Schembri, 1999b). ');
