    'Communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks dominated by shorter, mostly nongraminoid helophytes emerging from mesotrophic or eutrophic, stagnant or slow-moving, shallow water, and constituting fringes or patches within or alongside reedbeds. ', '(Golub and Mirkin, 1986; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Påhlsson, 1994; Hoda y al., 1998: 6).');
    'Formations of [Sagittaria sagittifolia] and [Sparganium emersum] of slowly flowing, and sometimes standing, meso-eutrophic waters of western Eurasia; formations of [Sagittaria sagittifolia], [Sagittaria natans] and [Caltha membranacea] of similar eastern Asian waterbodies.  ', '(Hanso, 1975: 101; Moravec y al., 1983: 29; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 78; Mirkin y al., 1985: 383; Golub and Mirkin, 1986; Delescaille, 1987: 72; Korotkov y al., 1991: 24, 26, 36-37; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 120-121; Hoda y al., 1998: 6; Seliskar, 1998: 15).');
    'Communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks dominated by [Sparganium neglectum], characteristic of standing or slowly flowing waters on mineral-rich, lime-poor muddy substrates.  ', '(Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 114; Ilijanic, 1996: 109).');
    'Communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks dominated by or rich in [Sparganium erectum], characteristic of riparian reedbeds along standing waters on lime-rich, mineral-rich muddy substrates. ', '(Moravec y al., 1983: 28; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 78; Delescaille, 1987: 72; Korotkov y al., 1991: 28; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 91; Seliskar, 1998: 14).');
