    'Communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks, often situated at the edges of reedbeds, rich in [Oenanthe aquatica] or [Rorippa amphibia].', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 183, 273, 404; Moravec y al., 1983: 28; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 78; Korotkov y al., 1991: 36; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 119; Ilijanic, 1996: 109; Seliskar, 1998: 15).');
    'Low, often extensive, homogeneous, usually inundated communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks dominated by [Equisetum fluviatile].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 75; Mäemets, 1974: 37; Horvat y al., 1974: 494; Moravec y al., 1983: 28; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 78; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.3.7 [p.]; Korotkov y al., 1991: 24-25; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 89-90; Påhlsson, 1994: units 3.3.4.1, 5.2.3.7, 6.1.2.1, 6.1.2.5, 7.2.2.4, [p.]; Ilijanic, 1996: 109).');
    'Communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks dominated by or rich in the tall umbellifer [Sium latifolium].  ', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: unit 74).');
    'Communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks, usually of clear, cold to temperate nutrient-rich water, dominated by [Hippuris vulgaris].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 75; Moravec y al., 1983: 29; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 78; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.3.7 [p.]; Mirkin y al., 1985: 383; Korotkov y al., 1991: 36; Oberdorfer, 1992a: 139; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 120-121; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 5.2.3.7 [p.]; Seliskar, 1998: 15).');
    'Low, often extensive and very homogeneous formations of Palaearctic lakeshores, pools and ditches with strongly fluctuating water regime, dominated by [Eleocharis palustris].', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 75; Hadac, 1969: 4-6; Moravec y al., 1983: 28; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 78; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 5.2.3.6a [p.], 6.1.2.5; Korotkov y al., 1991: 23-24; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 120-121; Påhlsson, 1994: units 4.2.4.1, 5.2.3.6b, [p.], 6.1.2.5a; Mossberg y al., 1995: 606; Seliskar, 1998: 15).');
    'Homogeneous [Iris pseudacorus] formations of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, rivers and brooks.', '(Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 79; Korotkov y al., 1991: 33-34; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 108; Ilijanic, 1996: 109).');
    'Communities of the margins of Palaearctic lakes, inland seas and sea inlets, rivers and brooks, eutrophic marshes, swamps and ditches dominated by medium or medium-tall helophyte Poaceae of genera [Glyceria], [Leersia], [Socolochloa] or [Calamagrostis].', '(Jordanoff, 1931; Lebrun y al., 1949; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988; Bournérias, 1979, 1984; Soo, 1980; Noirfalise y al., 1980; Moravec y al., 1983; Matuszkiewicz, 1984; Oberdorfer, 1990; Balatova-Tulackova y al., 1993: 88-89; Mossberg y al., 1995: 560).');
