    'Riparian formations of [Alnus glutinosa], locally of [Alnus cordata] or [Betula spp.] of the Mediterranean basin and of western Iberia, often with [Fraxinus angustifolia] and [Osmunda regalis].  ', '(Bolos, 1979; Dierschke, 1980; Yon and Tendron, 1981; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b).');
    'Riparian [Alnus glutinosa]-dominated multilayered formations of the meso- and supramediterranean levels of the Iberian peninsula, the C¿vennes, the Italic and Hellenic peninsulas.', '(Oberdorfer, 1953; Braun-Blanquet y al., 1956; Maire, 1961; Debazac and Mavrommatis, 1971; Horvat y al., 1974; Rivas-Martinez, 1975c; Bolos, 1979; Dierschke, 1980; Pedrotti, 1980; Molinier and Martin, 1980; Yon and Tendron, 1981; White, 1983; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b; Peinado Lorca y al., 1984; Veri and Pacioni, 1985; Chiappini, 1985b; Izco, 1987; Ladero Alvarez, 1987; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987; Navarro Andres and Valle Gutierrez, 1987; Gamisans, 1991).');
    'Meso-Mediterranean [Alnus glutinosa] riparian galleries of southern Galicia, Portugal, Extremadura, the western Cordillera Central, western Castilla, with [Betula celtiberica], [Salix atrocinerea], [Frangula alnus], [Fraxinus angustifolia], [Celtis australis], many lianas, [Clematis campaniflora], [Humulus lupulus], [Vitis vinifera] ssp. [sylvestris] and an herb layer comprising [Senecio bayonensis], [Galium broterianum], [Scrophularia scorodonia], [Osmunda regalis], [Carex acuta] ssp. [broteriana].  ', '(Braun-Blanquet y al., 1956; Rivas-Martinez, 1975c; Izco, 1987; Ladero Alvarez, 1987; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987; Navarro Andres and Valle Gutierrez, 1987).');
    'Supra-Mediterranean [Alnus glutinosa] riparian galleries of water courses with moderate seasonal fluctuations, of western Iberia, with [Betula celtiberica], [Ilex aquifolium], [Populus tremula] and [Luzula sylvatica] ssp. [henriquesii], [Paris quadrifolia], [Galium broterianum], [Paradisea lusitanicum], [Carex acuta] ssp. [broteriana]. ', '(Peinado Lorca y al., 1984; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1987; Ladero Alvarez, 1987; Navarro Andres and Valle Gutierrez, 1987).');
    '[Alnus glutinosa] riparian galleries of mainland southern France, mediterranean and submediterranean peninsular Italy, mediterranean Corsica, Sardinia, often with [Fraxinus angustifolia].  ', '(Oberdorfer, 1953; Dierschke, 1980; Pedrotti, 1980; Molinier and Martin, 1980; Veri and Pacioni, 1985; Chiappini, 1985b; Gamisans, 1991). ');
    'Low woods or scrubs formed by the multi-stemmed, up to 8m tall [Pinus rotundata] on drier buttes and ridges of raised bogs, acid fens and transition moors of higher Hercynian ranges and associated hills and depressions, in particular, of the Black Forest, the Harz, the Thuringer Wald, the Fichtelgebirge, the Erzgebirge (Metallic Mountains), the eastern Sudeten (Jesenik Mountains), the Bayerischer Wald and the Bohemian Forest (Sumava), the Slavkov Forest, the Czecho-Moravian Hills, the Trebon plain, with [Eriophorum vaginatum], [Vaccinium oxycoccos], [Vaccinium uliginosum], [Vaccinium myrtillus], [Ledum palustre], [Andromeda polifolia], [Sphagnum spp.].', '(Oberdorfer, 1967, 1990; Ozenda, 1975; Petermann and Seibert, 1979; Moravec y al., 1983: 45, 46; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 93, 186-187; Pott, 1992: 354-355; Steiner, 1993: 175-176; Schubert y al., 1995: 103-104; Rybnicek, 1998: 237-243, 302-304).');
    '[Pinus mugo] scrubs, very prostrate or up to 2m tall, developing on drier buttes and ridges of raised bogs, acid fens and transition mires of the alpine zone of the Giant Mountains (Krkonose, Karkonosze, Riesengebirge), of mixed alpine and arctic affinities, with, in particular, [Rubus chamaemorus].', '(Moravec y al., 1983: 45, 46; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 93, 186-187; Rybnicek, 1998: 237-243, 302-304).');
