    'Temperate forests dominated by broad-leaved sclerophyllous or lauriphyllous evergreen trees, or by palms. They are characteristic of the Mediterranean and warm-temperate humid zones, with a few representatives in the nemoral, Irano-Turanian and Saharo-Sindian zones.  ', '(Schweinfurth, 1957; Fenaroli, 1970; Tomaselli, 1970; Knapp, 1973; Zohary, 1973; Horvat y al., 1974; Ortuno and Ceballos, 1977; Ozenda, 1981, 1985; Quézel, 1981b; Debazac, 1983; Satoo, 1983; Fernandez Gonzalez, 1986; Noirfalise, 1987; Peinado-Lorca and Rivas-Martinez, 1987; Wildpret de la Torre and del Arco Aguilar, 1987; Barneschi, 1988; Rieley and Page, 1990; Dallman, 1998).');
    'Thermo-Mediterranean or thermo-Canarian woodland dominated by arborescent [Olea europaea] var. [sylvestris], [Ceratonia siliqua], [Pistacia lentiscus], [Myrtus communis] or, in the Canary Islands, by [Olea europaea] ssp. [cerasiformis] and [Pistacia atlantica]. Most formations will be listed as arborescent matorral (unit 35.12), but a few stands have a sufficiently tall, closed canopy to qualify for this unit.', '(Oberdorfer, 1947; Fenaroli, 1970; Lapraz, 1970; Horvat y al., 1974; Ozenda y al., 1979; Quézel, 1981b; Tomaselli, 1981b; Groppali y al., 1983; White, 1983: 157-158; Noirfalise, 1986; Fernandez Gonzalez, 1986; Asensi Marfil and Diez Garretas, 1987; Rivas-Martinez and Costa, 1987; Serrada y al., 1988; Bousquet, 1992).');
    '[Olea europaea] var. [sylvestris]-dominated formations. A climax olive forest, with [Ceratonia siliqua] and [Pistacia lentiscus] exists on the north flank of Djebel Ichkeul in northern Tunisia. Elsewhere, the communities most resembling olive forest are found in southern Andalusia ([Tamo communis]-[Oleetum sylvestris], extinct?), in Menorca ([Prasio majoris]-[Oleetum sylvestris]), Sardinia, Sicily, Calabria, Crete.', '(Oberdorfer, 1947; Fenaroli, 1970; Knapp, 1973: 474; Horvat y al., 1974; Quézel, 1981b; Tomaselli, 1981b; Groppali y al., 1983; White, 1983: 157-158; Fernandez Gonzalez, 1986; Asensi Marfil and Diez Garretas, 1987; Rivas-Martinez and Costa, 1987; Bousquet, 1992; Jahn and Schönfelder, 1995: 15-16).');
    '[Ceratonia siliqua]-dominated formations, often with [Olea europae] var. [sylvestris] and [Pistacia lentiscus]. The most developed examples, some truly forestlike, are to be found in Tunisia, on the slopes of the Djebel Ichkeul, where they constitute carob-dominated facies of the previous unit, in Mallorca ([Cneoro tricocci-Ceratonietum siliquae]), in eastern Sardinia, in southeastern Sicily, in Puglia, in Crete, in northeastern Algeria, in Cyrenaica.', '(Oberdorfer, 1947; Fenaroli, 1970; Knapp, 1973: 474; Horvat y al., 1974; Quézel, 1981b; Tomaselli, 1981b; Groppali y al., 1983; Rivas-Martinez and Costa, 1987; Bousquet, 1992).');
