    'Montane moist forests of the western Himalayas dominated by [Quercus semecarpifolia], [Quercus dilatata] or [Quercus ballota], limited, within the Palaearctic region as here defined, to Nuristan, and to the slopes and valleys of the Hindu Kush, west to central northern Afghanistan.', '(Schweinfurth, 1957; Gopal and Meher-Homji, 1983; Walter and Breckle, 1991c:198-201).  ');
