    'Mires of the subarctic and northern boreal regions of the Palaearctic domaine formed by a net-like or mosaic alternance of frozen mounds or ridges (palsas), 0.50 to 8 metres high, and of wet hollows, distributed in the discontinuous permafrost zone of Iceland and northern Fennoscandia, in the northern Kola Peninsula tundra and forested tundra zones, the Kanin Peninsula, the shrub tundra and forested tundra zones of the lower Pechora lowlands, north of the Arctic circle, the northern taiga, forested tundra and southern tundra zones of the Kara coastlands and hinterland in the middle and upper reaches of the Usa River, southern Nova¿a Zemlia, the northern taiga and southern forested tundra zones of the West Siberian plain, between the Ob and the Yenissei, the middle Siberian northern taiga and forested tundra zones of the Yenissei, lower Tunguska and stony Tunguska basins and uplands, south to the mouth of the Angara, in areas of more then 200 days of sub-zero temperatures and relative winter dryness, with limited snowfall.', '(Salmi, 1970: 143-152; Schenk, 1970a: 157; Svensson, 1970: 161-164; Ruuhijärvi, 1970: 322-323; Schenk, 1970b: 338-339; Walter, 1974: 31-40; Goodwillie, 1980: 10; Ruuhijärvi, 1983: 60-62; Sjörs, 1983: 87; Botch and Masing, 1983: 110, 112-113; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: 213; Polunin and Walters, 1985: 27-28; Walter and Breckle, 1986: 461-465; Succow and Jeschke, 1990: 69-70, 182-185; Påhlsson, 1994: 211, 215; Pakarinen, 1995: 30, 32).');
