    'Almost pure swards of [Eriophorum scheuchzeri] fringing small, cold, acidic lakes above the tree limit. Permanently inundated, they include few other vascular plants, limited to a few individuals of [Carex nigra], [Carex rostrata], [Carex lachenalii], [Carex brunnescens], [Juncus filiformis], [Eriophorum angustifolium], [Deschampsia cespitosa]; the moss [Drepanocladus exannulatus] is usually present and abundant.', '(Duvigneaud, 1949: 95; Braun-Blanquet, 1954: 28-29; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988: 428; Braun-Blanquet, 1971a; Guinochet and Vilmorin, 1978; Dierssen, 1978: 418; Oberdorfer, 1990: 37; Oberdorfer, 1992a: 234-239; Pott, 1992: 179; Steiner, 1992: 144-145; Steiner, 1993: 144-145; Julve, 1993: 75; Trpin and Vres, 1995: 41).');
