    'Rock and cliff crevice communities of granites, gneisses and acidic rocks of the boreal and arctic zones of the Palaearctic domaine.', '(Walter, 1974; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Rock and cliff crevice communities of granites, gneisses and acidic rocks of the mountains and uplands of the boreal and arctic zones of the western Palaearctic domaine, in particular of Fennoscandia and Iceland.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.1.1.1; Påhlsson, 1994: units 7.1.1.1, 7.1.1.2 [p.], 7.1.1.3 [p.]).');
    'Rock and cliff communities of boreal Fennoscandian and Icelandic granites, gneisses and acidic rocks, generally occurring in the humus accumulation of crevices and comprising few genuine chasmophytes, dominated by variable, usually paucispecific assemblies in which [Asplenium septentrionale], [Asplenium trichomanes], [Potentilla argentea] are often prominent.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.1.1.1; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 7.1.1.1).');
    'Rock and cliff communities of southern and middle Fennoscandian granite, gneiss and acidic sediment glacier-fashioned flat-top rock outcrops with dense lichen carpets, formed, in particular, by [Cladonia rangiferina], mosses, scrubs and sometimes sparse grasses and forbs. [Calluna vulgaris], [Deschampsia flexuosa], [Silene rupestris] are characteristic. Part of the communities may constitute more or less open [Pinus sylvestris] woods of unit 42, or [Calluna vulgaris] heaths of unit 31.2.', '(Påhlsson, 1994: unit 7.1.1.2 [p.]).');
    'Rock and cliff communities of southern and middle Fennoscandian granite or gneiss, sometimes with amphibolite or gabbro, glacier-fashioned flat-top rock outcrops with a varied lichen, moss and vascular plant cover, formed, in particular, by [Deschampsia flexuosa], [Woodsia ilvensis], [Lychnis viscaria]. Part of the communities may constitute more or less open [Pinus sylvestris] woods of unit 42, or [Juniperus communis] thickets of unit 31.8.', '(Påhlsson, 1994: unit 7.1.1.3 [p.]).');
    'Siliceous rock and cliff communities of the mountains and uplands of the boreal and arctic zones of the central Palaearctic domaine. Included are the communities of the Chibiny range, of the Urals, of the chains of northern central Siberia, from the Putorany to the Tscherski range and of the mountains of southern Siberia, from the Altai to the Stanowoi range.', '(Walter, 1974: 23, 347).');
    'Siliceous rock and cliff communities of the mountains and uplands of the boreal and arctic zones of the eastern Palaearctic domaine. Included are the communities of the Anadyr, Tschuktschi, Korjak, Kamchatka, Amurland and Sakalin mountains.', '(Walter, 1974: 23, 47, 49).');
