    'Fens of the montane and subalpine levels of Vitosha, characterized by the cooccurrence of acidopilous and basophilous plants. They are dominated by [Carex nigra] and [Carex echinata] or by [Eriophorum latifolium], [Eriophorum angustifolium], [Eriophorum vaginatum], accompanied by [Carex panicea], [Carex pallescens], [Dactylorhiza cordigera], [Pinguicula vulgaris], [Primula farinosa] ssp. [exigua], [Alchemilla bulgarica], [Cirsium heterotrichum], [Soldanella hungarica], [Gymnadenia frivaldii], [Juncus spp.], [Sphagnum spp.]   ', '(Soo, 1957b; Horvat y al., 1974: 520).');
