    'Bryophyte dominated communities of cold, oxygen-rich, soft-water springs and small mountain becks of alpine and lowland Iceland and of the Faeroe Islands formed by [Philonotis fontana], with, in Iceland, [Pohlia wahlenbergii] ([Pohlia albicans]), accompanied by a sparse formation of vascular plants in which [Saxifraga stellaris], [Cerastium cerastoides], [Epilobium alsinifolium], [Montia fontana] or [Agrostis stolonifera] may be dominant, while, at high altitudes, [Ranunculus pygmaeus] and [Saxifraga rivularis] are characteristic. The vascular cortŠge also includes [Caltha palustris], [Cardamine pratensis], [Epilobium anagallidifolium], [Epilobium hornemanni], [Epilobium lactiflorum], [Epilobium palustre], [Equisetum arvense], [Equisetum palustre], [Juncus biglumis], [Deschampsia alpina], [Phleum alpinum]. The spring communities of this unit often border onto the black sedge alkaline fen communities of unit 54.263, many of whose components may encroach on the spring community.', '(Vanden Berghen, 1969b: 81; Hadac, 1971a: 30-32; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 3.6.6.2b; Hadac, 1985a: 152-154; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 3.5.1.3a).');
