    'More or less level surfaces of siliceous rocks of lowlands and hills of the boreonemoral and boreal zones of the Palaearctic, in particular, flat tops of southern and middle Fennoscandian granite, gneiss and acidic sediment glacier-fashioned rock outcrops. They are often colonized by lichen communities of unit 62.32, by mosses and by scrub, grass and forb fissure communities of unit 62.2A.', '(Einarsson, 1994; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 7.1.1.2 [p.], 7.1.1.3 [p.]; Gudmundsson and Kjartansson, 1996).');
    'More or less level surfaces of siliceous rock of lowlands, hills and low mountains of the nemoral zone of the Palaearctic, in particular, sandstone slabs of north central and eastern France.', '(Bournérias, 1984: 83, 136-138, 147-149, 221-222; Arnal, 1996: 31, 35-41, 49-51, 65-69, 204; Sell y al., 1998: 29).');
    'Briophyte-rich communities of lime-poor cold springs of the subalpine and alpine zones of boreoalpine and arctoalpine mountains of Fennoscandia and of Iceland, characterized by a greater abundance of tall herbs than in the communities of units 54.1112 to 54.1115, in particular, of units 54.1112 and 54.1113, to which they are closely related, with a resulting lesser prominence of the moss carpet, dominated by [Pohlia wahlenbergii] ssp. [glacialis] ([Pohlia albicans] f. [glacialis]) or [Philonotis fontana]. The communities of this unit may grade into [Potentilla crantzii]-[Bistorta vivipara] communities of unit 36.12361 and moist [Dryas] heaths of unit 31.49323.', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 3.6.6.4; Hadac, 1985a: 150-155; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 3.5.1.2).');
    'Briophyte-rich communities of lime-poor cold springs of Iceland, similar to the Icelandic spring communities of unit 54.1112, but somewhat drier, dominated by [Philonotis fontana], with [Pohlia wahlenbergii] ssp. [glacialis] ([Pohlia albicans] f. [glacialis]), [Pseudobryum cinclidiois], [Bryum pseudotriquetrum], [Drepanocladus exanulatus], [Plagiomnium elatum], [Calliiergon giganteum], [Philonotis seriata], [Bryum duvalii]. The species cortŠge includes [Bartsia alpina], [Cardamine nymanii], [Rhodiola rosea], [Epilobium anagallidifolium], [Epilobium palustre], [Salix callicarpaea] ([Salix arctica]), [Saxifraga hirculum], [Saxifraga rivularis], [Festuca richardsonii], [Deschampsia alpina], [Poa alpina], [Poa pratensis] [s.l.], [Equisetum palustre].
', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 3.6.6.4 [p.]; Hadac, 1985a: 150-155; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 3.5.1.2 [p.]).');
    'Briophyte-rich communities of lime-poor cold springs of the subalpine and alpine zones of boreoalpine and arctoalpine mountains of Fennoscandia dominated by [Pohlia wahlenbergii] ssp. [glacialis] ([Pohlia albicans] f. [glacialis]),  with [Brachythecium rivulare], [Bryum curvatum], [Philonotis tomentella], [Philonotis seriata], [Scapania uliginosa]. The vascular species cortŠge includes [Alchemilla glabra], [Angelica archangelica], [Caltha palustris], [Cerastium cerastoides], [Epilobium alsinifolium], [Epilobium hornemannii], [Geum rivale], [Koeningia islandica], [Montia fontana], [Petasites frigidus], [Ranunculus acre], [Ranunculus hyperboreus], [Rumex acetosa] ssp. [lapponicus], [Salix herbacea], [Salix lanata], [Saxifraga stellaris], [Sedum villosum], [Polygonum viviparum], [Agrostis stolonifera], [Deschampsia caespitosa], [Phleum alpinum], [Equisetum arvense], [Petasites frigidus], [Salix glauca], [Saussurea alpina], [Stellaria nemorum], [Arctogrostis latifolia]. Many variants exist depending on species dominance. ', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 3.6.6.4 [p.]; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 3.5.1.2 [p.]).');
    'Bryophyte and encrusting lichen communities of lime-poor, often intermittent, springs of the high-alpine level of Palaearctic mountains of the Alpine system, formed by the lichen [Dermatocarpon rivulorum] and the mosses [Brachythecium glaciale], [Schistidium rivulare]. ', '(Zechmeister, 1993: 227-229). ');
    'Bryophyte and small herb communities of shallow depressions filled by thaw water in permafrost areas, in particular, of Spitzbergen, constituted by the mosses [Calliergon sarmentosum], [Drepanocladus exannulatus], [Drepanocladus uncinatus], [Aulacomnium palustre], [Philonotis tomentella], [Bryum pallens], [Oncophorus wahlenbergii], and by [Ranunculus hyperboreus], [Ranunculus sulphureus], [Saxifraga foliolosa], [Saxifraga rivularis], [Saxifraga cernua], [Cardamine nymanii], [Phippsia algida], [Alopecurus alpinus], [Luzula confusa], [Equisetum boreale]. ', '(Hadac, 1989: 142-146; Safronova and Glazovskij, 1995; Ronning, 1996: 167).');
    'Spring communities of mostly collinar and montane, shaded waters poor in lime  of the Palaearctic domaine, with [Ranunculus hederaceus], [Cardamine amara], [Cardamine flexuosa], [Cardamine raphanifolia], [Chrysosplenium oppositifolium], [Chrysosplenium alternifolium], [Saxifraga clusii] ssp. [lepismigena], ranging southwest to the Cordillera Cantabrica.', '(Lebrun y al., 1949: unit 70; Ellenberg, 1963, 1988: 430-431; Westhoff and den Held, 1975: 192-193; Matuszkiewicz and Matuszkiewicz, 1975: 105; Schumacher, 1977; Bournérias, 1979, 1984; Soo, 1980: 527; Moravec y al., 1983: 38; Hadac, 1983: 341-342; Matuszkiewicz, 1984: 75; Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b: 186-187, 189; Oberdorfer, 1990; Korotkov y al., 1991: 252; Rodwell, 1991b: 29, unit M36; Coldea, 1991: 412-416; Pott, 1992: 173-174; Oberdorfer, 1992a: 208-209; Zechmeister, 1993: 216-220; Schubert y al., 1995: 217-218).');
    'Soft water spring and rivulet communities of the high altitudes of the mountains of the southern Palaearctic.', '(Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b: 188-189, 230; Martinez Parras y al., 1987; Gamisans, 1991: 314, 346-348, 354; Julve, 1993: 10).');
    'Spring and rivulet communities of high Iberian mountains, characteristic of the oro- and cryo-Mediterranean levels of the Cordillera Cantabrica, and of the Cordillera Central, the Iberian Range, the Sierra Nevada, with [Myosotis stolonifera], [Veronica langei], [Festuca rivularis], [Stellaria alsine], [Saxifraga stellaris] ssp. [alpigena].  ', '(Rivas-Martinez y al., 1984b: 188-189, 230; Martinez Parras y al., 1987).');
    'Soft water spring and rivulet communities of subalpine and alpine levels of the mountains of Corsica.', '(Gamisans, 1991: 314, 346-348, 354, 361; Julve, 1993: 10).');
