    '[Dryopteris villarii]-dominated formations of calcareous screes of the east Adriatic mountains, widespread in the Dinarides and Pelagonides, with [Doronicum columnae], [Ligusticum dinaricum], [Scrophularia bosniaca].', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 601-603; Seliskar, 1998: 13).');
    '[Petasites paradoxus]-dominated formations of the foot and grooves of calcareous scree slopes of the Dinarides and Pelagonides.', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 601-603; Seliskar, 1998: 13).');
