    'Screes of the mountains and uplands of the boreal and arctic zones of the Palaearctic domaine.', '(Hadac, 1971b: 106-107; Walter, 1974; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Géhu, 1984a; Påhlsson, 1994; Fredskild, 1998, 2000).');
    'Communities of noncalcareous screes of the mountains and uplands of the boreal zone of the western Palaearctic domaine, developed on siliceous substrates or on basic to ultrabasic igneous or metamorphic substrates. Included are the screes of Greenland, Iceland, the Faeroes and Fennoscandia, around the rim of the western polar basin, in regions of Atlantic climate influence.', '(Hadac, 1971b: 106-107; Nordiska ministerradet, 1984; Påhlsson, 1994).');
    'Open pioneer communities of nutrient-rich, noncalcareous screes of the subalpine and low alpine levels of the boreoalpine and arctoalpine mountains of Fennoscandia and of the foot of west- or southwest-facing slopes of alpine southwestern Iceland, often composed of a mixture of lowland and alpine species, with an absence of chalk-dependant species; characteristic species include [Veronica fruticans], [Epilobium angustifolium], [Convallaria majalis], [Poa glauca], [Poa nemoralis].', '(Nordiska ministerradet, 1984: unit 1.1.4.1; Påhlsson, 1994: unit 7.1.4.1).');
