    'Calcareous cliff and rock communities of the Dalmatian mesomediterranean zone, with the endemic [Centaurea ragusina] and [Convolvulus cneorum].', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 144; Ilijanic, 1996: 110-111).');
    'Calcareous cliff and rock communities of the central and southern parts of the Dalmatian mesomediterranean zone, with [Moltkia petraea].', '(Horvat y al., 1974: 144; Ilijanic, 1996: 110).');
    'More or less open grasslands constituting the second stage of succession in the colonisation of Pontic dunes. Detailed communities can be indicated by addition of codes identifying subunits of 34.A212.', '(Vicherek, 1972; Walter, 1974; Horvat y al., 1974; Sanda y al., 1980; Bondev, 1991; Donita, 1992; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992; Donita and Ivan, 1992a, 1992b; Sanda y al., 1992; Hanganu y al., 1994).');
    'Closed swards of basophilous, humus- and nutrient-rich, sandy or mixed sand-loessy soils of Pontic fixed dunes.  Detailed communities can be indicated by addition of codes identifying units 34.A213 or 34.A214.  ', '(Vicherek, 1972; Walter, 1974; Boscaiu, 1975; Popescu and Sanda, 1976; Sanda y al., 1980; Sanda y al., 1987; Donita, 1992; Donita and Ivan, 1992a, 1992b).');
    'Formations of large shrubs colonizing Pontic dunes. ', '(Vicherek, 1972; Horvat y al., 1974; Walter, 1974; Popescu and Sanda, 1976; Bondev, 1991; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992; Donita and Ivan, 1992b; Sanda y al., 1992).');
    'Natural woods installed within Pontic dune systems. Their composition can be specified by use of codes of 41. ', '(Vicherek, 1972; Horvat y al., 1974; Walter, 1974; Popescu and Sanda, 1976; Bondev, 1991; Chifu and Mititelu, 1992; Donita and Ivan, 1992b; Sanda y al., 1992).');
    'Dunes of the wooded steppe belt occupying, north of the Pontic and Caspian plains, the southern edge and valleys of the Podolian, Central Russian and Volga plateaux east to the Volga-Kama trough (unit 34.922).', '(Vicherek, 1972; Walter, 1974).');
    'Dunes of the steppe and wooded steppe belts of extreme eastern Europe and western Siberia, extending from the Volga-Kama system in the west to the Tarbagatai and western Altai in the east, including the Transvolgan steppes of Orenburg and Bachkiria, the Kurgan, Ishim, Baraba, Kulunda, Barnaul, Kirgiz, Kazakh steppes, and the mountain steppes of the Tarbagatai and the Altai (unit 34.93).', '(Walter, 1974).');
    'Dunes of the East Asian steppes (unit 34.94) of Transbaikalia, Outer Mongolia, Inner Mongolia, the Songnen Plain of Northeast China, the western Loess Plateau of North China, the mountain steppes of the Tien Shan, from the rim of the Naryn and Isyk-K¿l basins eastwards, of the Sayan and Tannu mountains, in particular, of the steppes of Inner Mongolia and Manchuria. ', '(Knapp and Sancir, 1986; Walter, 1974: 223-224).');
    'Inland dunes of the Anatolian Plateau, of Transcaucasia, of the Iranian Plateau and of northern Mesopotamia, in the Irano-Anatolian zone of transition between the continental Eurasian steppes and the Mediterranean and southern Palaearctic desert zones, of the eastern cis-Caucasian hills of Daghestan and the Terek basin, the Kopet Dagh, the Pamir-Alai, the extreme western Tien-Shan. ', '(Zohary, 1973; Walter, 1974; Walter and Breckle, 1986, 1991c).');
